<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><gpx xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" version="1.0" creator="Groundspeak, Inc.All Rights Reserved.http://www.groundspeak.com" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0 http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0/gpx.xsd http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1 http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1/cache.xsd" xmlns="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0"><name>Cache Listing Generated from Geocaching.com</name><desc>This is an individual cache generated from Geocaching.com</desc><email>contact@geocaching.com</email><url>http://www.geocaching.com</url><urlname>Geocaching - High Tech Treasure Hunting</urlname><time>2026-06-02T21:38:02.180317Z</time><keywords>cache, geocache</keywords><wpt lat="33.495933" lon="-85.8077"><time>2006-07-14T00:00:00</time><name>GCWXQ4</name><desc>Cache Across America - Alabama by wesleykey - Adopted by CaverScott</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCWXQ4</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Alabama</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="420862" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Alabama</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>wesleykey - Adopted by CaverScott</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="539423">CaverScott</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Alabama</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>New hide effective March 15, 2011. New Container as of January 8, 2014. Now the container is an Ammo Box as of March 26, 2015. Please place the logbook inside the two ziplocs. Reminder - If you really enjoy this cache, please add a Fav Point!
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Alabama&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/Flag_of_Alabama.svg/744px-Flag_of_Alabama.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Montgomery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Birmingham&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 30th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 23rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 22nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series. Once you log the Alabama find and post your photo, email the CO and I will provide the Alabama Code for the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Cheaha State Park is a beautiful park containing great views from Alabama's highest point. This cache used to be an ammo box with of course ALABAMA painted on it, but frequent thefts have left a full size tupperware container for a couple of years. As of March 26, 2015 it was upgraded to a small ammo box again. PLEASE HIDE IT WELL. It is located just off a 1/4 mile long wheelchair access trail. See the gallery of pictures for more information. PLEASE rehid this well. Cover it with loose stones and lots of leaves! It has gone missing at least FOUR times!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. (If the code is no longer in the cache, please email the this CO after posting your photo and he will email you the code.) Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Go downhill to the right of Bald Rock between the two big outcroppings. Turn left at the bottom of the rocks outcropping and you should see the Slingshot shapped tree. Look at the base, downhill side, hole in bottom of the tree. Cache is covered with leaves and a rock in the tree hole. PLEASE HIDE WELL</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1359395697"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-05T15:34:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="595183">A-Cran</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Camping at Cheaha so decided to check this one out almost 11 years to the day after the first time. Thanks for maintaining!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359018014"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8050763">Gixboy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc! Decided to visit cheaha state park on our way home to atlanta</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356138195"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-19T13:29:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="272017">DanielSan</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">With the deadfall on the ground, we slipped and slid all the way down to the cash location.But it was in great shape. Glad to put my hands-on a actual cash out here in this park. Thanks.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356138536"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2029058">SlimSmitty</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Really enjoying the park and all the views here. This was a bit of a challenge to get to the cache due to the loose leaves sliding around. Read the hint and zeroed in though. Out on a post tax season tour with DanielSan to get Alabama counties and some high points. Threw in some caches of interest along the way as well. Thanks for the fun!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356489862"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="598646">tdb1977</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day 3 of my trip through the southeast states this weekend.  I am targeting counties, the oldest in several states and the CAA in those states as well.  Today was a 21 find day that started in Trussville and ended up in Augusta, GA.

When I set this trip up, I had to get the CAA caches in each of the states that we were traveling through.  This was the first CAA that I would get on this trip.  We made our way down the nice boardwalk and then did a little bit of scrambling at the end to come up with the find.  I will someday complete all the rest of the CAA's, but in the mean time, this is my 24th CAA cache that I find.  All is well here.  Thanks for the cache.  Took nothing, left nothing.  Signed the log, took my picture, recorded the 3 digit number, and placed back where it was found.

TDB1977</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="61.487067" lon="-149.2599"><time>2011-06-17T00:00:00</time><name>GC2YDRF</name><desc>Cache Across America - Alaska (Version 2.0) by AKStafford</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC2YDRF</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Alaska (Version 2.0)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2313113" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Alaska (Version 2.0)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>AKStafford</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="410459">AKStafford</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="0">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Alaska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The first version of this cache was muggled one too many times... So we've redone it. Winter accessibility will depend on how much snow there is...
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Alaska&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Flag_of_Alaska.svg/709px-Flag_of_Alaska.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Juneau&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Anchorage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 1st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 47th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 49th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; The Alaskan Cache is placed along the Reflection Lake Trail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To the south is the Chugach Mountains which are included in the Chugach State Park &amp;amp; the Chugach National Forest, America's 2nd largest national forest. To the southeast is the Knik Glacier and the northeast is the Matanuska Glacier. To the north is the Talkeetna Mountains. Gold was discover there in the early 1900's. The village of Knik, along the Knik arm sprung up as an unloading point for supplies to be hauled up to the mine. Unloading could only be done on high tide, so incoming boats would wait at the mouth of Ship Creek, which become known as the Knik Anchorage. In 1916 when the Alaska Railroad was being built they chose this area as their construction headquarters and the name was shorten to just Anchorage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reflection Lake is part of the Palmer Hay Flats State Game Refuge. Cache is winter accesible, but a little more challenging...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
