&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Wilmington&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 49th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 45th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 1st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series
&lt;a rel="nofollow"
href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=bf517972-5f45-4ed9-ac4b-afbde9231a6c"&gt;
HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle"
bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg"
     width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a
series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire
United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These
caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to
&lt;a rel="nofollow"
href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;
one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion
of the series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Local men working for the
Public Works Administration built the pavilion in the 1930's during
the Great Depression. All the supporting beams &amp;amp; benches were
replaced in 2005-2006. The Observation/photography blind offer a
chance to watch wildlife undisturbed &amp;amp; upclose. Ocean City MD
&amp;amp; Fenwick (DE) Lighthouse can be seen across the Little
Assawoman Bay to the south.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a little known area, hardest thing is finding it, it is
just off Route 1 near Bethany Beach. As you travel to it, there is
a mailbox by the red barn before the entrance to the tract where
you can get auto-tour maps. There is hunting in season, park is
open 7am to dusk, the dirt driveways can easily be travelled by
vehicles but get narrow in some areas. Cache is hidden &amp;amp; not
removable unless by force, please rehid as well as before so it can
not be easily seen. DO NOT go into the wildlife refuge area, it is
well marked &amp;amp; closed off to human or domestic animal traffic.
Horses &amp;amp; dogs are allowed but if your dog has a tendancy to run
uncontrolled then please keep them leashed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(&lt;a rel="nofollow"
href="http://www.fw.delaware.gov/Hunting/Pages/HuntingSeasons.aspx"
target="_blank"&gt;DE hunting seasons link&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Caches only
available on Sundays during hunting season from Sept 1st until Feb
31st.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Permission granted by Region 3 Fish and Wildlife
Management for cache placement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img514.imageshack.us/img514/2572/fwcol75ru2.gif" /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you
would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant
in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself
or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you
for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please
make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual
cache owner (make note of secret code on inner lid &amp;amp; notebook).
There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required
before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three
digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure
place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all
50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good
luck!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
