     border="0"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Click To Rate This Cache&lt;/a&gt;--&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>look for the box where you can see birds but they can not see you.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="437481345"><groundspeak:date>2014-08-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hooray!  The new Cache Across America - Delaware is published and ready to be found!  For those of you working on the series the new owner is someone VERY familiar to you…the one and only flyingmoose who is the man behind keeping the Final cache available to all!

We are so excited that the new cache will be available to all as flyingmoose went the extra mile in getting permission to place the new CAA DE in beautiful Delaware Seashore State Park! [^]  Great job, sir!

The bookmarks have been updated and the new cache can be found here:

http://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC59ZYA_cache-across-america-delaware?guid=f55ca0f5-299b-47b6-940b-9a77f660cce9</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="425140409"><groundspeak:date>2014-07-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">CAA Watchers:  There is a new CAA DE in the works.  The new owner has chosen NOT to use this area.  While beautiful, there has been too much trouble with muggling over the past few months.  The new cache will be published in a state park nearer the beach.  We hope to have it up and available in the next two weeks.  Thanks for your patience...</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="422665562"><groundspeak:date>2014-07-06T18:20:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="609591">OReviewer</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">As there's been no response to the earlier reviewer note, I am archiving this cache.  

If you wish to repair/replace the cache sometime in the future, just contact us (by email, include the GC Code), and assuming it meets the guidelines, we'll be happy to unarchive it.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="410812415"><groundspeak:date>2014-05-27T06:37:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="609591">OReviewer</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The cache appears to be in need of owner intervention. I'm temporarily disabling it, to give the owner an opportunity to check on the cache, and take whatever action is necessary. Please respond to this situation in a timely manner (i.e., within 30 days) to prevent the cache from being archived for non-responsiveness.
[size=1][beige]#bf07c5357286a79ea8cb32cbc18c8834[/beige][/size]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="409145935"><groundspeak:date>2014-05-21T16:42:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Lorriebird here. At the request of Blue Power Rangers I have accepted the continuing maintenance of the Cache Across America Series.

My apologies to those currently participating in the Cache Across America quest. We are aware that the CAA Delaware is missing, and have done everything we can to contact the owner about getting a replacement up and running. We have written several emails over this past 2 months but unfortunately have not received a response. We have also attempted to adopt out this cache to no avail. We wish the CO well and thank them for their years of commitment on keeping this CAA Delaware running for several years.  But the CAA series of caches are now busier than ever, and we must move forward with a new CAA Delaware cache with a current and active owner.

I know there are several cross country road trips in progress at the moment and understand completely how critical it is to get the great state of Delaware back up and running. We are working on getting a new Cache Across America Delaware published as soon as we possibly can.

Thank you for your patience.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="28.91415" lon="-81.5445833333333"><time>2006-10-16T00:00:00</time><name>GCYXHW</name><desc>cache across america - florida by spot-trotter</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCYXHW</url><urlname>cache across america - florida</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Multi-cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="480281" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>cache across america - florida</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>spot-trotter</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="242149">spot-trotter</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Multi-cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="1">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="1">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Florida</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="4" style="width:76%;"&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td rowspan="4"&gt;
			&lt;h2&gt;Florida&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;img height="135" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Flag_of_Florida.svg/750px-Flag_of_Florida.svg.png" width="187" /&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Capital: Tallahassee&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Largest City: Jacksonville&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Size Rank: 22nd&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Population Rank: 4th&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Admission to Union: 27th&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41" rel="nofollow"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style="vertical-align:middle;"&gt;
			&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img height="221" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7" rel="nofollow"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation&amp;#39;s capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache: &lt;/strong&gt;As of May 2024, all stages are present and visible. Due to the inordinate amount of people who have not been able to find the stages, I am going to leave the puzzle I posted when stage 3 was under water: follow the trail to the edge of Lake Norris, listen for 30 seconds for the cries of Osprey. The number of cries you hear will be equal to &amp;quot;Y&amp;quot;. Back track to the canoe storage hut that you passed on the way in (where stage 3 is hidden). Count how many canoes CAN be stored there. (Just in case someone happens to be using one and it&amp;#39;s spot is empty. spoiler - this will be an EVEN number) The number of canoe parking spaces will be equal to &amp;quot;X&amp;quot; Work the following problem. North = 28 55. (x+1)(x+5)(x-3) West = 81 33. x (x+5)(x+4) You will notice that &amp;quot;Y&amp;quot; did not enter the equation. I just wanted to get you to the lake for the view. Would hate for you to come all that way and miss it!! Enjoy. This cache is located in north central Florida. Near here highway 44 runs east to west across the state and runs approximately one hour to each shore. The cache is in Lake Norris Preserve which was acquired by the St. John&amp;#39;s Water Management District for the state of Florida and is managed by the Lake County Water Authority.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Blackwater Creek ambles through the property, giving park goers a chance to see a true Florida swamp. The trail takes you back to the shores of Lake Norris where you can sit on a cypress knee and watch osprey fish in the lake. Continuing on to the final cache you can enjoy the freshness of a planted pine forest. This area was once a cattle ranch (Florida is still the 2nd largest producer of beef in the nation) and is still used to graze cattle today. So, watch where you walk, and shut the gate behind you!&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The first set of co-ordinates will take you to the next set of co-ordinates, etc., until you reach the 4th and final stage. Each stage has it&amp;#39;s own hint. Along the way enjoy what cracker country used to be like. Cache contents are dedicated to the Florida cracker (ie. cowboy) and include a horse shoe, an old gray mare, a set of spurs, pink bandana (in honor of the cracker girls) and some trinkets to trade with the Indians. Included for the FTF, if they care for it, are a geocaching window decal, a pill container for hiding micros and travel bug dogtags.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Substitute numbers for new cords
Everyone seems to be stumped by the third stage. 
I guess I kneed to let you know, it looks just like the first two...
BIG SPOILER!!!!
Unless you are on your own version of Spot, you will have to climb on something to find stage two. Climbing aparatus has been provided.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364443148"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T15:34:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1853544">yackadus</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is my 5th find out of 6 attempted Cache Across America hides. It was very reminiscent of the one I failed to find in Minnesota, where we were thwarted by massive mosquitoes and bailed at ground zero. Although the mosquitos weren't bad here, I felt like there were a number of hazards and irritants... No see ums, massive snapping turtle, lone star ticks, fire ants, deer flies, banana spiders and the heat. But that's FL in a nutshell isn't it. Haha. Anyway. I spent way too long looking for the stage one and not having any service. We drove back to where we got service again and read the description better. This was certainly an adventure as I decided to run the length of the hike while smileyearthgirl took things more casually. 

Thanks for the cache and helping me add one more to my Cache Across America journey. Travelled down here from Maine. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352715005"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-03T14:46:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15590652">marbles2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Glad it was April and not August. Wish it had been evening and not midday. Thanks to Mr Toad for pushing me to get it when it was out of the way and in the opposite direction of our final destination. And thanks to Mr Toad for pushing the up and coming geocacher in the stroller. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352698584"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-03T13:59:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15546098">Mr J Thadeus Toad</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found on a hot afternoon after a long with my our grandson in a stroller!  Found with Marbles2.  I think this is close to #30 for the s for CAA. Thank you!  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351309461"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-26T18:04:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5377235">AngelusCowl</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an adventure this was for my penultimate find (for now) in Florida!

For the better part of three years, I’ve lived in the Orlando area, and always meant to come get this one, but never made the time. With my move north impending very soon, I finally made time after work today to make the trek up here. Didn’t get to park quite where I wanted to, and began the pleasant, but long, hike along this multi. Found the final after a decent search, I think this is my 13th completed in this series. Thank you for the lovely hike that highlights the natural side of Florida that sometimes gets lost near the theme parks and tourism. TFTC! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349430827"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12885796">EJKPBR</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings from the owner of the CAA Colorado. 
This one was a tad out of the way but o knew i just had to add it to the list. 
Luckily I did all the correct assumptions from home and found the cache in is most likely home. 
I should've wore pants because I ended up drawing blood in more than one body part. 
‐----------------------------

I came down to Florida to watch the Minnesota Twins at Spring Training. A bucketlist trip I've been wanting to do for over a decade.

But a trip to Florida wouldn't be complete without a visit to the Keys. And the Everglades and the Cape and and and......... GEOCACHES!!!

I am on a 5 day whirlwind geocaching tour of the state.

My route should take me on a 1,500 mile journey around Florida. I plan on getting a cache in 22 new counties, at least 60 caches worth over 10,000 favorite points. And I will witness all the sights and sounds Florida has to offer through the windows of a rental campervan.

Follow my journey on my Instagram account @EJKPBR

Thank you spot-trotter for placing and maintaining "cache across america - florida" for me to find and log. Sunday March 15, 2026 1:25 PM</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="33.316433" lon="-83.844067"><time>2006-06-30T00:00:00</time><name>GCWP4X</name><desc>Cache Across America - Georgia by Rebel (adopted by Biker64 &amp; then by Team Bear-Cat)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCWP4X</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Georgia</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="414531" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Georgia</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Rebel (adopted by Biker64 &amp; then by Team Bear-Cat)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="272266">Team Bear-Cat</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Georgia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="4" width="76%"&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966" width="190"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center"&gt;Georgia&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/user/66e2cbdf-cd6a-431c-ae5d-909d9ba7978c.jpg" height="135" width="187" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Atlanta&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Atlanta&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 24th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 9th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 4th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td align="center" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" height="48" valign="middle" width="693"&gt;
&lt;h1 class="style1" align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" height="221" width="450" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" height="61"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is placed near the geographic center of population for the state of Georgia. It's a lovely location near the Ocmulgee River and very close to a good place to snag some bream or get your feet wet. The Ocmulgee River flows through most of the state and empties into the Atlantic Ocean near Savannah.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache itself is not too far from a good parking area and muggles, during the week, should not be a problem. Please hide the cache back better than you found it. Have fun!.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#CCCCCC" height="61"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.wunderground.com/US/GA/Jackson.html?bannertypeclick=miniWeather2"&gt;&lt;img src="http://banners.wunderground.com/weathersticker/miniWeather2_cond/language/www/US/GA/Jackson.gif" alt="Click for Jackson, Georgia Forecast" border="0" height="50" width="150" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;Congratulations to the First to Find(ers)!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#FF0000"&gt;Maviman &amp;amp; Gingingman&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;Congratulations to the First to Find(ers) of the Entire Series!!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#FF0000"&gt;ZSteve &amp;amp; Hopperzx&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;big&gt;&lt;big&gt;Find me on FaceBook at: &lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/Biker64.GA" target="_blank"&gt;Biker64&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365033864"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T16:16:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9366409">rickdorsey8080</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Made the most of my Atlanta layover Tuesday by renting a car and driving down to this spot to claim my 33rd CAA. The traffic both ways on I-75 made me nervous but I was still able to navigate to get to the state park. Once there, I parked inside and took a short hike through the greenery to get to the obvious hiding spot. I've got 2 more to go to knock out the North coordinates. FP added, Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364579992"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T18:25:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35451479">naturelvr59</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Caching with my wife Sweetbeamie and our Geopup Little Bear, out of Elkhart Indiana. This vacation trip was based on our need of several south eastern states to have all states east of the Mississippi. We will proceed to Hutchinson Kansas for GeoWoodstock XXII. Along the way we are focusing on states oldest, the Cache Cross American series, Cache Odysseys, web cams and high favorite points.  
 What an epic journey. 18 states traveled, 13 new caching states for the books. 4000 plus miles traveled. 
Thanks to every cache owner who helps make our hobby amazing! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358116462"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T15:58:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="45513856">HidinCache</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357655757"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-27T14:22:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2166699">SuzySquirrel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc,  don't see enough of these.  Only one traceable here.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356541155"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="598646">tdb1977</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day 3 of my trip through the southeast states this weekend. I am targeting counties, the oldest in several states and the CAA in those states as well. Today was a 21 find day that started in Trussville and ended up in Augusta, GA.

My second CAA cache of the day!  This one puts me at exactly 25 found/25 to go!  Arrived at the lower parking lot and made the way back to this one.  Sure am glad that the mosquitos are not bad yet.  Got to ground zero and made the find quickly on the container.  All is well here.  Thanks for the cache.  Took nothing, left a travel bug.  Signed the log, recorded the number, took my picture, and placed back where it was found.

TDB1977</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="21.40085" lon="-157.896067"><time>2006-10-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC10RJA</name><desc>Cache Across America - Hawaii by Hawaii Geohana</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC10RJA</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Hawaii</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="536033" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Hawaii</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Hawaii Geohana</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="381373">sillygirl &amp; jrr</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="0">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Hawaii</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Hawaii&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ef/Flag_of_Hawaii.svg/800px-Flag_of_Hawaii.svg.png" width="187" height="93" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Honolulu&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Honolulu&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 43rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 42nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 50th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; You can access this cache via the Aiea Loop Trail, which is a wonderful scenic and shady hike. Along the way, you’ll be treated to views of Diamond Head, downtown Honolulu, and the Ko’olau and Wai’anae mountains. If you hike the whole loop, the distance is just under 5 miles; this cache is located less than ½ mile from the upper trailhead. There are a total of 6 other caches you can get to from this trail, one of which is the &lt;i&gt;oldest&lt;/i&gt; cache in Hawaii (Geocache - GC23). There is also a military plane crash site, complete with information plaque.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be sure to rehide the container completely; it's an ammo box so use lots of cammo so it is not visible from any direction. Just remember: Cammo the ammo!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- Start of StatCounter Code --&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.statcounter.com/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="http://c21.statcounter.com/counter.php?sc_project=2249932&amp;amp;java=0&amp;amp;security=d9c11bea&amp;amp;invisible=0" alt="hit counter code" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;!-- End of StatCounter Code --&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>40 feet off trail on ground under a hollow piece of dead wood [please cover well when re-hiding]</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363629846"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T13:12:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9698939">davidsonsa</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc. Took a trackable and can’t wait to share it somewhere new!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363581574"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T09:01:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="41414301">NickandGerie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC! Very convenient find. TNLN. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357824695"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-28T09:19:48</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54908189">jadenstambaugh</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice sized cache. Wish I could do the others!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355494764"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13418066">bitlux</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Mission accomplished! This was the main goal of the trip. My family and my brother-in-law's family spent a long time discussing where to go over spring break. My SIL's goal was to go to a national park, and Hawai'i won out over Yosemite due to lodging availability. We spent three days on the island of Hawai'i before a two day stint on Oahu. I woke up early today (still on California time) and arrived at Keaīwa Heiau State Recreation Area as it opened. This was a beautiful, easy hike to GZ, worthy of a favorite point. My first CAA of the year and I think 14th overall. TFTC!

Follow along with my [CAA journey](https://bitlux.github.io/caa).</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354240948"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-09T13:35:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="544348">emandel</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Slightly misleading hint, but a quick find regardless.  Thank you!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="21.399833" lon="-157.896533"><time>2006-10-29T00:00:00</time><name>GCZ49E</name><desc>Cache Across America - Hawaii by sillygirl &amp; jrr</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCZ49E</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Hawaii</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="486747" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Hawaii</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>sillygirl &amp; jrr</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="381373">sillygirl &amp; jrr</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="0">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="1">Horses</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Hawaii</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br&gt;
