http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=a68e7240-fa43-4acc-a6f8-2d482dbaa84b</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="60236954"><groundspeak:date>2009-01-06T13:00:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="571405">Rockin Roddy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Ok, I decided to place this a very short distance away, but the experience will have changed, so out with the old and in with the new! THANKS to those who visited, those watching this, there'll be a new one coming active very soon, already submitted!

It's been fun!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="58553145"><groundspeak:date>2008-12-11T10:26:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="571405">Rockin Roddy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">OUCH, someone must have needed that ammo box! Sorry for the inconvenience, will replace shortly!!

THANKS for bringing this to my attention!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.8736408" lon="-93.016886"><time>2006-08-06T00:00:00</time><name>GCX2RZ</name><desc>Cache Across America – Minnesota by Pto</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCX2RZ</url><urlname>Cache Across America – Minnesota</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="425724" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – Minnesota</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Pto</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="140089">Pto</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Minnesota</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>For the most scenic view, the Best Parking is available at the South St. Paul Public Water Access parking lot. N44 52.876 W93 01.088. Please see long description for full details
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Minnesota&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b9/Flag_of_Minnesota.svg/759px-Flag_of_Minnesota.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Saint Paul&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Minneapolis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 12th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 21st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 32nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; In the fall of October 2002, Mn Dept of trasportation &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.dot.state.mn.us/metro/projects/wakota/index.html" target="_blank"&gt;MNDot Project&lt;/a&gt; began work on a 5 year Construction Project which would completely redefine the entire area by widening this bridge, as well as other major improvements to the major infrastructure in the area. On Octber 22, 2002 a cache was placed here (one of the older caches in MN- &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=6854827f-5ff4-4959-a37f-e4cc7e2101ff" target="_blank"&gt;GC9F78&lt;/a&gt; ) in order to draw cachers to this view of its progrees. That cache has since been reported SBA, and after a lenghty search I was unable to recover the original, So... Since this bridge is scheduled to re-open in the fall of 2006 - as a Tribute tricolor, and as a celebration of the project ending, I thought this to be a good place for this hide. This hide offers an alternative, more scenic viewpoint from which to observe the bridge and the changes it has undergone. This is a longer than average walk along a paved walking/bike path with adequate rest stops along the way including park benches &amp;amp; picnic tables. Follow established trails after the pavement ends. No need to bushwhack until the last 100ft. Eagles nest in a nearby tree- hopefully you are lucky enough to see it while on the hunt. Container is a tricolor camo'd ammo can. Original contents: Log book, pen, pencil and misc. assorted goodies. Please rehide as well or better than found to avoid this cache being muggled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a partici pant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>
under cover camo'd, please rehide well</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364602600"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T07:18:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24035021">Scotty24fan</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false"> My wife and I stayed at my sons in Fridley last night. I got up early this morning to grab a select few caches. This is my first CAA cache. I stumbled upon them while looking at caches for a trip. Neat. Another list of caches to find. 😂. It was a pleasant walk all the way along the river. GZ wasn’t so pleasant. 😂. Of course I decided to wear shorts today. The nettles were stinging like crazy. Thankfully it wasn’t too long of a search. The stinging stopped by the time I got back to the car. 😂. Thanks! Find #6595 </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364264276"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="598646">tdb1977</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day 3 of my trip to Yellowstone NP with my wife to celebrate our 25th anniversary.  It was almost 3 years to the date that I DNFed this cache.  We stayed the night in the Twin Cities and before heading to my event, we came back over to the Mississippi River so I could attempt to avenge my DNF here.  This time, because time was tight, I had my wife drop me off at the shortcut and she proceeded to take the car back to the main parking area.  I scuttled down the trail and into the woods.  I gave myself about 30 minutes to search for this cache before having to move on and head to my event.  I searched high and low and was coming up empty.  Man, I didn't want to leave with another DNF here.  But finally, my persistence paid off and I made the find on this CAA cache.  This is my 29th CAA cache and one of my most rewarding finds in the series as I took the hard DNF last time.  All is well here.  Thanks for the cache.  Took nothing, left 2 travel bugs.  Signed the log and placed back where I found it.

TDB1977</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361445858"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-16T12:04:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2426415">BeachBumsX2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Beautiful day to take this short hike. I parked at the best parking and took the scenic route. It was nice to stretch my legs from all the driving I’ve been doing. I put together many photos and made it one collage.
Left my 3 trackable trading cards for discovery and some swag. 

Day 4/14
I left Florida on Wednesday the 13th and  I’m heading to all the north states that I need before GWSXXII. Caching on the way for some caches and specific ones on my list. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359394243"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-05T15:21:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2583507">geoking2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After many years of hunting for CAA caches, I FINALLY am coming by to find the one in my own state. It’s been almost 10 years in the making for me. Because it’s so close, it’s always been an “I can find it later” mindset. This just led to procrastination for me. Well today I finally decided it was time to take advantage of the snowless and bugless time now to come down here and find it. I enjoyed my walk down and made the find shortly after getting to GZ. Got the code and pic and am on my way. Thanks! Find #15153</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358135954"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T18:43:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43498594">gillicudy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">🥔</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="31.432817" lon="-88.718517"><time>2006-08-05T00:00:00</time><name>GCXH02</name><desc>Cache Across America - Mississippi by back2eight</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXH02</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Mississippi</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="439367" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Mississippi</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>back2eight</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="710634">back2eight</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Mississippi</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Located in the DeSoto National Forest. Simple roadside cache.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
