     alt="counter" border="0"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;!-- End of StatCounter Code --&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Should be obvious, but if it isn't, look for something large and tall.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="54736939"><groundspeak:date>2008-10-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="156408">webscouter.</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The new cache has been submitted and should be online soon. 

Cache number is GC1H2Z1</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="50238170"><groundspeak:date>2008-08-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="527285">Blue Power Ranger</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Can we have the person who would like to replace this cache, please contact us through our profile and we will work with you on getting a new Missouri cache set up as soon as possible. Thanks so much!! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="50213871"><groundspeak:date>2008-08-07T20:19:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="232437">OzarksJim</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I have received verification that this cache was recently washed away in a flood. Unfortunately, that means any travel bugs that were in the cache are gone as well.

It may be a while before I can get around to creating another "Missouri" cache. If somebody else wants to place one, I'd be willing to give someone else the opportunity to be the owner of the "Missouri" cache. Please contact me if you would like to do so. Otherwise, I might replace this one myself.

~OzarksJim</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="50219523"><groundspeak:date>2008-08-07T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="232437">OzarksJim</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">FYI - Someone has already volunteered to replace this cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="50136840"><groundspeak:date>2008-08-06T14:39:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="232437">OzarksJim</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It seems like the cache has gone missing. I'm disabling it for now but will probably end up archiving it.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="46.7712" lon="-111.892983"><time>2007-04-15T00:00:00</time><name>GC1272W</name><desc>Cache Across America - Montana by yumitori (Proudly Adopted by MontanaScarecrow)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1272W</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Montana</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="578799" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Montana</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>yumitori (Proudly Adopted by MontanaScarecrow)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="956917">montanascarecrow</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="9" inc="1">Significant hike</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="1">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="23" inc="1">Dangerous area</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>4.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>4</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Montana</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;This Cache is said to be the HARDEST CAA Cache...Some People have had to be RESCUED while attempting this cache&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Disclaimer: KNOW YOUR LIMITATIONS! You are under no obligation to hunt this cache. You do so at your own risk. Like any outdoor sport, it carries the risk of unforeseen hazards. Use your best judgment with the environment and conditions. As conditions and cache locations may vary, it is the responsibility of the searcher to be familiar with the conditions in the area to be searched, to adequately prepare for those conditions, and to conduct oneself safely and responsibly and remain within his or her personal abilities and limitations. Children should be well supervised. When and if you find this cache, you are under no obligation to touch it, reach for it, climb to it, pick it up, or even open it. Open it at your own risk.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Montana&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Flag_of_Montana.svg/615px-Flag_of_Montana.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Helena&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Billings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 4th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 44th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 41st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Montana's Cache Across America geocache is hidden near the state capital of Helena and on national forest land along the Missouri River, Lewis &amp;amp; Clark's route through this part of the state. This stretch of the river is extremely popular for fishing so bring your pole if you have the extra time. The mostly level walk is a little over two-thirds of a mile each way, and starts at &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.pplmontana.com/producing+power/power+plants/Hauser+Dam.htm"&gt;Hauser Dam&lt;/a&gt;. In keeping with usual Montanan caching procedures, a portion of the drive in is over (well-maintained) dirt roads. Note that the parking area is narrow; recreational vehicles and trailers are not allowed past Black Sandy State Park, approximately 1.5 miles from the parking at the dam.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache container is hidden above the trail at 3750', both to allow for better views of the canyon and to hopefully avoid accidental discovery. The climb from the trail requires a little less than 100' of elevation gain. When you start getting close to the coordinates pick your best route; there's no need to scramble straight up the slope. Doing so will only lead to increased erosion. The climb should not be too difficult for most folks; just take your time and watch your footing. Accuracy may be an issue due to the canyon walls and rocky terrain, so the hint has a detailed description of the cache's hiding place. Don't be afraid to use it. When re-hiding the cache, please cover it completely and carefully so it does not attract unwanted attention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note that on occasion Hauser Dam may be closed to the public due to Homeland Security concerns. I've provided a waypoint route to an alternative parking area at the other end of the trail. This is a day-use-only area below Hauser Dam; the road is primitive for the last 3 miles so a high-clearance vehicle is recommended. Street cars can make it, but the going will be a bit slower.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Climb to the top of the rocky outcropping overlooking the river. With your back to the river, look directly up the slope towards a collection of boulders. To the left of the boulders is a large sagebrush; the cache is hidden at its base under rock and branches. Please re-hide it in the same manner so that nothing looks unusual or out-of-place.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360071407"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2610378">Shark Z</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I think this is # 4 for us.  We have a long way to go.
We are on a trip to Visit relatives.  We are making a Lots of quick stops for Delorme  pages, and interesting caches along the way.
Thanks. May 9, 2026</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349558435"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-15T15:44:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19810498">wickedcurt</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">FOUND!  I would not recommend doing either with snow on the ground but it sure was worth the view!  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1345171272"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-15T16:02:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7279438">jlccort</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc. Crazy to be out in February looking for geocaches in a shirt. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1342442118"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14038240">juliecscs</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We went to hike this trail for the first time today on this sunny morning! On the way back we looked together for this cache. What a nice view from the top! Thank you for placing this one! 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1333396417"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-06T20:38:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52640026">UrbanBlacksmith</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TF this epic Cache! Yeah… the wife, justgeocachingalong ❤️, wrote a novel so I will spare the details. I however say this, any more vertical and you might want some climbing gear. 😂😂😂

Happy caching!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.22385" lon="-103.577033"><time>2006-07-22T00:00:00</time><name>GCXCRG</name><desc>Cache across America - Nebraska by Team StarBrand</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXCRG</url><urlname>Cache across America - Nebraska</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="435320" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache across America - Nebraska</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Team StarBrand</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="39181">StarBrand</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="1">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>30 Cal ammo box. General prairie terrian including grass, sand,
some cactus and the rare but occasional snake. Short walk from
parking. Be sure to rehide well with local natural coverings. Very
well stocked cache and very full - be sure to close the lid well.
Watch for possible muggles. Pay close attention to the "native"
signs in the area.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Nebraska&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src=
"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5a/Nebraska_state_flag.png"
     width="187" height="135"&gt; 
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Lincoln&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Omaha&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 16th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 38th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 37th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=bf517972-5f45-4ed9-ac4b-afbde9231a6c"&gt;
HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle"
    bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg"
     width="450" height="221"&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a
series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire
United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These
caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;
one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion
of the series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Placed near the path that
most take on the way though Nebraska. It is a shame that most
visitors see our beautiful state from this narrow cooridor. This
area is the southermost edge of the famed Nebraska Sandhills. This
vast region of stabilized dunes covers more than 1/3 of the state.
North and west of here is the North Platte River valley with lush
cropland and stunning hills and other erosional features. Far to
the north are the first rolling hills that become part of the Black
Hills region and act as a gateway to the Rocky Mountains. Across
the entire state is the Historic Oregon trail. Just southeast of
here riders once thundered across the plains carrying mail for the
Pony Express. Take time to visit more of the state than I-80
offers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you
would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant
in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself
or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you
for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please
make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual
cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge
participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required
before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three
digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure
place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all
50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good
luck!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.wnag.net"&gt;&lt;font size="1"
      fontface="arial" color="black"&gt;Placed by a Member
      of:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;img border="0" src="http://www.wnag.net/images/wnag1.gif"
     width="129" height="136" align="top"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;br&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Under.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="567238384"><groundspeak:date>2016-01-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15177653">ExpLaur</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Previously logged as GaxnLa and critln58 (now Gax2884).</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="63225515"><groundspeak:date>2009-02-23T09:37:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39181">StarBrand</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Archive - new cache for Nebraska at GC1N0ZV</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="62803869"><groundspeak:date>2009-02-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39181">StarBrand</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Checked and it is gone but so is the hiding place - not much of a change but I really didn't feel right about trying another hide at this spot - especially with the container I had brought for a replacement. Will try to craft a new container or look for a new spot soon.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="62018759"><groundspeak:date>2009-01-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="117226">Dorkteam6</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I was sad to see this one gone. I will check back next time I am driving through.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="59212214"><groundspeak:date>2008-12-26T18:12:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39181">StarBrand</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Will check on this soon.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.695983" lon="-103.265733"><time>2009-02-22T00:00:00</time><name>GC1N0ZV</name><desc>Cache Across America - Nebraska by Team StarBrand</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1N0ZV</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Nebraska</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1138968" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Nebraska</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Team StarBrand</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="39181">StarBrand</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>General prairie terrain including grass, weeds, soft uneven ground, some marshy conditions. You are looking for a 30 Cal ammo box - please rehide well with natural materials. Park at 41 41.741 W 103 16.100. &lt;b&gt;DO NOT park along the highway.&lt;/b&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Nebraska&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5a/Nebraska_state_flag.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Lincoln&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Omaha&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 16th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 38th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 37th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=bf517972-5f45-4ed9-ac4b-afbde9231a6c"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This part of the CAA series has been moved to a new location as the old spot was too muggle prone. The new location 40 miles or so North of old location) is a much better representation of Nebraska anyway. This cache is placed very nearly in the wagon ruts of the Oregon Trail. Off to the west you will see historic Chimney Rock. This natural landmark greeted pioneers as they travelled across the great plains 150 years ago. It also graced the back of the Nebraska quarter as part of the 50 state series. Please use the included parking coordinates for best access to the location and use extra caution if it has been wet and rainy recently. Enjoy this cache and use it as a gateway to explore the rest of the state.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.wnag.net"&gt;&lt;font size="1" color="black"&gt;Placed by a Member of:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img border="0" src="http://www.wnag.net/images/wnag1.gif" width="129" height="136" align="top" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>at the base</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="640115160"><groundspeak:date>2016-09-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello Cache Across America watchers and players!

We are proud to announce that the brand new CAA Nebraska is now published!  The bookmarks have been updated and the new CAA NE cache is GC6TB1E.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="631987827"><groundspeak:date>2016-08-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello CAA watchers,  just an update on the new CAA NE cache.  There is a plan in place with a new owner in a new location.  We are working hard as a team to get the new CAA Nebraska cache up and running asap!  Thanks for your patience, there is always a little time involved when a new CAA cache is required.  We are very excited about the new owner ...more details soon! [:D]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="625649933"><groundspeak:date>2016-08-06T18:33:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="531429">Heartland Cacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings I'm Heartland Cacher, one of the volunteer reviewers for new caches submitted to Geocaching.com.

It has been a while since I first looked at this cache.  I can't find any recent responses from the Cache Owner about maintaining this cache which makes it appear the Cache Owner is either unwilling or unable to maintain the cache. **Cache maintenance includes listing maintenance including updating any changes to the text, updating coordinates, removing needs maintenance attributes and enabling the listing.**  The cache will be archived and removed from the active cache listings. 

Thanks for your understanding,
Heartland Cacher
Your friendly Geocaching.com Volunteer Cache Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="625673732"><groundspeak:date>2016-08-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dear Cache Across America watchers and players.

Lorriebird here, caretaker of the Cache Across America series of caches.

It is with sadness that we see the CAA NE cache has been archived.  This cache has been a great game piece for the CAA series for many years and we appreciate the CO's many years of being a state cache owner. 

We also want to thank reviewer Heartland Cacher who has been so helpful during this process and so patient while we tried to contact the current owner.

There is a plan in place for a new Cache Across America Nebraska and we are working on getting it published as soon as possible.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="623208887"><groundspeak:date>2016-07-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2403780">GuacIsGoodDNJ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Didn't see this one was disabled until we refreshed our cache data when we got back to the car. Doh! Only DNF of a CAA cache so far on this otherwise awesome roadtrip. Ohh well.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.935367" lon="-114.69185"><time>2006-07-09T00:00:00</time><name>GCWXQT</name><desc>Cache Across America - Nevada by BadAndy adopted by Shootie, DzzyOnes  now Tbone34</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCWXQT</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Nevada</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="420883" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Nevada</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>BadAndy adopted by Shootie, DzzyOnes  now Tbone34</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="887918">tbone34</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nevada</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>left an Idaho geocoin for the ftf.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center"&gt;Nevada&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Flag_of_Nevada.svg/744px-Flag_of_Nevada.svg.png"
width="187" height="135" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Carson City&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Las Vegas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 7th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 35th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 36th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=bf517972-5f45-4ed9-ac4b-afbde9231a6c"&gt;
HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor=
"#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg"
width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a
series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire
United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These
caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;
one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion
of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Jackpot!!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Nevadas own "Mile High City" is located on the northern Nevada /
Idaho state line. Nestled in the high desert alongside Salmon falls
creek, this is one of Nevadas true gems. Rockhounds will love the
abundance of mineral deposits in the area. Geodes litter the desert
floor nearby.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The cache itself is a painted ammocan hidden just 3 miles south of
Jackpot Nevada. I filled it with casino themed items. Use the BLM
access road and park just past the gate.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you
would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant
in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself
or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you
for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please
make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual
cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge
participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required
before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three
digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure
place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all
50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good
luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="472099551"><groundspeak:date>2013-10-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7994938">1st_mate</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Late log entry. Made this find with captphil and Captainwilly a while back when I was logging in under his username. He often referred to me as Mrs. Captphil or 1st mate. Now that I have my own account I would like to claim this as a find. We will be making a future trip this way and will grab the new one too. TFTFun!! TFTC!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="313770363"><groundspeak:date>2013-05-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We are happy to announce that the new Cache Across America Nevada cache has been published!

Check it out at GC4BQEX!

Cache on!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="312977804"><groundspeak:date>2013-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello watchers of this cache and Cache Across America players!

We are very excited to announce that the brand new Cache Across America Nevada cache is almost ready for publication!  The new owner (whom many of you will recognize) has chosen the gorgeous Red Rock Canyon area to showcase the great state of Nevada.  The new cache will be listed as GC4BQEX.  You won't be able to view it until it is published, but watch for it in the near future.

Here is a link to my bookmark that will remain current with all the Cache Across America caches both past and present:

http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41

Thank you for your patience while we continue working very hard to get all the Cache Across America caches back on track and the series running properly.  Nevada is almost ready! [^]

Regards,

Lorriebird and ZSteve</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="307981333"><groundspeak:date>2013-04-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello all.  I am helping out the creators of the CAA series and will be taking on the watch of the 50 states.  I am aware of the loss of Nevada and am working on getting a new one.  Please stand by and there will be a new one asap!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="300719769"><groundspeak:date>2013-03-25T18:01:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="887918">tbone34</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Goner.  Nevada is now open to a new CAA.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.228083" lon="-71.5731"><time>2006-08-20T00:00:00</time><name>GCXVV4</name><desc>Cache Across America - New Hampshire by Max Jerome</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXVV4</url><urlname>Cache Across America - New Hampshire</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="448824" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - New Hampshire</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Max Jerome</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="145859">Max Jerome</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="0">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="20" inc="1">Abandoned mine</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New Hampshire</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;New Hampshire&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Flag_of_New_Hampshire.svg/660px-Flag_of_New_Hampshire.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Concord&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Manchester&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 46th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 41st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 9th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; New Hampshire once had a large industry surrounding the quarrying of granite, this gave it the nickname of "The Granite State." Granite stone walls, curbs, buildings, and even bridges can be found throughout the state. At one time, it appeared that almost every town had at least one quarry. Although most of the granite quarried was used locally, New Hampshire granite has journeyed to many places in the world to become part of monumental buildings, such as the Library of Congress, the Tomb of the Unknown Solider, the Brooklyn Bridge, The Pentagon, and many Civil War monuments.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
When the word "granite" is mentioned, one thinks of other words such as solid, grounded, unyielding, and set in stone. When the term "The Granite State" is mentioned, that brings to mind New Hampshire, and in New Hampshire, the word "granite" stands for something just a bit more. It stands for the industry that was born in the late 1800's in the city of Concord, on Rattlesnake Hill.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This cache is located on one of the many trails that run through Rattlesnake Hill. It is a 30-cal ammo canister located near one of the granite quarries in the area. The trail is level most of the way, but it is very rocky. Supposedly, this trail doubles as a mountain bike trail, so bring a bike if you wish. I wouldn't recommend small children for this hunt. And you may want to leave slightly older children behind if you decide to look at the views... there's some inappropriate graffiti in a couple spots.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Park on the side of the road at N 43° 12.999 W 071° 34.310. Then, just go where your GPS tells you &lt;strong&gt;EXCEPT&lt;/strong&gt; when you're about .19 miles from the cache, the trail forks. The GPS will probably tell you to go left, but you're better off going right.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The cache is about 100 feet off trail, and should be pretty easy to find. The coords are within 22 feet of accuracy.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Enjoy!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Look for a rock with notches in it.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="656862061"><groundspeak:date>2016-12-25T06:39:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="145859">Max Jerome</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">New cache = GC6XGVJ</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="654156560"><groundspeak:date>2016-12-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="145859">Max Jerome</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The replacement cache is by Mount Monadnock... GC6XGVJ.  I'm gonna archive this one pretty soon.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="646566959"><groundspeak:date>2016-10-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="145859">Max Jerome</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yup.  This one's toast.  I wasn't crazy about the new signage they have on the gate I usually park at, and some people in the past have been creeped out by the "no trespassing" signs, so I'm gonna place a new CAA cache elsewhere.  I'll keep this cache active until that replacement happens (a couple weeks to a month I would think).</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="643907718"><groundspeak:date>2016-10-12T17:20:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="145859">Max Jerome</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Darn.  If it turns out this cache is missing, I'm gonna end up replacing it a little closer to home, probably somewhere around Mount Monadnock (Jaffrey, NH).  Stay tuned.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="643784996"><groundspeak:date>2016-10-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1695533">PastorChris</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I made the hike out with Lucy the Dog and all we found was a lid to a lock-n-lock that was painted green.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.9261" lon="-74.65785"><time>2007-04-20T00:00:00</time><name>GC12A5P</name><desc>Cache Across America - New Jersey by JoenGPS</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC12A5P</url><urlname>Cache Across America - New Jersey</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="581770" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - New Jersey</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>JoenGPS</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="560813">JoenGPS</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New Jersey</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;New Jersey&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/Flag_of_New_Jersey.svg/750px-Flag_of_New_Jersey.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Trenton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Newark&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 47th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 10th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 3rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Your Cache Across America stop here in the Garden State wouldn't be complete without a visit to the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.pineypower.com/geninfopbpg10.html"&gt;NJ Pine Barrens&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the rich &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.hoganphoto.com"&gt;biodiversity&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.njpinebarrens.com/category/explore/history/"&gt;historical elements&lt;/a&gt; listed in the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pine_Barrens_(New_Jersey)"&gt;Pine Barrens Wiki&lt;/a&gt;, you will find scrub oaks, atlantic white-cedar and the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.pinelandsalliance.org/ecology/habitats/pygmyplains/"&gt;famous Pygmy Pines&lt;/a&gt;. The area is also known for its &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.pineypower.com/blueberries.htm"&gt;wild blueberries&lt;/a&gt;, and it's &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.pineypower.com/cranberries.htm"&gt;cranberries&lt;/a&gt; Learn about the legend of the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.oocities.org/heartland/2809/whitestag.htm"&gt;White Stag of Shamong&lt;/a&gt; at Quaker Bridge or the ghost of &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://weirdnj.com/stories/local-heroes-and-villains/joe-mulliner/"&gt;Joe Mulliner&lt;/a&gt; (NJ's Robin Hood of the Pines). Visit the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.onlyinyourstate.com/new-jersey/nj-ghost-towns/"&gt;lost towns of NJ&lt;/a&gt;, and of course the legend of the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.csicop.org/si/show/the_jersey_devil_the_real_story"&gt;Jersey Devil&lt;/a&gt;.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache you are seeking is near the lost town of &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://weirdnj.com/stories/ongs-hat/"&gt;Ong’s Hat&lt;/a&gt;.  There is dispute as to how the name "Ong's Hat" became to be.  One legend states that a resident, a Dutchman named Ong, perhaps in a drunken fit, once threw his hat into a high branch of a pine tree. The hat remained there for many years before eventually disintegrating.  Another legend is that Ong was a bit of a partier and built a hut as a waystation between his home further north and Washington Tavern.  The Dutchman pronounced hut as "hat" and that is where the name came from. Don't venture too far back into Ong's Hat as you may just cross "the gate" into another dimension. See the link above! &lt;b&gt;Don't forget to get the clue!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Downed log not far from the road. The Clue is on the inside of the lid and on the log. Note: This cache went missing twice. Someone actually took a dump in the container. I moved it twice and hence a small cache instead of a bigger container.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363106832"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T06:45:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1041842">lschweic</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The cache is in good shape. Lovely drive to GZ. Did some CITO. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361023350"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T19:36:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25469529">lindsayasdnil</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Well here MissB and I on our scrapple/williamsburg adventure with cache #5 for the day 
We read some logs on the way to this one so were able to attack at an angle that left us with few thorns … quick find and off we went again TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363007015"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25469328">Missbderycke</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Phone in Airplane Mode, Work Phone &amp; Laptop Shut Off, 5 days. 4 New States. 5 CAAs, 4 Cache Odysseys, 3000+ km driving, 25+km on foot, a lifetime of laughs &amp; memories = priceless. 

Here is a short story long... in booking a hotel in November of 2025 I was asked to stay on the line and listen to an offer. While listening I was getting ready to head out on a hike with a friend so Im not going to lie I was paying zero attention. Afterward the lady was like does that sound good and I answered yes which prompted her to ask for my credit card number. Still not paying attention to what was going on and thinking I was paying for the November hotel I ended up with a 3 night 4 day stay to 11 different locations in the US for a really good deal. When I saw the email stating what I had just signed up for I called lindsayasdnil and said well I did this thing so pick from these 11 locations and we will go on a geotrip! She ended up deciding on Williamsburg, VA as it was one we could drive to and the closest-ish one. Now just to decide when we would go. We seem to like to road trip in May so we decided on doing that again and combine it with a milestone birthday for her. Since my goal is to visit all of the states and also complete this series while doing so we chatted about tacking on an extra day and visiting Delaware as neither of us had it as a state we were planning on visiting for a specific reason (but boy am I sure glad we did, more on this later). About a week before leaving I convinced her that we werent far from the New Jersey CAA either and we would be driving super close to the North Carolina border so we might as well pop down there for a hot minute and grab a cache as well. 

This was the first must grab cache on our list and my 9th CAA cache. We left Niagara Falls, ON at 7:45am and it is now almost 12 hours later, thankfully we made it to this one with daylight still. After reading through some logs on our way here we were able to miss all the thorns and made a quick find here. This is also our first cache find in this state so adding a fav point all around. Tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353010939"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="46573847">1Gringe</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out exploring on this beautiful day. Visiting from Michigan. Glad to find my first Cache Across America. Wish I could do all of them! I recorded the code just in case. Cache is in good shape. TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353009234"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="560813">JoenGPS</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Checkup and new log added. Good luck!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.2599" lon="-105.99715"><time>2006-08-09T00:00:00</time><name>GCXMJD</name><desc>Cache Across America - New Mexico by suz55tbird &amp; Ghia girl</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXMJD</url><urlname>Cache Across America - New Mexico</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="442819" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - New Mexico</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>suz55tbird &amp; Ghia girl</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="428698">suz55tbird</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New Mexico</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;New Mexico&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Flag_of_New_Mexico.svg/1000px-Flag_of_New_Mexico.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Santa Fe&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Albuquerque&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 5th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 36th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 47th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="red"&gt;If you are visiting from out of state:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt; (or even far away in-state): and if you'll be in Albuquerque on a weeknight, I'd love to host a meet-n-greet for you! Try to let me know as far ahead of time as possible so an event can be published.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; It was difficult to choose a location for this cache; there is no one area that typifies the essence of the amazing state of New Mexico! From the Organ Mountains, White Sands, and the City of Rocks in southern NM, to the beautiful mountains, calderas, and geographic highlights of the north, with buttes, the Jornada del Muerto, mesas, hoodoos and tent rocks between, there is so much to see here for the outdoor enthusiast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As with the geography, you'll find a range of cultures and history in New Mexico. There are ancient cultures from Anasazi to current Pueblo and a more recent tricultural heritage, including rural ranches and farms, sophisticated city life, and universities. New Mexico history runs from the prehistoric through early explorers, the Camino Real, Civil War sites, to present day cutting edge technology throughout the state.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We wound up placing the cache nearly smack dab in the center of the state, hoping you'd take the time to check out the rest of the state along the way...you may choose to follow the Camino Real and the Rio Grande River, which was our route to the cache (see pics). The Gran Quivera National Monument is just a few miles west of the cache, and definitely worth a stop!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please post a photo of yourself with the cache, AND a favorite photo which typifies New Mexico in your mind, with your log. I originated the cache with some New Mexico items; it would be nice if NM cachers would leave these for out-of-staters and add additional New Mexico-type swag to the cache. Thanks! Can't wait to see your photos!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364266244"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:58:46</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3726515">TeamPumpJack</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">12:58. # 20211.
United States, New Mexico

We drove the 2 hours from Albuquerque just to get this cache!!!  The cattle must have thought HeJack resembled their Rancher because they came running down the hill moooing all the way. When they got about 50 yards from us, they stopped in a row. We turned our back to do something and when we turned around, they were about 25 yards from us. Like they snuck up on us!!  After a bit, they got bored and the 2 Bulls went to work. 

We got the code, took some pictures and left a Geocoin!

Thank you to suz55tbird for a fun Cache!!

Since 7/14/24, we are full time World travelers enjoying every adventure! 

