</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363552493"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T13:25:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1041842">lschweic</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wow!  READ OLD LOGS was the lesson for today. I looked up when the last cache was found, but not the text. I looked around GZ for about 45 min before I read logs that mentioned the coordinates were off. Once I recalibrated, it was not a hard find. 

It had been raining a lot recently, so the creek had lots of flow. There is no need to cross the water. I parked at the bottom, found a little trail and bushwhacked  up to GZ. The area around GZ was a complete SWAMP with 3-4 inches of standing water in some parts from all the rain. I just found a couple of walking sticks and that helped. I also made a couple of waypoints on my iPhone to find the trail again for the way out, which I was glad I did. 

The canopy can be dense in parts, so go after this one when you have plenty of daylight left. It would get dark in here pretty quickly. 

This cache is definitely worthy of CAA status. 

TFTC!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361023340"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T13:50:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25469529">lindsayasdnil</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Targeted cache on our way for our scrapple adventure 
Nice hike and thanks for all the help in the previous logs made this not a bad adventure and a fairly quick find </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363002602"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25469328">Missbderycke</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Phone in Airplane Mode, Work Phone &amp; Laptop Shut Off, 5 days. 4 New States. 5 CAAs, 4 Cache Odysseys, 3000+ km driving, 25+km on foot, a lifetime of laughs &amp; memories = priceless. 

Here is a short story long... in booking a hotel in November of 2025 I was asked to stay on the line and listen to an offer. While listening I was getting ready to head out on a hike with a friend so Im not going to lie I was paying zero attention. Afterward the lady was like does that sound good and I answered yes which prompted her to ask for my credit card number. Still not paying attention to what was going on and thinking I was paying for the November hotel I ended up with a 3 night 4 day stay to 11 different locations in the US for a really good deal. When I saw the email stating what I had just signed up for I called lindsayasdnil and said well I did this thing so pick from these 11 locations and we will go on a geotrip! She ended up deciding on Williamsburg, VA as it was one we could drive to and the closest-ish one. Now just to decide when we would go. We seem to like to road trip in May so we decided on doing that again and combine it with a milestone birthday for her. Since my goal is to visit all of the states and also complete this series while doing so we chatted about tacking on an extra day and visiting Delaware as neither of us had it as a state we were planning on visiting for a specific reason (but boy am I sure glad we did, more on this later). About a week before leaving I convinced her that we werent far from the New Jersey CAA either and we would be driving super close to the North Carolina border so we might as well pop down there for a hot minute and grab a cache as well. 

This was the first must grab cache on our list and my 8th CAA cache. I was a little leery as we were driving down a dirt road on what appeared to be a mountain side with no guard rail and the recent rains we had been getting. When we reached parking there was only a transport truck back here but, none the less lindsayasdnil donned her orange and I put on my pink backpack because I may or may not have forgot my orange hunting vest. A bit of a climb up the hill but thankfully we had our trusty "jesus sticks" to carry us on our way. A bit of searching around and some boots stuck in the mud (thankfully I didnt forget my rubbers for this one). Eventually we spotted it a ways in front of us and made our way over some trees to claim the find. Awarding a fav point for the adventure. Tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358991705"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T13:09:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11265453">thiayack</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found my ninth CAA thanks for being a part of the series. This was a very difficult find, steep, rocky,  lots of down trees, no trail, coordinates a little bit off and marshy area all around GZ. But I found it and had a fun adventure. The day was perfect sunny and 50°.
Unfortunately, I wasn’t paying attention to the direction I was going on the way out, so I ended up down by the boat ramp.  at least I didn’t have to cross over the stream again. Saw lots of sign of deer and bear bear scat.
TFTCAA SL left a personal path tag

I’m in the area celebrating my 73rd birthday letterboxing, adventure, labbing, caching and rail trail riding</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1330116637"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-16T19:26:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7093949">Lakegal44</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with wanablee. Beautiful day of fall colors. 

For hubby wanablee and I this cache is part of our adventure into the New England states. We left home in northern Arizona in August, explored our way through New Mexico, Colorado, Wyoming, South Dakota, Iowa, North Dakota, Minnesota, a corner of Wisconsin, UP of Michigan, then into some Canadian Provinces ending in New Brunswick. Now we’re on a leaf-peeping tour of the New England states. On this trip we are focusing on counties, oldest, Cache Across America, and Cache Odyssey. So far we have explored Maine, New Hampshire, Vermont, New York, Massachusetts, Rhode Island, Connecticut and now Pennsylvania.  This cache was one we couldn’t pass up. Thank you. 

Photo of wanablee and my signature duck which I left in the cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.7922" lon="-71.372917"><time>2006-08-01T00:00:00</time><name>GCWVNF</name><desc>Cache Across America – Rhode Island by Downy288</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCWVNF</url><urlname>Cache Across America – Rhode Island</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="418889" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – Rhode Island</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Downy288</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="73561">RIclimber</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="0">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Rhode Island</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Rhode Island&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src=
"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Flag_of_Rhode_Island.svg/500px-Flag_of_Rhode_Island.svg.png"
     width="187" height="187"&gt; 
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Providence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Providence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 50th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 43rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 13th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=bf517972-5f45-4ed9-ac4b-afbde9231a6c"&gt;
HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle"
    bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg"
     width="450" height="221"&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a
series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire
United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These
caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;
one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion
of the series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is hidden in
Squantum Woods Park in Riverside, RI. This is kind of an overlooked
park with views of downtown Providence.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you
would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant
in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself
or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you
for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please
make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual
cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge
participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required
before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three
digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure
place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all
50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good
luck!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Under log, uphill end.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="278560808"><groundspeak:date>2012-11-09T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5961553">elonka</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">As of November 2012, the Rhode Island CAA cache is now &lt;a href="http://coord.info/GC3XAC9"&gt;GC3XAC9&lt;/a&gt;</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="49492713"><groundspeak:date>2008-07-28T18:48:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="73561">RIclimber</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">New cache-- GC1ENDM</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="49458032"><groundspeak:date>2008-07-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="73561">RIclimber</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This area in the park cant be used for a cache.   I'm working on placing a new CAA cache.

[This entry was edited by Downy288 on Tuesday, July 29, 2008 at 10:09:43 AM.]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="49014254"><groundspeak:date>2008-07-22T07:47:55</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="73561">RIclimber</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">missing?</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="49420336"><groundspeak:date>2008-07-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="208298">Ms. Anne</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I was so disappointed about not finding this one after traveling aal the way from Virginia for this cache across America.  It was a great location except for the fact that it is obviously a party place- strewn with beer cans and other litter.  We searched for over an hour but to no avail. We gave up for the day.  Hopefully someone will take care of this matter.  Ms. Anne  Big Stone Gap, Va.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.751333" lon="-71.348167"><time>2008-07-28T00:00:00</time><name>GC1ENDM</name><desc>Cache Across America – Rhode Island   by Downy288</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1ENDM</url><urlname>Cache Across America – Rhode Island  </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="950079" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – Rhode Island  </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Downy288</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="73561">RIclimber</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Rhode Island</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table&gt;
