     height="221" width="450" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a
series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire
United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These
caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to
&lt;a rel="nofollow"
href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;
one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion
of the series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#ffffff" height="61"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Hidden in Haines Memorial
State Park. Haines Memorial State Park was established in 1911 when
Ida M. Haines donated 83 acres of land to the Metropolitan Park
Commission. The land was donated for use as a park in memory of her
brother.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#CCCCCC" height="61"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you
would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant
in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself
or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you
for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please
make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual
cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge
participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required
before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three
digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure
place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all
50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good
luck!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Base of tree.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="472100473"><groundspeak:date>2013-09-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7994938">1st_mate</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Late log entry. Made this find with captphil on 6/21/09. At that time I was logging in with his username and he often referred to me as Mrs. Captphil or 1st mate. Now that I have my own account I would like to claim this one as a find. We will be making a future trip back here and will be looking for the new one at that time. TFTFun!!  TFTC!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="277990861"><groundspeak:date>2012-11-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5961553">elonka</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">As of November 2012, the Rhode Island CAA cache is &lt;a href="http://coord.info/GC3XAC9"&gt;GC3XAC9&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This entry was edited by elonka on Saturday, 10 November 2012 at 08:05:46 UTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="269895520"><groundspeak:date>2012-09-30T15:10:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="73561">RIclimber</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">New one listed.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="269530376"><groundspeak:date>2012-09-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1015404">coloReido</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was a tough find and my GPSr bounced from 60 - 100 feet.  I was only able to locate it after the previous finder mentioned it was off by 22 meters and taking a close look at the photo.  tftc, SL</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="268185714"><groundspeak:date>2012-09-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1980131">Marg886</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Glad this one was moved to a more people friendly location.  Both our gpsrs were 22 meters off but the hint helped.  Found with N while visiting from Ontario.  Great location - love rail trails.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.913333" lon="-76.95"><time>2007-05-20T00:00:00</time><name>GC12E08</name><desc>Cache Across America - Series Final  by Cache Across America</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC12E08</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Series Final </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Unknown Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="585445" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Series Final </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Cache Across America</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1065830">Cache Across America</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Unknown Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="71" inc="1">Challenge cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>District of Columbia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="66%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="187" rowspan="5" align="center" bgcolor="#919352"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg/800px-Flag_of_the_United_States.svg.png" width="187" height="122" /&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the list of all 50 current state caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="659" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/c1a9439b-cbec-4838-934c-9b410390054a.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a nationwide tour of the entire United States. One cache in this series is hidden in each of the 50 United States. These caches each contain a three-digit numeric clue that that will lead you to this final cache located somewhere in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We hope you have enjoyed your tour of the 50 United States of America. This final cache will lead you to our nation's capitol, a fitting end to your tour of this great land. There are so many wonderful monuments and places to visit in Washington DC that we couldn't even begin to name them all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also hope that while you have been caching in all 50 states, you have been able to see places you may otherwise have never visited and have enjoyed finding the caches along the way. We hope that this series has shown you what a wonderful country this truly is. The true prize in completing the Cache Across America series will be the memories of a journey that will last a lifetime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would like to give a huge thanks to all 50 of the state hiders, both past and present. Also - a big thanks to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=77e86847-188f-4acb-84a0-9dc83875ee39"&gt;Flyingmoose&lt;/a&gt; for volunteering to hide and maintain this final cache. Please note that the five-star difficulty of this cache does not represent this particular hide but instead the difficulty in collecting the necessary information to solve this puzzle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Do not search for this cache at the listed coordinates. Of course, the cache is not in the middle of the tidal basin and there is certainly no need to swim. Simply solve the puzzle at the bottom of this page to obtain the correct coordinates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; In order to log this cache, you must have completed the required cache of this series in each of these 50 United States. As was mentioned in the state cache pages, you must have verified each of those 50 finds either by posting a photo with your logs or by having made alternate arrangements with the individual cache owners. Logging this cache without first finding the required 50 state caches will result in a deleted log.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While participating in the series you will have recorded each of the three-digit codes provided in the state caches. You will use those codes in the puzzle below to determine the coordinates of the final cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;div align="center"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The puzzle :&lt;/strong&gt; (UPDATED: 12/12/2023) To find the final N coordinates you will need to use the codes you found in the Cache Across America caches. For starters, add together the codes from the first 25 states admitted to the Union. Add this number to the N coordinates listed on this page above treating the N coordinate as if it were one large number (3854800). Take your new number and simply subtract 14391. This will give you the new N coordinates.
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Repeat this process for the W coordinates. Simply add the codes you found while searching for the second 25 states admitted to the Union. Once you have this number, add it to the W coordinates listed on this page above (7657000) just as you did for the N coordinate. Once you have this number, subtract 12769 from your total and you will now have the final W coordinates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now you are ready to search for the final cache. Please confirm your Final coordinates with Lorriebird or ZSteve after solving the puzzle. Then be sure and contact flyingmoose before searching for the Final cache!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oh...and one more thing. After you finish the Cache Across America Series and join the CAA Finishers family, Lorriebird and ZSteve will have a gift for you. We feel that finishers deserve something special and so we created the official Cache Across America Finishers Coin. This coin is not available for purchase but is our gift to you. We are also proud to announce that you will also receive two CAA Finishers patches, courtesy of NPGlenn! When will you claim yours?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="https://d1u1p2xjjiahg3.cloudfront.net/12795be8-e0cf-4ad4-8884-9c6e8332dc26_l.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;font size="5" face="comic sans" color="red"&gt;&lt;span class="style2"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Congratulations to&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=e21a81c6-d1ab-4aaa-beeb-b7d8e61a911d"&gt;ZSteve&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=67d296d5-d4be-42d9-840f-10c4f3c8e1d2"&gt;Hopperz&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="style2"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;- First to Find!&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;font size="5" face="comic sans" color="red"&gt;&lt;span class="style2"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;You guys rock!&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#000000"&gt;
