</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>
Back side of a log in a geocaching lock-n-lock</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1315776634"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="78712">rragan</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Congratulations bolosky! Always exciting to hear tales from each new finisher. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1315766899"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2414534">originalta</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Congratulations Bolosky. As the most recent finder I figured I should send a welcome note. Also as a fellow victim of a layoff that resulted in CAA finish, I commend you on turning those lemons into spiked lemonade. Also go Nats!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1315652614"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-06T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1214365">FLPirate</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">aaarrrRRRR !!
CONGRATULATIONS !!!  bolosky
A journey well done and we all know you enjoyed the travels.
Just think, if the ballgame was Bananaball, you would have been an unpaid professional ball player as you recorded a Putout.
Hope to see you at one of our "reunions" during the GeoWoodstocks.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1315595139"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-06T05:49:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26588241">Mermaidsh</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Congratulations, bolosky! And welcome to the CAA finishers family. I enjoyed reading your journey, and what a great finale, catching a baseball. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1315562247"><groundspeak:date>2025-08-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="484250">bolosky</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After 30+ years, Microsoft laid me off in February, 2023.  I decided that I wanted to take a few months and drive around the country.  The original plan was to go from Seattle to Santa Clara to pick up an award I won at a technical conference (ha!) and then go to Arizona for Spring Training and proceed from there.

I thought that it would be fun to see how many CAA caches I could get along the way.  Two months later, I had found 35 of them and was committed to finishing.  Eventually.

The main places I didn't hit on the trip were a big chunk of the upper Midwest/West, because it was still snowy in much of it, and Utah, New Hampshire, and Vermont, all of which I tried and failed to find because of snow, and for some reason Florida.  And, of course, Alaska and Hawaii.

This was a great excuse to go places I wouldn't otherwise have gone.  I took a little road trip to get Idaho, Wyoming and Montana. I visited my son in Maine and got New Hampshire and Vermont.   I took my kids to see National Parks and get Utah (much less snowy this time).  I did a solo trip to Alaska, and even drove up to Fairbanks to move my northernmost find a little farther north.  My wife went to Hawaii.  While we'd been many times, we'd never gone to Oahu.  I went to Florida with my sister.

Finally, in October of 2024 (about 18 months after starting), I took a trip to get Minnesota, Iowa, the Dakotas and Wisconsin, which were all that were left.  I flew into MSP and was planning to get the nearby Minnesota cache and then drive to the rest.  This would be kind of cool, because North Dakota would be the last of the 50 states that I'd set foot in and also the last of the 50 CAA caches.  But Minnesota was gone, so that was out the window.

Lucky for me, the CO was able to replace it while I was making my loop, and I found it before I had to return home.  It was my only DNF (discounting Vermont, which was there but under so much snow it was unfindable).

Now, all I had to do was come to DC and get the final.  That took another 10 months, but today was the day!  And as a bonus, after finding the cache I went to a Nationals game and got a foul ball in the first inning.

Thanks so much Lorriebird and all of the COs for making this possible!  It's a huge amount of work, but I'm glad you all did it.  It was such a wonderful challenge that got me to travel lots of places I would never otherwise have gone!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.101317" lon="-81.133667"><time>2006-08-27T00:00:00</time><name>GCXCXK</name><desc>Cache Across America – South Carolina by Llatnek (Adopted by Skillet)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXCXK</url><urlname>Cache Across America – South Carolina</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="435447" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – South Carolina</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Llatnek (Adopted by Skillet)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="677907">Skillet68</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>South Carolina</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;South Carolina&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Flag_of_South_Carolina.svg/744px-Flag_of_South_Carolina.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Columbia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Columbia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 40th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 26th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 8th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache: located in the Midlands of SC.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This cache is easily accessed along the Stewardship Trail in Harbison State Forest, a little less than one mile round trip hike from the nearest parking spot. If you park in the parking area outside the front gate, it is closer to a 4 ½ mile round trip hike (along the Firebreak Trail West, the Connector Trail, and the Stewardship Trail).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Harbison State Forest is over 2,000-acres of wooded forest land just 9 miles from downtown Columbia, located along the Broad River. As the largest Urban GreenSpace in the SE USA, it features over 16 miles of trails for hiking and bicycling, picnic shelters, and special forestry education programs. The Headquarters of the South Carolina State Forestry Commission is located here as well.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
There's a $5 ($25 annual) parking permit fee which can be paid at most of the marked parking areas. Bicyclists will also need to pay a Trail Use fee. The closest parking is at parking area "6" or trail junction "S", if you're sure you'll be out of the park by closing. &lt;a href="http://www.state.sc.us/forest/refhartg.htm"&gt;view the trail guide map here.&lt;/a&gt;. The gates are locked after 4:30 pm on weekdays and 6:30 pm on Saturday and Sunday. It's OK to be in the forest until sunset, but if you expect to be in the park after hours, be sure to park your car outside the gates to avoid the parking fine. &lt;strong&gt;Check the posted signs for seasonal variations to the gate schedule.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Permission for this cache was given by Harbison State Forest management. You may contact the Harbison State Forest Office at (803)896-8890 with any questions or if you need any assistance while in the forest.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Feel free to remove any/all decoys you may find near this cache. These "enhancements" were not placed by me. I believe that the proliferation of these "unauthorized" decoys has lead to the demise of many caches in our area and around SC. I believe that they draw too much "unwanted" attention to the cache. Thank you for your cooperation. Happy Caching!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Ammo Can in the Woods, hidden in the midst of friends.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363738263"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:25:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3100031">Team Michtana</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We traveled the country. Try to get as many as easy as we can. Don’t know if we will ever get them all.  But it sure is fun.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364582516"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T13:52:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35451479">naturelvr59</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Trail closed. To far for us in this heat. 86*</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352390866"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-02T07:17:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30988181">Colorado_Marty</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I actually found this back on March 23rd. Not sure why. My log seems to be missing but I figured just as well repost it. All is good tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1347893753"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3837551">Lalang</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the cache, we are headed south today, with this cache one of the goals. This is our 24th Cache Across America find (Langlie is incorrect in his log) Yippee!! We struggled with parking lots closed, so we found a pull over to just get this one, and bagged the plan for the oldies and puzzles too. oh, well. 

Langlie and I traded snow boots for hiking shoes and left the Minnesota cold far behind — and honestly, we haven’t looked back. 

So far this journey has been everything we hoped for and more — picking up new counties, visiting some beloved oldies, standing atop a few high points, and adding more CAA and Cache Odyssey finds to the list. Every day feels like its own mini expedition, with winding back roads, unexpected stops, and caches that lead us to places we never would have discovered otherwise.

TFTC and happy caching from the road! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1347643750"><groundspeak:date>2026-02-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2409869">Langlie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today is day 28 of a 30+ day trip south from Minneapolis to South Shores, AL for all the MEGA action. Making our way north, albeit slowly! Last night we camped at Solitude point campground. We are now on the road to somewhere else, but before we get there, we stopped for this one. Lalang loves a CCA, so we make certain we stop, this works out to be #21, fun stuff! TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.887617" lon="-97.058483"><time>2006-07-14T00:00:00</time><name>GCX4Y3</name><desc>Cache Across America – South Dakota by martinell</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCX4Y3</url><urlname>Cache Across America – South Dakota</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="427774" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – South Dakota</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>martinell</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1796714">room104</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>South Dakota</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Cache Across America – South Dakota
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;South Dakota&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/user/84dde5b7-a807-4e83-af23-2f9f856efe8b.jpg" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Pierre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Sioux Falls&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 17th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 46th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 39th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Watertown, South Dakota's 4th largest city located along I-29 and US 212 in Northeastern South Dakota. A quiet, safe, progressive city. A perfect place to make memories for a lifetime. Enjoy great hunting, fishing, swimming and camping at our beautiful lakes. Home of the popular Terry Redlin Art Center and other talented artists, cultural and historical attractions, unique shops and wonderful hospitality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.watertownsd.com"&gt;http://www.watertownsd.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache rests by the Redlin Art Museum. Redlin's most compelling project is the construction of the museum to house his original art in Watertown, South Dakota, where he now resides. The Redlin Art Center, which includes a regional tourism office, Domed Theater, and state-of-the-art Amphitheater, opened in the summer of 1997 and has seen more than 1 million visitors from all over the world. Terry Redlin donated the $10 million museum to the State of South Dakota in appreciation for an art scholarship he received after graduating from high school in Watertown.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Few artists can rival the standards of excellence achieved by Master Artist Terry Redlin over the past 25 years. He is truly one of the country's most widely collected painters of wildlife and Americana. For eight consecutive years, 1991 through 1998, Redlin has been named America's Most Popular Artist in annual gallery surveys conducted by U.S.ART magazine. His induction into U.S.ART's Hall of Fame in 1992 followed the magazine's poll of 900 galleries nationwide which, that year, placed five of Redlin's limited editions in the top 11 in popularity. Over the life of the poll, 30 prints have been included in that list. His use of earthy colors, blazing sunrises and sunsets and nostalgic themes are often cited as the reasons for his immense popularity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache has been placed by the approval from Executive Director Julie Ranum of the Redlin Art Center.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://redlinart.com/"&gt;Visit the Museum Web Site.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://redlinart.com/artist.php"&gt;http://redlinart.com/artist.php&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1045957104"><groundspeak:date>2021-08-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dear CAA watchers and players::

We are always sad to see an old classic CAA cache get archived, but sometimes as the game and players evolve this is sometimes unavoidable. 

The great news is that there is a brand new CAA SD cache up and running in this same location! The new CAA SD is GC9EMYE and the master list has been updated.

Thank you for your patience as it takes time for the archival and replacement process to complete. Thank you also to reviewer GeoCrater for your assistance throughout this process.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1045667638"><groundspeak:date>2021-08-27T07:49:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1778438">GeoCrater</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I am regretfully archiving this cache since there's been no response from nor action by the cache owner within the time frame requested in the last reviewer note.

GeoCrater
Geocaching.com Community Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1039091939"><groundspeak:date>2021-08-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6497286">RogueAirPirate</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Enjoyed the leisure walk to GZ at the Center. Cache found quickly in good condition and log was signed. Thanks for getting this one back in order. Really enjoying the series!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1037438917"><groundspeak:date>2021-07-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5909880">SimmyJellers</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">All is perfect here. Hopefully it can stay for future finders to keep having fun.
This is Cache Across America #7 for this road trip. There will be hopefully a few more over the next few weeks.
Day 6. Today was mostly spent traveling far out of my way, just to visit some phone line in northern Minnesota. Then from there to as close to Fargo as I could get. Another fantastic day seeing what all this planet has to offer.
I am currently driving cross country from Maryland to Montana, ultimately to spend some time in Glacier. My goal is to navigate by the Cache Across America series. I also left time to stop for anything else that looks amazing, really old ones and high favorites. That is how I ended up here! Thanks for placing and maintaining this hide, and adding more fun to my amazing time playing!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1036892196"><groundspeak:date>2021-07-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello CAA watchers and players. Without a forthcoming CO response regarding maintenance, this cache will be archived very soon. While we are always sad to lose an original CAA cache, when a CO stops responding our options are limited as per Groundspeak rules.  Please know there is a plan in place to submit for publication a brand new CAA SD as soon as possible in case of said archival. Keep watch on this page for developments. Thank you! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="36.084417" lon="-86.895467"><time>2006-07-01T00:00:00</time><name>GCWX5K</name><desc>Cache Across America - Tennessee by salpal</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCWX5K</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Tennessee</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="420319" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Tennessee</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>salpal</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="215950">salpal</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Tennessee</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>12/29/2007: Please be sure the camo and other things are disguising
the cache well. Hopefully it won't go MIA again.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br&gt;
