</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Just Hanging.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="561878621"><groundspeak:date>2015-12-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">For Cache Across America players and watchers, the new CAA Texas is up and running!  You can find the new Austin-area CAA TX at:

https://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?wp=GC677MT&amp;title=cache-across-america-texas</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="561694955"><groundspeak:date>2015-12-13T16:51:55</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="601992">Bigguy  In  Texas</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This great cache has been moved closer to the Austin (state capitol) area. I am excited to be able to share this great challenge to caches in the Central Texas area. If you have already found this one when it was near Abilene, I invite you to come back to find this new one and enjoy some of the areas other great caches. A big thank you to ZSteve  (for his help) and Lorriebird for the opportunity to continue this very cool cache.

The GC code for the new cache is GC677MT, see you soon!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="555957527"><groundspeak:date>2015-11-09T17:43:41</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="601992">Bigguy  In  Texas</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache Across America - Texas was transferred from AMMOMAN to user Bigguy  In  Texas</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="553202397"><groundspeak:date>2015-10-30T12:55:20</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6066891">Tarheel4Life</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I believe this cache is missing.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="553202391"><groundspeak:date>2015-10-30T12:19:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6066891">Tarheel4Life</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Searched for 20 minutes and couldn't find it. Very disappointing.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.005033" lon="-112.313567"><time>2006-07-16T00:00:00</time><name>GCX1PB</name><desc>Cache Across America – Utah by UTAG </desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCX1PB</url><urlname>Cache Across America – Utah</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="424682" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – Utah</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>UTAG </groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="74159">UTAG</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Utah</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Utah&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Flag_of_Utah.svg/660px-Flag_of_Utah.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Salt Lake City&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Salt Lake City&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 13th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 34th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 45th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41" target="_blank"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7" target="_blank"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="http://i65.photobucket.com/albums/h221/damenacek/FillmoreCapital.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; On October 5, 1851, the Territorial Legislature of Utah passed a resolution providing for the organization and settlement of Millard County with the seat of government in the county, to be called Fillmore City, named after the President of the United Sates, Millard Fillmore.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The city was planned to be the Capitol of the State, and construction began on the "Statehouse." The first wing of what was to be a monumental structure was completed and used for legislative sessions in 1855 and 1856. The building was never completed and the Capitol was moved to Salt Lake City.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The Statehouse stands today as the oldest existing governmental building in the state.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cache can be accessed via exit 167. Travel about one mile on the West frontage road&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Territorial Statehouse Sign</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1242674090"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hooray! Finally! 

The new Cache Across America - Utah cache has gone live.

It is GCARCTE and is located in the Zion area. 

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1241690514"><groundspeak:date>2024-06-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dear CAA players and watchers... the new CAA Utah is almost ready and we hope to have it online very soon. Just a heads up for your planning purposes, it will be in the Zion area. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1237484628"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dear CAA watchers and players:

 We are relieved to see a resolution on this cache as Utah has been in limbo for quite some time. While it is unfortunate  to archive a CAA cache, over time new locations and active owners must be updated. We thank UTAG for their years of being a CAA cache owner. 

We are very excited to report that we have a new Cache Across America - Utah cache in the works, but of course the new CO couldn’t move forward with the placement and approval process until the current one was either replaced or archived. We don’t have the final location assured pending the permission process, but we can report that it will be in the southeast quadrant of the state. 

Please know that we are moving as quickly as we can to finally get Utah up and running again, and are very happy that the new location will proudly represent the gorgeous state of Utah! 

We will post the GC of the new cache here as well as on the master lists of CAA caches. 
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1237435713"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-30T19:24:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2388405">BlueRajah</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I am archiving this cache to keep it from continually showing up in search lists, and to prevent it from blocking other cache placements. The reviewers requested the cache to be reviewed and no action was taken.  If this was done in error please contact me immediately.  If the cache was archived because of maintenance issues (no response to our earlier notes on the cache page)  you will need to submit a new cache.


Thank you,
BlueRajah
Volunteer Geocache Reviewer  - Utah</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1237100546"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-28T20:22:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Needs Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8756231">Seemyshell</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It’s been a few months since the reviewer gave notice on this cache, with no response from the CO. 
It may be time to go, to allow a replacement by a regular player. 
Cheers 🍻 
Seemyshell </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.277317" lon="-72.569367"><time>2006-08-07T00:00:00</time><name>GCXJHP</name><desc>Cache Across America – Vermont by Tharagleb adopted by DJ and CAL</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXJHP</url><urlname>Cache Across America – Vermont</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="440875" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – Vermont</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Tharagleb adopted by DJ and CAL</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="285063">DJ and CAL</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Vermont</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A short walk in a city park. Park in the parking lot and cross the river on the foot bridge. When you get within 75 or 100 feet you can start bushwhacking. Have fun!
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Vermont&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/e/ee/Vermont_state_flag.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Montpelier&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Burlington&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 43rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 49th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 14th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is located in a park in Montpelier, Vermont. It is an easy hike and kid friendly. The cache itself is located about 75 feet from the trail and a little bushwhacking is involved. During the summer there is lots of vegetation but in the winter it is easier to get to the cache. However in the winter snow may make the cache difficult to find.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Montpelier is the smallest capital city in the U.S., and yet it has many attractions for tourists and locals alike. The capitol building is a great place to photograph with its golden dome and green lawn. There is nearby Hubbard Park and its tower, the Vermont Historical Society Museum, the T.W. Wood Art Gallery and Green Mount Cemetery with unique monuments from talented sculptors. From May to October there is a farmer's market downtown on Saturdays from 9:00 A.M. to 1:00 P.M.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The original cache contents is several Vermont souvenirs (keychains, magnets, euro stickers and the like); a bunch of TB's (including the 50-State TB) and the log book. It would be nice if you traded items from other states, but not required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Under a large tree, container is a Lock &amp; Lock.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364917253"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5653263">GalinaF</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Enjoyed my walk to the GZ despite rather muddy trails. Didn't feel safe searching for the CC as there was a tent and a fire ring very close to the GZ. Glad that the coords were dead on, and it was a very quick find, so I didn't disturb anyone in the tent. There was water in the CC and the log was damp, but signable. I'd call the size of the CC "small". Grabbed a TB. Thanks!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361010390"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T18:59:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14566146">CheekyBrit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">That is possibly the wettest cache across America i have done thus far. If I ever manage to swim out to Hawaii that one will win.
Things are soaking wet all around but it is dry inside the logbook hiding spot. Thanks for adding to the adventure and to this illustrious series.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359104563"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-26T13:22:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5040676">BlackCats3</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Up north with Mrs. Brown dog for local yarn day and ended up staying over till Sunday.  She needed a regular for a challenge they were working on and this cache fit the bill. She made a quick find here and we decided to keep hiking since it was such a great day and there was another cash out further ahead of us so if we went.  tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357605485"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4428457">BrownDog09</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today filled the second to last day that we need to fill in order to have a Regular for EVERY day of the year!! BlackCats3, had hung out this weekend with me since Mr. BD is away for work. I planned this hiking area so then we could divide and head our own ways afterwards but yet the BD herself could get in a pretty good walk. The trails were MUCH drier than I was expecting. We came up to this cache and found it pretty quickly, although I am pretty sure that this wouldn't be a Regular but I'm okay with that, we found it! Once tucked away and hidden again we decided to go and find the other cache in the park and enjoy the nice spring day! 
TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1349566021"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15248411">maysv</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">10th CAA! Almost had to give up on this one. Very thankful for all of the spoiler photos, because I could not have found the cache without them. I had to dig so much snow, and if there's another cacher soon they'll have it very easy. Started digging, got confused when I didn't find it, and realized I had to dig through more snow. Might've given up if I didn't have gloves. 

A nice trail, I thought it was cool that you could borrow snowshoes. Didn't need them, but I did wear my spikes because a lot of the uphill trail was ice. Could probably use another log. Enjoyed a nice sunset. Also happy to have another state capital completed since there's always a challenge for that. 

With this being my third cache I've found in Vermont, (and the first time I've been in Vermont,) this marks my 47/51 state I've cached in! and the 47/50 state I've been to. Very exciting. Rhode Island, New Hampshire and Maine left for me. 

TFTC #1287</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="36.67835" lon="-81.93578333333333"><time>2007-03-06T00:00:00</time><name>GC11A1X</name><desc>Cache Across America - Virginia by treasure_hunter</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC11A1X</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Virginia</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="551861" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Virginia</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>treasure_hunter</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="63226">treasure_hunter</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Virginia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Virginia&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src=
"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Flag_of_Virginia.svg/670px-Flag_of_Virginia.svg.png"
     width="187" height="135"&gt; 
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Richmond&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Virginia Beach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 35th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 12th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 10th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=bf517972-5f45-4ed9-ac4b-afbde9231a6c"&gt;
HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle"
    bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg"
     width="450" height="221"&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a
series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire
United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These
caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;
one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion
of the series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;This cache is located just
outside of Abingdon, VA. I felt that Abingdon was a great location
to place the cache. It is not far from Interstate-81, only about
8-10 min away. The cache is located at an opening to the Creeper
Trail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After exiting from I-81 continue on US 58 Lee Hwy. For approx.
1.3 mi then make a right on Watauga Rd. for approx. 2.2 mi.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Abingdon is a town in Washington County, Virginia, 189 miles
(304 km) west by south of Lynchburg. In 1910, 1,757 people lived
here. The population was 7,780 at the 2000 census. It is the county
seat of Washington County. The town is included in the Tri-Cities
Metro area of Johnson City-Kingsport-Bristol, TN-VA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The land that the city of Abingdon is situated on was originally
surveyed between the years 1748 and 1750 by Dr. Thomas Walker and
was part of the Great Road that Colonel William Byrd III ordered
cut through the wilderness on to Kingsport, Tennessee. In 1760,
famed frontiersman, Daniel Boone, named the area Wolf Hills, after
his dogs were attacked by a pack of wolves during a hunting
expedition. The original location of the attack is located on
'Courthouse Hill' and is also the location of The Cavehouse Craft
Shop. During Lord Dunmore's War, Black's Fort was established in
1774 by Joseph Black to protect local settlers in the region from
Indian attacks. In 1776 the community of Black's Fort was made the
county seat of the newly formed Washington county. In 1778, Black's
Fort was incorporated as the town of Abingdon, said to be named for
the ancestral home of Martha Washington. Martha Washington College,
a school for women, operated in Abingdon from 1860 to 1932 in a
former private residence; since 1935 the building has been occupied
by a hotel, the Martha Washington Inn. The Barter Theatre, the
state theatre of Virginia, was opened in Abingdon in 1933. Virginia
Governors Wyndham Robertson, David Campbell, and John B. Floyd
lived here. Abingdon is also the final stop along the Virginia
Creeper Trail, which allows pedestrian, cyclist and equestrian
traffic. The Washington County Historical Society is located in
Abingdon and serves as a regional genealogy center, in addition as
a repository for Washington County history. .&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you
would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant
in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself
or a member of you group with the cache in your online log. If you
for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please
make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual
cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge
participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required
before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three
digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure
place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all
50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good
luck!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>count 9 posts down on top and then 2 legs under. You will find the cache tucked away in the ties!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="397576779"><groundspeak:date>2014-04-16T15:06:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Didn't find it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6600545">LonelyGoose</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">DNF, even though the hint was pretty clear.  Hasn't been found in 2 years, so may need maintenance.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="352749817"><groundspeak:date>2013-09-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache Across America watchers:  There is now a brand new Cache Across America Virginia cache published: GC4NMVK.  Here is a link to the Cache Across America bookmark which contains all CAA caches past and present and is kept updated at all times:


http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41

Thank you for your patience, and Cache Across America on!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="340245772"><groundspeak:date>2013-08-15T17:24:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2426990">offline.cacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Archiving.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="340248254"><groundspeak:date>2013-08-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">For watchers of this cache and those participating in the Cache Across America series of caches, thank you for your patience.  We are working quickly to get a new CAA VA published as soon as possible.  The new owner may choose this location or a different location.  As soon as we know where the new owner will choose we will post a note both here and on this CAA list:

http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41

Again, thank you for your patience and just know that we work as quickly as we can to put Virginia back in play.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="335135034"><groundspeak:date>2013-07-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1525116">SmilingBee</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bummed out because we were here and couldn't get it and the clue.  :-(</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="47.658533" lon="-122.426767"><time>2006-07-05T00:00:00</time><name>GCWWRT</name><desc>Cache Across America - Washington by Blue Power Ranger (originally placed by fishiam)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCWWRT</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Washington</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="419953" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Washington</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Blue Power Ranger (originally placed by fishiam)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="527285">Blue Power Ranger</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Washington</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Washington&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src=
"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Flag_of_Washington.svg/553px-Flag_of_Washington.svg.png"
     width="187" height="135"&gt; 
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Olympia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Seattle&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 18th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 14th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 42nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=bf517972-5f45-4ed9-ac4b-afbde9231a6c"&gt;
HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle"
    bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src=
"http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg"
     width="450" height="221"&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a
series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire
United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These
caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel=
"nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;
one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion
of the series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;This cache series is all about
discovery. That was reason enough to select Seattle's Discovery
Park as the cache site for Washington's entry into the Cache Across
America series. Seattle is also a gateway to the Pacific, thus a
beach hide seemed also appropriate. Finally, this is my family's
favorite beach in the city so we are motivated to properly maintain
this cache. The cache is a large ammo can. It is available at all
water levels but is somewhat easier to access at lower than high
tide since the beach walk is simpler than the driftwood scramble.
Please re-hide at least as well as you found it.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
There are quite a few other caches in Discovery Park you may enjoy
when you visit:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=ea15632e-7d30-4f14-84f0-2bb9e4d8404a"&gt;
I Could Come Here Every Day and Not Get Bored&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=82a2621f-4d2b-47fc-b6f4-d804e273bb31"&gt;
West Point Light&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=324b0501-8163-43c1-b413-a89a73821181"&gt;
Discoteca - A Very Disco Park&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=4a54c9be-4c8b-4fdc-a864-a4dd2a9a58ff"&gt;
Designation: HARRY&lt;br&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=789524ca-34a4-4309-9bc4-10a64459c876"&gt;
Discovering Discovery 101&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=0df83828-8449-4906-ba22-f12cda37dddd"&gt;
Used To Be!! Biking Trails&lt;br&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href=
"http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=0ee119e9-3ee8-4706-9cb4-22bb480c3148"&gt;
Big Camo'd Ammo Can from the Little Rams!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you
would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant
in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself
or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you
for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please
make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual
cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge
participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required
before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three
digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure
place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all
50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good
luck!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>It's a driftwood hide</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="58129547"><groundspeak:date>2008-12-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="884447">jcurtis55</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">See GCX7TR for the current Washington CAA cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="49641040"><groundspeak:date>2008-07-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1485888">Zane26</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I saw it in the magazine also to bad its archived[:(]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="49521816"><groundspeak:date>2008-07-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1142352">Sherlock Boy</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I saw this on the Ranger Rick Mag!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="37999188"><groundspeak:date>2008-01-21T07:44:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="527285">Blue Power Ranger</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sad day for caches in Discovery Park. 

The reason for the archive...
http://forums.groundspeak.com/GC/index.php?showtopic=177879

Standby for the new Cache Across America - Washington coming soon. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="36195053"><groundspeak:date>2007-12-07T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="488057">korth</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Went to grab this one for my 100th find, before it goes away. Ammo box was sitting in plain sight so it made it a bit easier! Signed log, took sand dollar coin to release it from its purgatory, left a nebraska quarter. Hid it better than I found it.  Thanks for bringing me to this great spot; hope the caching activity can continue here in the future ....</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="47.187567" lon="-124.198833"><time>2006-07-19T00:00:00</time><name>GCX7TR</name><desc>Cache Across America - Washington by FluteFace</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCX7TR</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Washington</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="430554" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Washington</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>FluteFace</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="87639">FluteFace</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="1">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="1">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Washington</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Washington&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Flag_of_Washington.svg/553px-Flag_of_Washington.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Olympia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Seattle&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 18th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 14th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 42nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/f6e55ebb-dd28-47ec-93ba-20da0e5a7a41.jpg" align="left" vspace="10" hspace="20" border="2" /&gt;The Washington coast has always been one of my favorite places -- a place to center myself, a place to renew. I have been coming to this area, just a bit north of the city of Ocean Shores, for years. It's a beautiful and rugged place, its scenic wildness sculpted by the wind and water. Be attentive as you come out this way. Wildlife is bountiful -- many birds (including bald eagles) and flowers and, if you're watchful, a deer or two.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can literally drive up to this cache, although I would suggest parking just a bit to the north, where the view is better. Grab the cache, enjoy the view, then move on. Keep a hand on your young ones as it is a long drop (there is no need to venture beyond the guardrail) and the road you are next to can be busy at times. Also be a bit sneaky as there are usually muggles nearby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note how the cache is placed when you snag it and return it the same way (largest flat side to largest flat side), as far in as you can get it. I promise, you can't place it too far out of reach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want sandy beach access, Roosevelt Beach is just to the south with parking and a bathroom.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="blue"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Congrats to Kosiusmc on his FTF. He won a set of unactivated TB tags.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As always, please let me know if there are any problems with the coordinates or the cache. Most importantly, have fun!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!--- Begin WSGA Logo =--&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.wsgaonline.org" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3130/2898182648_28499a5d9e_o.gif" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;!--- End WSGA Logo =--&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of you group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The joy is guarded, just inside the rail.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363042392"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5889280">Checkers042</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Another CAA down! #34 for me. Made the most out of this long weekend with a trip to the coast to check off Washington and Oregon from my list. This was a great way to start the day. All in good shape here, tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362982810"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T11:42:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="50045989">Mamatrucker1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC with Orville 999 Texas ⭐️ and Zoe. Beautiful location!  ☮️😊</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360504444"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T10:18:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4080322">Megster66</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Driving along the coast with Dewettes to get some caches, grabbing this CAA along the way - TFTC SL </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359208252"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T18:49:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3980840">Dewettes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello from Georgia 🍑
Myself, Megster66, her fiancé, and doggo Sadie are driving along the coast from Seaside OR to Seabrook  WA for the day. 

My motto certainly applies here:
The things we do for a Smiley 😃 
We drove over 100 miles and 2+ hours one way from Astoria OR to here just to get this CAA. Thank goodness this was a very quick and easy park and grab. Lovely location along the coast. Got the code and photo ops. 
CAA#29
SL TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357989945"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-29T14:54:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3729065">duma332</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It was such a beautiful day today I drove to the ocean caching along the way.  When I stopped here, there were 2 people in another car stopped to take photos.  I enjoyed the view until they drove off and got the cache.  It was covered with tiny, tiny ants swarming all over it.  Upon opening it, there were a bunch inside too — but I signed the log, tried to brush most off and closed it.  Thanks for placing it here to get me to stop.  I never tire of seeing the ocean.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.412933" lon="-82.41915"><time>2006-07-23T00:00:00</time><name>GCXA6B</name><desc>Cache Across America - West Virginia by oldnavy59</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCXA6B</url><urlname>Cache Across America - West Virginia</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="432835" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - West Virginia</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>oldnavy59</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>West Virginia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This Cache is to Pay Honor to Those that died and to those who carried on and rebuilt. They demonstrated the Spirit of West Virginia This cache is a medium sized Lock &amp;amp; Lock container. Please rehide as good or better then when you find it.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;West Virginia&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/1/1a/West_Virginia_state_flag.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Charleston&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Charleston&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 41st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 37th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 35th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=945ad12c-cf93-4d79-99ad-c3d727f767da"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;This cache is located not far from the Memorial Honoring those who died in the Marshall Plane crash. The Marshall Memorial honors the University football team, coaches, staff and supporters who died in the November, 1970 plane crash. In front of the obelisk are six unmarked graves, in memory of the victims that could not be identified. The names of these six are engraved in the front face of the memorial. Bobby Pruett called Marshall's rise from the ashes of the crash to national prominence "truly God's miracle."It's still considered a very special time in the history of Thundering Herd football. Following the plane crash in November 1970, Marshall had pieced together a football team for the following season and the media called it the "Young Thundering Herd." It was the first home game after the crash. With no time left on the clock in the September 25, 1971 game, Terry Gardner, No. 26, a freshman pulled in a pass from quarterback Reggie Oliver for a 15-13 win over Xavier. The score came on a play never used by the Herd. On a bootleg screen pass off the left side, Oliver threw to Gardner instead of to the expected receiver who was well covered. "It was a storybook finish," proclaimed new coach Jack Lengyel in the locker room after the victory. "No one thought we had a chance to win except the team." The Herd finished the year 2-8, also beating Bowling Green.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Spirit of your typical West Virginian was demonstrated many times following the tragic event. Which is why I chose this place. Please be respectful as visit this Monument. Gates are closed to vehicular traffic at sundown however foot traffic is still allowed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.easycounter.com/"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.easycounter.com/counter.php?oldnavy59" border="0" alt="Hit Counters" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.easycounter.com/FreeCounter3.html"&gt;Hit Counter&lt;/a&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Base of tree</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1168688247"><groundspeak:date>2023-05-21T12:25:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2464712">Troopbiz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">**Cache Across America - West Virginia**
**Find #10173**

**About My Day**
Was in the area for Kryzstof and RainB0w_G00se’s wedding but couldn’t make the drive home without checking out some caches. Made the short drive down to Beech Fork State Park and Marshall and found a few along the way. Thanks, lorriebird, for placing and maintaining this hide! TFTC SL

As the new CAA - West Virginia owner, I felt it was only right I make my way to Huntington to pay respect to the original cache. This is such a nice spot for a cache, although I do see how it could have attracted muggle attention. Picked up any remains of the cache to ensure no litter is left behind. Thanks for keeping this one alive! It served it's purpose well.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1166333607"><groundspeak:date>2023-05-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you to all cachers who worked with us while we transitioned from this Cache Across America West Virginia cache to the newly published one, we thank you for your patience during the process. We left both the old and the new CAA WV caches available in tandem for a couple of weeks to help cachers currently on road trips to complete their missions. From this date forward only finds on the new CAA WV will be accepted for the Cache Across America series of caches. 

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1163987315"><groundspeak:date>2023-05-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3101648">camper248</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Noooooooooo.  Going there as part of our trip to Woodstock and were planning on stopping here to get this one.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1163422446"><groundspeak:date>2023-04-30T12:17:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sadly it is time to say goodbye to this sentimental favorite location. We would like to thank oldnavy59 for his many years of service to the Cache Across America series of caches in the service of WV. Without individual state owners the CAA series would not exist.

The good news is that there is a brand new Cache Across America - West Virginia: GCA7F55. It is in a gorgeous location within Coopers Rock State Park in the northern part of WV. 

For those working on CAA and are currently on road trips, we will work with you for the next few days if you are already enroute to this old location. There is currently no code in the container, so take a photo of yourself that identifies you at the location and you will be provided with the code. 

For those of you making plans to attend one of the mega events over the next couple of months, we wanted to give you a heads up as far in advance as possible for your road trip planning to include the new CAA WV as this one is no longer available.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1162665632"><groundspeak:date>2023-04-27T21:47:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is a sad one for me to write. While this location is a sentimental favorite for many (including myself) the cache has for quite some time not been in good condition as a game piece cache for the Cache Across America series. After researching the long history of this cache, we have realized that this cache is often damaged, muggled or has operated as a ‘throw down’ when the cache goes missing (which has happened too often over the past couple of years). 

This cache will be archived soon, but we will leave it only disabled for a few days for those who are currently en route or on road trips. There is a container on site, but it is a throw down with no code in it. For those working on Cache Across America, please take a photo showing you on location and I will send you the WV code.

This cache will be archived by May 1. There is a new  CAA West Virginia in the works that should be published soon. It is in the northern part of the state and more information will be forthcoming. We will absolutely work with CAA players to help with the transition to the new WV cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.502686" lon="-88.061"><time>2006-07-02T00:00:00</time><name>GCWY01</name><desc>Cache Across America - Wisconsin by AstroD-Team</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCWY01</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Wisconsin</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="421107" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Wisconsin</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>AstroD-Team</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="178323">Astro_D</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Micro</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="1">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Wisconsin</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;b&gt;Lambeau Field’s ORIGINAL geocache. Since 2006!&lt;/b&gt; &lt;img src="http://www.wi-geocaching.com/awards/April2017NortheastZone.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;PLEASE NOTE: SPECIAL PERMISSION HAS BEEN SECURED FOR THE PLACEMENT OF THIS CACHE BY MR. TED EISENBACH - DIRECTOR OF FACILITIES &amp;amp; MR. GERRY PARIN - DIRECTOR OF SECURITY. DUE TO THE SECURITY SENSITIVITY OF THE LOCATION, PLEASE BE DISCREET, CONSIDERATE AND RESPECTFUL. THIS CACHE HAS BEEN ALLOWED DUE TO BEING PART OF A SPECIAL NATIONWIDE SERIES.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;b&gt;CACHE DESCRIPTION AND LINKS WITHIN DESCRIPTION HAVE BEEN UPDATED ON 7.29.2020&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Wisconsin&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;a href="http://beta.photobucket.com/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="http://i63.photobucket.com/albums/h125/GateGeek/wistateflag_zpsf1957cbf.jpg" border="0" alt="Photobucket" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Madison&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Milwaukee&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 23rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 18th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 30th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;PLEASE DO NOT LOOK FOR THIS CACHE ON GAME DAYS OR DURING MAJOR STADIUM/ATRIUM ACTIVITIES.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nothing says Wisconsin better than beer, brats, cheese and football! Where in this great state can you find all these in one place? Why a journey to the very heart of it all - Lambeau Field! Lambeau Field is located in the small and quaint city of Green Bay (the stadium and lot is in Green Bay) - one of Wisconsin's oldest settlements. The cache is a fake rock located in a medium traffic area. When the Packers are at home, it will be impossible to find this one undetected. PLEASE DO NOT HUNT DURING PACKER HOME GAMES!! Please, BE DISCREET AND RESPECTFUL AT ALL TIMES. The location of this cache offers some great photo ops. When you're done finding the cache, take a stroll through the atrium, shop at the Packers Pro Shop and eat at one of the fine establishments located inside. So come see and experience what makes Wisconsin great!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a href="http://www.wunderground.com/cgi-bin/findweather/getForecast?query=zmw:54229.2.99999&amp;amp;bannertypeclick=wu_blueglass"&gt;&lt;img src="http://weathersticker.wunderground.com/weathersticker/cgi-bin/banner/ban/wxBanner?bannertype=wu_blueglass_both&amp;amp;airportcode=KGRB&amp;amp;ForcedCity=Green%20Bay&amp;amp;ForcedState=WI&amp;amp;zipcode=54229&amp;amp;language=EN" alt="Click for Green Bay, Wisconsin Forecast" height="90" width="160" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="display:block !important;width:170px;text-align:center;font-family:sans-serif;font-size:12px;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.wunderground.com/cgi-bin/findweather/getForecast?query=Green%20Bay,%20WI" title="Green Bay, WI Weather Forecast"&gt;&lt;img src="http://weathersticker.wunderground.com/weathersticker/sunandmoon150/language/english/US/WI/Green_Bay.gif" alt="Find more about Weather in Green Bay, WI" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://www.wunderground.com" title="Get latest Weather Forecast updates" style="font-family:sans-serif;font-size:12px;"&gt;Click for weather forecast&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Up the steps. At the top, take the corner seat on your right. Reach behind for the fake rock tucked against the wall between your seat and the light post.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1065110132"><groundspeak:date>2021-11-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3457860">ralverde</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Looks like the new hide is GC9ACQH.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1015341828"><groundspeak:date>2021-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8814283">TheLF</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks AstroD-Team for owning this one so long and keeping up the maintenance.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1000799843"><groundspeak:date>2021-03-17T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello Cache Across America players. We are very sad to see this classic original CAA cache archived. I will never forget my own road trip to find it so many years ago and this location is in the video I made.  We will be ever so grateful to the AstroD-Team for all the years of hard work (and it IS hard work!) of being a Cache Across America state cache owner. Without individual state owners the CAA series could not exist. Just know that we are aware of this archival and are working on a solution as soon as possible. Thank you for your patience! ...and THANK YOU AstroD-Team for your years of dedication. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1000789704"><groundspeak:date>2021-03-17T09:10:46</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="178323">Astro_D</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Well, after much thought, this one is going by the wayside. It has gone missing much too often in the last year than in the last 15 years it’s been active. I can’t tell you the last time we even attempted to look for a geocache  (it’s been years). 

Hopefully someone will get this one up and running. But keep in mind, that if one wishes to place a new physical cache here, permission will need to be sought from the Packers organization. My blanket permission will not extend to any new/adopted/replaced  physical caches placed here. 

Thanks for all the finds and support of this cache. And this series in general. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="999741568"><groundspeak:date>2021-03-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5161635">TeamJanine&amp;Jon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Are you getting close to replacing this cache?</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.63155" lon="-110.565217"><time>2006-10-02T00:00:00</time><name>GCYMZZ</name><desc>Cache Across America - Wyoming by Onerka - adopted by Lorriebird</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCYMZZ</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Wyoming</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="472999" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Wyoming</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Onerka - adopted by Lorriebird</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="0">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="0">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="0">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="0">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="29" inc="0">Telephone nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="62" inc="1">Seasonal access</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="0">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="10" inc="0">Difficult climb</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Wyoming</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Wyoming&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Flag_of_Wyoming.svg/744px-Flag_of_Wyoming.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Cheyenne&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Cheyenne&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 10th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 50th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 44th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Jackson Hole and the surrounding National Parks (Grand Teton and Yellowstone) are popular tourist destinations, so this seemed like a logical spot to put this cache. The road to the cache is paved and plowed in the winter. The cache is near the road, but for safety reasons please park in the small parking lot just past the cache. The cache was placed near the road (instead of near "The Marrying Tree") to allow easier winter access.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for a unique perspecive of the Teton Mountains, then this cache is for you. This is a popular spot for summer weddings, so the tree at the end of the short path is locally known as "The Marrying Tree".&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363642497"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T20:31:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24669481">dragonchash</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cool spot.
Nice tree, and easy find.

CAA #1 here we go!!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362716563"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T14:24:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14566146">CheekyBrit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This one has been taunting me for quite some time being so close as the crow fide flies and yet , requiring pretty much an entire day to come and get. My journey , returning home from work on the east coast was an excellent excuse to find myself able to make a small detour to get this bad boy. The wedding tree location nearby is utterly fantastic.And for that alone earns this a favorite point. Add on to that , the fact that this is cash across america and this is brilliant. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362439536"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T06:24:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54964614">annaskare67</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Photo from our find 📸</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361563738"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T17:18:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55056431">tonester2013</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361246570"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T17:18:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54964614">annaskare67</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you!!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.78595" lon="-71.37005"><time>2012-09-22T00:00:00</time><name>GC3XAC9</name><desc>Cache Across America – Rhode Island (#3) by Downy288</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC3XAC9</url><urlname>Cache Across America – Rhode Island (#3)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3203582" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – Rhode Island (#3)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Downy288</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="73561">RIclimber</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Rhode Island</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>A replacement CCA-RI cache. &lt;font color="red"&gt;There is now a Letterbox nearby. &lt;b&gt;Don't take the stamp!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td rowspan="4" bgcolor="#999966" width="190" align="center"&gt;
