&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Rotted hole in tree.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="708050114"><groundspeak:date>2017-08-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hooray! Finally we have a new Cache Across America Rhode Island in place, GC78QC5!!! We are most grateful to geogerry36 for stepping up to the plate as the new CAA RI owner who went above and beyond getting this one published after we lost our old location. Without individual state owners like him the Cache Across America series would not exist. Cache on!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="708009418"><groundspeak:date>2017-08-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1015404">coloReido</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The new CAA RI is here!  Check out GC78QC5  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="703098726"><groundspeak:date>2017-07-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">For those of you awaiting the new Cache Across America Rhode Island: We are delayed as we have run into a snag and have lost the location of the old CAA RI due to a claim on the location.  We are in the process of finding a new location and hope to have everything revised in a couple of weeks. Just wanted to update everyone on the progress, and we are working on it.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="693389699"><groundspeak:date>2017-06-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="733552">GeoGerms</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Mahalo lorriebird!  Bummaz on the cache, but I totally understand.  Mahalo to all the owners and maintainers of the series for all your hard work.  Will gettum the next time through the Ocean State.  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="693384430"><groundspeak:date>2017-06-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello GeoGerms, while we are working as quickly as possible to get the new CAA Rhode Island up and running, I am afraid it will likely take longer than just a few more days. The new owner is still deciding where the location will be and then the cache will be published. Keeping the CAA series up and running is a labor of love and we are doing the best we can. My apologies that your visit coincided with the archival of the old one. Best regards, Lorriebird</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.982783" lon="-105.44555"><time>2011-09-21T00:00:00</time><name>GC34KP9</name><desc>Cache Across America - Colorado by cameltrekor</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC34KP9</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Colorado</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2497557" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Colorado</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>cameltrekor</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Colorado</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This cache is the third iteration for this series.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/seek/cache_details.aspx?guid=15761471-7958-4e35-a0ec-bd4f9485b946" target="_blank"&gt;previous CAA-CO&lt;/a&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Colorado&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Flag_of_Colorado.svg/800px-Flag_of_Colorado.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Denver&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Denver&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 8th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 22nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 38th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41" target="_blank"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7" target="_blank"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is placed in what I think is a typical Colorado outdoors location. Nearby, you can see both the natural and man-made in Colorado. The peak-to-peak highway takes you from one set of riches (casinos) to another (Rocky Mountain National Park). Near the cache is rock-climbing and stream fishing and/or just a spot to relax.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Upstream is the eclectic town of Nederland and downstream is a college town, Boulder. Enjoy the view, water is a valuable asset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache!&lt;br /&gt;
Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocachingcolo.com" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/07725843-2df2-4f12-a33a-0b663ad8fda4.jpg" alt="Geocaching Colorado" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Rocks by tree near road</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1191247401"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-27T12:52:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The new Cache Across America - Colorado is now published and available. The new CAA CO is near Pike's Peak, a wonderful location to represent the great state of Colorado. The new cache is GCAD7AB.

We would like to thank cameltrekor for the many years of service to the Cache Across America series of caches. Even though the CAA CO has had a couple of different locations throughout the years, cameltrekor is the original CO for Colorado and spent many years making sure Colorado was well represented. Without individual state owners, the CAA series could not exist. 

Thank you, cameltrekor, for the years of service and also for letting us know that you were ready to adopt out the Colorado cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1186776580"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-09T07:58:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The new CAA CO cache should be available in the Colorado Springs area soon, the new CO is working on it now choosing a new location. His plan is within a couple of weeks. I’ll post any updates I receive from him. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1186682740"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-08T19:34:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="193942">litngbug</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Will this be available by the end of September for a Magical Michie Tour stop?</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1186389021"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-07T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Dear Cache Across America players and watchers,

Every once in a while it is time to say a sad goodbye to a CAA cache.  This can happen for several reasons to any cache, and that includes CAA caches. 

This CAA Colorado Cache is in transition to a new owner and location. We sincerely thank cameltrekor for all the years of hard work in keeping the CAA Colorado cache up and running, this cache has been popular and we have been grateful for your participation. Without individual state owners, the Cache America Series of caches could not exist. 

The new CAA Colorado is now being created, and will be located in the Colorado Springs area. We are working as quickly as possible to get the new CO cache published and will post updates as they are available. 

Thank you for your patience!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1186141028"><groundspeak:date>2023-08-06T10:22:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="36306843">JediTrashPanda</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">CAA #12    
    
Logging with the permission of the CO, lorriebird.    
    
As I was planning my trip to Colorado, I started making a list of must-find caches. This CAA definitely was close enough to grab. As the trip got closer, I noticed the container went MIA. So, I asked the CO of she'd like me to bring a new one (what I'm holding in the photo), and she said yes.    
    
Got to GZ, old container is definitely gone based on the hint and previous log photos.    
    
Scenery here is great! Was a lot of fun driving through the canyon.     
    
Thanks again to the CO.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="36.0786" lon="-115.467067"><time>2013-05-09T00:00:00</time><name>GC4BQEX</name><desc>Cache Across America - Nevada by Clay4 &amp; whtwolfden</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4BQEX</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Nevada</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3633230" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Nevada</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Clay4 &amp; whtwolfden</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3049613">Clay4&amp;whtwolfden</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nevada</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Nevada&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Flag_of_Nevada.svg/744px-Flag_of_Nevada.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Carson City&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Las Vegas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 7th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 35th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 36th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Red Rock Canyon - Las Vegas!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Red Rock Canyon National Conservation Area presents awe-inspiring views most wouldn't expect to see near a major metropolitan city. In contrast to the bright lights and hype of the Strip, Red Rock offers desert beauty, towering red cliffs and abundant wildlife.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The Red Rock Canyon National Conservation Area receives 1.2 million visitors a year.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The mountains in the Red Rock area were formed by a number of geological forces including fractured faults where the earth's crust collided over millions of years and fossilized sand dunes. Some cliffs reach up an astounding 3,000 feet.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The sandstone rocks in the conservation area get their color from iron oxide. Over centuries the iron oxide built up, producing the vibrant, crimson color the canyon illustrates today.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
One of the more scenic parts of Red Rock Canyon is the Keystone Thrust Fault. Here, millions of years ago, two of the earth's plates collided with such force that part of one plate was shoved up and over the other. This created a magnificent contrast between grey limestone and red sandstone.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This amazing conservation area is also home to about 200 different mammals which include burros, rabbits, coyotes, bighorn sheep, red tailed hawks, golden eagles, hummingbirds and even a few wild horses, bobcats and mountain lions.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The 13-mile scenic loop drive exposes visitors to the geological history and splendor of the canyon. There are chances for photo opportunities at various locations including Calico Hills' colorful sandstone, limestone Indian roasting pits, Indian "handprints" and pictographs at Willow Springs.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Since Red Rock Canyon is so isolated and quiet, many like this recreational area as a temporary getaway from the craziness of the Las Vegas Strip. It's also a popular location for weddings.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
On certain trails, hikers can even witness waterfalls cascading into the canyon.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Red Rock is open year-round and a favorite among many tourists, sightseers, joggers, hikers and rock climbers. Visitors can also go horseback riding.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Red Rock Canyon is part of the Mojave Desert, which stretches out to the corners of California, Utah, Arizona and Nevada.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Make sure to check out the Red Rock Visitor Center, which is is bigger than you can ever imagine. The massive outdoor exhibit may be hot during the summer months, but there are plenty of areas in the shade as well as water fountains at every corner.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The area is divided into four large sections: Earth, Air, Fire and Water. Within these four sections, you'll get a chance to read about history, geography and animal and plant life. One of the fascinating facts about Red Rock is that it has 10,000 years of human history. You'll see artwork (petroglyphs) as well as fire pits, giving you an idea how native people lived.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
If you're lucky, you might get a peek at Mojave Max, the center's desert "spokes" tortoise. There are also seven female tortoises outside, so if Max is hiding you might see one of them. On certain days of the week, the workers give them ground-up plants with water, packed with plenty of nutrients.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The exhibit also features enlarged maps of the 19 different hiking trails, complete with highlights of each one.You can have a picnic at Willow Springs, or even see springs and waterfalls at Ice Box Canyon and Lost Creek. There is also a list of hiking tips just outside the gift shop.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
You'll learn that this area is a lot more colorful than ever. The interactive stations also include information on several different animals including deer, sheep, squirrels, burros, kangaroo rats, kit foxes, rabbits, roadrunners and much more. You'll also read a slew of fun animal facts. For instance, did you know that the ground squirrel uses its white fluffy tail like an umbrella to cool off his back? There is also information about creatures you may not have heard of, like the ring tail cat. This unique animal looks like a small fox with a raccoon tail. You'll even learn more about all the vibrant-colored birds (like hummingbirds and partridges) that dwell in the desert.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In addition to all the creatures, there is more to Red Rock than just cactus trees and sage bushes. The visitor center also provides information about all the types of flora, from the desert wildflowers to the purple mats and desert marigolds. Other desert plant life includes coyote tobacco, buckhorn cholla and the famous Joshua tree, home to birds, lizards, mice and more.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The gift shop sells hiking sticks (complete with bells), Southwest-inspired artwork, a variety of stuffed animals and much more. Make sure to stop by the front desk before you leave to grab free pamphlets and more information about the different hikes.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
-- Review by Jeannie Borbe&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="blue"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.redrockcanyonlv.org/" target="_blank"&gt;Click here for more information about Red Rock Canyon!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;b&gt;This cache is &lt;u&gt;not&lt;/u&gt; located in the scenic loop.&lt;br /&gt;
Therefore, &lt;u&gt;no fee&lt;/u&gt; is required to access this cache.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Also, be sure not to miss the nearby&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://coord.info/GCHY48" target="_blank"&gt;First Creek Falls Cache - GCHY48&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
It's a nice little spot to take a break!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;!-- Our brought to you by Icon --&gt;
&lt;!-- Our brought to you by Icon --&gt;
&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;img src="http://i1131.photobucket.com/albums/m550/Clay4geocache/0489ece5.jpg" width="100" height="75" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;Brought to you by&lt;br /&gt;
Clay4 &amp;amp; whtwolfden!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;!-- Our brought to you by Icon --&gt;
&lt;!-- Our brought to you by Icon --&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Rocks!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1358138286"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-27T12:43:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4364549">nozy nabor</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out with the girls geocaching: Team Libra, Jellis, and Nozy Nabor on a four day weekend. Fisherwoman (of DavidT21 &amp; Fisherwoman) was with us first two days. Flew into Las Vegas from the San Fransisco Bay Area to add to our collection of smiles.  No pressure trip just for enjoyment! Collecting Virtuals, earth caches, challenges and looking for highly favorited ones and some we just find along our journey as time permits. No pressure trip just fun time and making memories. 
So glad to find this one. Don’t have many in series but will work on it. Took pictures and made note of code. Nice hike to end our four day trip to Az and NV. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359186225"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="673850">jellis</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bug drp</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358081492"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="673850">jellis</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was one of goals for the trip to Arizona. Out here with Team Libra and nozy nabor. Beautiful location for this part of the series. This is the second one of the series I found, First was Oregon. TYFTH</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357856886"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="84135">Team Libra</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with nozy nabor and jellis while on a girls' long weekend road trip through Arizona, California and Nevada.  This cache was one of my main goals for the trip and is my fourth in the series.  Long way to go! Great hike here amongst the beautiful landscape.  Once we got to GZ, nozy spotted the cache quickly.  We all took turns signing the log and taking each other's photo.  Afterwards, we made our way to the bonus reference point.  It was not the optimal time of year to visit, but still spectacular!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1353688213"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-06T17:38:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1567152">HikingSeal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I cannot believe how many time I’ve been so close to this cache and not found it. That had been my story with CAA caches for a lot of years. This one, I’ve been here since I started focusing on CAAs and still didn’t find it until today. Quick find on a lovely trail. Thanks for bringing me here. 

Thanks for the cache!

Found with [Cachly](https://www.cach.ly/)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.616267" lon="-84.251617"><time>2013-05-17T00:00:00</time><name>GC4BPKP</name><desc>Cache Across America – Ohio by Matkat* </desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4BPKP</url><urlname>Cache Across America – Ohio</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3632418" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – Ohio</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Matkat* </groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="3789779">geocat_</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Ohio</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>In the event that I am unable to maintain this cache "geocat_" will be watching this cache for me.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Ohio&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Flag_of_Ohio.svg/480px-Flag_of_Ohio.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Columbus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Columbus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 34th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 7th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 17th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Ohio is located in the Midwest and was the first state created out of the Northwest Territory, which originally included all of modern-day Ohio, Indiana, Illinois, and parts of Michigan and Wisconsin. The word "Ohio" comes from the Iroquois Indian term "O-Y-O," which means "the great river." Chillicothe was Ohio's original capital, but in 1816, the city of Columbus became the seat of government. The north bank of the Ohio River defines Ohio's southern border. To the north, Ohio is bordered by the state of Michigan and an international boundary with Canada that passes through Lake Erie. On the east, Pennsylvania and West Virginia neighbor the state, with Indiana forming Ohio's western border. Ohio is approximately 355 kilometers across at its widest point. It is exactly the same distance from its most southerly to its most northerly point. The state encompasses 116,096 square kilometers of area. Land mass comprises 106,054 square kilometers, with water making up the additional 10,042 square kilometers. The state is shaped somewhat like a heart. As a result, Ohio leaders often use the phrase "The Heart of It All" to tout its business, educational, and recreational opportunities. The highest point in the state is Campbell Hill near Bellefontaine. It rises 1,549 feet above sea level. The lowest point in the state is at the Ohio River near Cincinnati, 455 feet above sea level. Within its boundaries, Ohio enjoys some of the most fertile soil in the United States. Much of that soil was deposited by a series of glaciers that advanced into the area thousands of years ago. The most recent of these left the region about thirteen thousand years ago. The glaciers also had a major impact on the topography of Ohio, smoothing and flattening the central and western areas of the state. Eastern Ohio, which was untouched by the glaciers, features more rugged terrain marking the foothills of the Appalachian Mountains. Another important geographical feature in early Ohio was the Black Swamp located in the northwestern part of the state. It originally consisted of dense forests, and for much of the year, the land was flooded. During the mid-nineteenth century, Ohioans drained the swamp. This area now consists of some of the most fertile agricultural land in the entire United States. During prehistoric times, American Indians from several major traditions occupied the area. The Paleo-Indian people were hunters and gatherers who entered the region about 13,000 B.C. People of the archaic tradition were also hunters and gatherers who lived in the region from about 8000 B.C. until 500 B.C. The Woodland tradition, which lasted from about 800 B.C. to A.D. 1200 introduced pottery, cultivated plants, settled village life, and mound building to the region. Many of the mounds and earthworks created by various cultures of the Woodland tradition are now preserved as prehistoric treasures within the state. Perhaps the most famous of these is Serpent Mound in Adams County. Just a mile and a half from here stands Miamisburg Mound it is one of the two largest conical mounds in eastern North America. It is a burial mound built by the people that archaeologists have called the Adana culture (800 B.C. to 100 A.D.). Miamisburg Mound is listed on the National Register of Historical Places. It is 65 feet tall, 800 feet in circumference, and contains 54,000 cubic yards of dirt, which corresponds to the contents of more than 3,400 dumptrucks.The last prehistoric people to occupy the region were members of the Late Prehistoric tradition. These people, who lived in large villages surrounded by farms, lived in the area from about A.D. 1000 to 1650. French explorers in search of furs first came to the area now known as Ohio in the 1660s. They found a richly forested area with abundant water and mineral resources and a generally pleasant climate. Those same features later attracted English settlers from the colonies on the Atlantic seaboard who were more interested in farming and settling than fur trading. At the same time that the region was attracting the interest of Europeans, it was in the process of being re-settled by historic Indian tribes including the Chippewa, Delaware, Eel River, Iroquois, Kaskaskia, Miami, Mingo, Munsee, Ottawa, Piankashaw, Potawatomi, Sauk, Seneca, Shawnee, Wea, and Wyandot. The English colonists eventually established their dominance in the area with victories in the French and Indian War and the Ohio Indian Wars. Throughout the 19th and 20th centuries Ohioans reshaped the state's landscape with networks of canals, railroads, and highways. During the same period, Ohio's population swelled and the state developed into a dominant economic and political force nationally.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
I picked this location near Dayton because it's Historical significance in OHIO. Ohio - where the phrase "Birthplace of Aviation" is etched on license plates - was where flight was born, because the Wright brothers made their plans and constructed their aircraft in their bicycle shop on Dayton's West Side. Developing and flying their aircraft took place at Huffman Field, which is now Wright Patterson AFB. Orville was born in Dayton and Wilbur was born nearby in Indiana. Both lived and died in the Dayton area. Ohio is also the state that has produced the most astronauts, 24 in all, including John Glenn and Neil Armstrong. Just on the Eastern border of Dayton lies the National Muesum of the US Air Force. You could spend a day there and not see it all.
&lt;p&gt;There are plenty of great geocaches in the area to do. Dayton Ohio is a Geocachers Dream. We are loaded with every kind of Geocache imaginable. Ammo cans to evil micros!! So if you geocache for numbers or for the scenery you'll love this area. Dayton is just minutes away and has Fifth Third Field, home of the Dayton Dragons, Which currently has the longest running string of sold out games in the history of professional sports, and should exceed 11 years this summer. There is so much to do around here that I can't possibly name it all .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Dead tree. Don't forget to get the code. Look for the geo trail.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364885038"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3301211">Scouter74</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We have had this on our radar for awhile. After getting the Cache Across America Kansas and Missouri last week we had to stop and get this one this week. We just spent the weekend in Lima visiting family for a graduation. We are now heading home to Illinois. Thanks for being a part of this Geocaching series. I dropped a Trackable and swapped Pathtags. Cache Across America was also on a panel of the new GPS Adventures Exhibit at GeoWoodstock. 

I hope everyone has an amazing adventure geocaching.

Follow my Geocaching Adventures at [Scouter74.com](https://www.scouter74.com)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364884820"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="28260953">CAREA97</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Scouter74 and I came to my home state of Ohio to attend my great-nephews high school graduation and to visit family. We decided to go about a hour off our route home to get this cache. I picked up a TB and also dropped a TB. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364444211"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3797805">mrahudson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Took a terrible route in and a less terrible route out but we managed to make the find.  TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364443482"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3791981">mrsahudson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Didn't exactly find a geotrail in, but we found our way in and got ink on the log. Thanks!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363711065"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T09:46:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42375063">GeoKelterFam</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it! Here we find ourselves back in Ohio . Hoped for a regular but got a small. 🤷‍♂️ Still has a good amount of trackables and swag 😀 took a TB to move along Thanks for bringing us here. Heading back from our GeoWoodstock XXII adventure. Grabbing some caches along the way. TFTC 1,3

Cache Across America #8</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.0527166666667" lon="-84.4066333333333"><time>2009-01-06T00:00:00</time><name>GC1KHE3</name><desc>Cache Across America - Michigan by Team Rod &amp; Tod w/KAboom adopted by allenite</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1KHE3</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Michigan</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1095204" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Michigan</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Team Rod &amp; Tod w/KAboom adopted by allenite</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1641852">allenite</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="0">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Michigan</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Michigan&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/aa68ac1f-0677-4c5c-931b-c0de92868076_l.gif" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Lansing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Detroit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 11th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 8th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 26th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="https://coord.info/BM21GBP"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Welcome to this great Team Rod &amp;amp; Tod cache. This peaceful park, nestled in the middle of Somerset Center, has many great features...the bridges, made of cement, look like wooden bridges, there are fish in the eastern cement pool. The two cement "trees" are chimneys for the building in the hillside. Rumor has it that this area was once used by Al Capone while on his travels between Chicago &amp;amp; Detroit! Also, this park was recently listed as one of the most haunted parks in America...keep an eye out for the previous inhabitants!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bring a picnic and the family, there are grills available on site, as well as a nice covered picnic area, a playground, disc golf course, tennis courts, and a baseball diamond. There are several other caches on grounds as well....happy hunting!!&lt;/p&gt;
I talked with the owners of this park a few times and am glad to see many improvements being made, a new drive, walkways and restorations of the buildings in the hillside are among the projects planned! The new and some restored bridges fit right in with the old and beautiful ones still in place, and I hear there might even be a bit of restoration in the planning for the MASSIVE bird hotel (it can't be considered a house, just way too big!
&lt;p&gt;Just to the southwest of this area is the beautiful Somerset State Game Area...a 600+ acre rustic park mainly used for hunting, has the scenic Lake Lombard in the center. There is a great scenic trail which circles the large lake...this 4 mile trail takes you through many great geological features, the lakes have some great fishing...not easily accessible by boat though...sorry! MIS, Stagecoach Stop, Walter J. Hayes State Park, Hidden Lake Gardens, and Mystery Hill are just a few other attractions located in and around the beautiful Irish Hills to the east. Even U.S. 12 is historic...this road was once a main east-west stagecoach route, as well as the main smuggling route for some notorious gangster like Capone. Many nearby caches also await you!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come enjoy this great area, spend some time in the beautiful state of Michigan...we are glad you came!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=3593b94e-1851-4fb1-ac91-8cd7a3732788" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/stats/img.aspx?txt=The+Cachestalkers&amp;amp;uid=3593b94e-1851-4fb1-ac91-8cd7a3732788&amp;amp;bg=2" border="0" title="Profile for Rockin Roddy" alt="Profile for Rockin Roddy" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>UPS near fence post</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364437794"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T15:11:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="33370833">MeekMoose</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cool cache! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364092817"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16271950">grandmabonnie44</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great to get another of the CAA checked off the list. Great park here</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364092713"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="468159">cjhanson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On a road trip from Wisconsin with GrandmaBonnie44. This was one of the most important caches on our list. Totally enjoyed the McCourtie Park concrete sculptures. Found the cache, signed the log and made note of the code. This is find #49 for me in the Cache Across America series. Hoping to finish in August when we travel to Alaska. Thanks for helping keep this series going.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363327732"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T17:15:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19483995">Aegir101</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aegir101 and beJs are on a 5 day trip from Maryland💪🦀 to MI, IN, KY and OH to complete their second Jasmer loop. Today was day 5 the drive from OH to MI. It was an overcast day but we had fun. We started at an event in Dayton and headed to Columbus then Toledo and Detroit. We stopped along the way to look for old caches, webcams, challenges, and counties, as well as all cache types to stay well rounded. Thanks to all these COs for placing and maintaining these caches.
     Hooray! This was one of our targets Wednesday but Delta rescheduled our flight and we had to cut it. This was a really nice park and a pretty easy find, coords and hint good. My 22nd CAA, 28 to go!! AIO, TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363333542"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2938303">bejs</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aegir101 and bejs from the D.C. area have teamed up for a five day caching tear through Michigan, Indiana, Kentucky, and Ohio, getting the oldests, CAAs, cache types, and finishing our second Jasmer loops.  We are on our last day, mainly in Ohio and wrapping up back in Michigan.

This cache was our last of our major targets for the trip.  A fairly quick find.   Thanks for the fun hide, beJs

---
Find # 4566
As found: Traditional Cache 1.5/1.5 Regular</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="36.707117" lon="-81.96715"><time>2013-09-19T00:00:00</time><name>GC4NMVK</name><desc>Cache Across America Virginia  by RubyRedCachers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4NMVK</url><urlname>Cache Across America Virginia </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3928620" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America Virginia </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>RubyRedCachers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2681402">RubyRedCachers</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Virginia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Virginia&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Flag_of_Virginia.svg/670px-Flag_of_Virginia.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Richmond&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Virginia Beach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 35th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 12th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 10th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;This cache is located just outside of Abingdon, VA. I felt that Abingdon was a great location to place the cache. It is not far from Interstate-81, only about 8-10 min away. The cache is located at an opening to the Creeper Trail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After exiting from I-81 Exit 17, take a right at the bottom of the ramp. Continue on Cummings St for about a 1/4 mile, take a right onto Greenspring Rd. Continue for about half a mile until you find the train. Parking is across the street.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Abingdon is a town in Washington County, Virginia, 189 miles (304 km) west by south of Lynchburg. In 1910, 1,757 people lived here. The population was 7,780 at the 2000 census. It is the county seat of Washington County. The town is included in the Tri-Cities Metro area of Johnson City-Kingsport-Bristol, TN-VA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The land that the city of Abingdon is situated on was originally surveyed between the years 1748 and 1750 by Dr. Thomas Walker and was part of the Great Road that Colonel William Byrd III ordered cut through the wilderness on to Kingsport, Tennessee. In 1760, famed frontiersman, Daniel Boone, named the area Wolf Hills, after his dogs were attacked by a pack of wolves during a hunting expedition. The original location of the attack is located on 'Courthouse Hill' and is also the location of The Cavehouse Craft Shop. During Lord Dunmore's War, Black's Fort was established in 1774 by Joseph Black to protect local settlers in the region from Indian attacks. In 1776 the community of Black's Fort was made the county seat of the newly formed Washington county. In 1778, Black's Fort was incorporated as the town of Abingdon, said to be named for the ancestral home of Martha Washington. Martha Washington College, a school for women, operated in Abingdon from 1860 to 1932 in a former private residence; since 1935 the building has been occupied by a hotel, the Martha Washington Inn. The Barter Theatre, the state theatre of Virginia, was opened in Abingdon in 1933. Virginia Governors Wyndham Robertson, David Campbell, and John B. Floyd lived here. Abingdon is also the final stop along the Virginia Creeper Trail, which allows pedestrian, cyclist and equestrian traffic. The Washington County Historical Society is located in Abingdon and serves as a regional genealogy center, in addition as a repository for Washington County history. .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of you group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Walk into the field. Center stage right. Take a seat in my shade and enjoy the view.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1090990653"><groundspeak:date>2022-04-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7248922">Gnomey Yo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found long ago with Dan The Man an Luckycharm tftc yo</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1066882258"><groundspeak:date>2021-12-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">While we are always sad to see any Cache Across America cache go away, sadly sometimes it is necessary as the years go by.  The good news is that as of today we have a brand new CAA Virginia: GC9HTFF!! CAA players please update your PQ’s, etc. We will be updating the master lists immediately. Cache on! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1066785027"><groundspeak:date>2021-12-11T22:40:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29522102">CardinalReviewer</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">There has been no response from the CO.  Without recent communication on future cache availability, we can not hold this area for you any longer and so this cache is being archived. Please pick up any remaining cache bits as soon as possible.

Thank you for your understanding,
CardinalReviewer
Volunteer Geocaching.com Reviewer
[Known Virginia Geocaching Guidelines](https://wiki.groundspeak.com/display/GEO/Virginia)
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1066133120"><groundspeak:date>2021-12-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="282126">Cornflakes</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We will be attempting this cache on December 23rd. It's a long trip for us so we are hoping it is still in place and ready for visitors! If there is anything we can do to help you fix it up, please, please let us know.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1062901484"><groundspeak:date>2021-11-11T20:19:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29522102">CardinalReviewer</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Any word on when this cache will be available again?

Please post an update to the cache page as a service to your fellow geocachers.  If you have a specific date that it will be available again, please add the date and the reason(s).

Reviewers will post a note asking for an update after 30 days of no communication, so please keep the status of the replacement up to date.

Thanks,
CardinalReviewer
Volunteer Geocaching.com Reviewer
[Known Virginia Geocaching Guidelines](https://wiki.groundspeak.com/display/GEO/Virginia)
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.6937" lon="-115.671283"><time>2013-10-22T00:00:00</time><name>GC4QRVD</name><desc>Cache Across America - Idaho by tentha</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4QRVD</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Idaho</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3992040" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Idaho</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>tentha</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1172622">tentha</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Idaho</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Idaho&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://idaho.gov/"&gt;&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_Idaho.svg/668px-Flag_of_Idaho.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Boise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Boise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 14th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 39th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 43rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; The Bruneau Canyon overlook is the one accessible (by family car) overlook from which to view this canyon. Bighorn sheep and antelope can be seen in the area. The Bruneau River is a 153 mile long tributary of the Snake River, in the U.S. states of Idaho and Nevada. It runs through a narrow canyon cut into ancient lava flows. The Bruneau Canyon, which is up to 1,200 feet deep and 40 miles long, features rapids and hot springs, making it a popular whitewater trip. There are markers in the form of 3 caches each named "Cache Across America - The Way To": GC4TYQ8, GC4TYQ6, and GC4QVNA, Use these to guide you to the goal as there is precious little to no phone communication for much of the journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of you group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Rocks</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364426652"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:23:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9054399">meganator216</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for the cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363618064"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T15:30:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9366409">rickdorsey8080</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I loved my time at Bruneau Canyon and had the place to myself most of Memorial Day Monday. I ventured through the gate to get to the gz and find the ammo can in the rock pile about 100 feet from the trail. While the trip to get to the canyon was bumpy I'm happy to report my 32nd find and second in two days. Love these adventures. Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359815817"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T14:05:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8614773">Zargonians</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We don't always go for Cache Across America caches unless we are near one.  Someone told us to go to Bruneau Overlook and we saw the CAA cache here so made the short trek over to sign the log.  Thanks for placing and keeping this CAA alive!  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360788949"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25527694">nikkitty123</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This cache was way out here but I'm so glad i made the drive. This is my 3rd in the series I think. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356498586"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-21T15:13:57</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3054235">vmgreg</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Visiting friends in Nampa and out exploring the area.  A bit of a bumpy ride the last few miles, but the incredible view made it worth it! This one gets another favorite vote from us. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="37.005083" lon="-86.3759"><time>2013-11-25T00:00:00</time><name>GC4QDD5</name><desc>Cache Across America - Kentucky by 6Lindseys</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC4QDD5</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Kentucky</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="3981058" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Kentucky</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>6Lindseys</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2167870">6Lindseys</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Kentucky</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Please replace the cache exactly where you found it. Container is an ammo box, chained in place.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;table width="77%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="4"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Kentucky&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Flag_of_Kentucky.svg/428px-Flag_of_Kentucky.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Frankfort&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Louisville&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 37th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 25th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 15th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; If you are attempting to complete the entire &lt;i&gt;Cache Across America&lt;/i&gt; series, you are sure to put some miles on your vehicle. I am sure only a few of us are lucky enough to be able to drive the same kind of cache-car that is honored here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/199df53a-f02d-4551-8ae4-919a40cd1de4.jpg" align="left" border="1" hspace="5" /&gt;What a better to place to stop on a series dedicated to America than a museum dedicated to the American Sports Car!! You will definitely want to cruise in to get this cache which is located at the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.corvettemuseum.com"&gt;National Corvette Museum&lt;/a&gt; in Bowling Green. If at all possible, you will want to make time to visit inside the museum as well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;Since 1953 the Corvette has been America's Sports Car. The National Corvette Museum was established as a 501(c)3 not-for-profit foundation with a mission of celebrating the invention of the Corvette and preserving its past, present and future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;The 68,000 sq. ft. building houses more than 50 Corvette models and one-of-a-kind concept cars spanning the history of Corvette. Also on hand are thousands of Corvette related photos, movies and videos, advertisements, scale models and rare memorabilia. Spotlighted are the people who have made Corvette an American icon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/c7e14737-9c0a-4aa8-877b-05d43324c17d.jpg" align="right" border="0" /&gt;Inside, striking full-scale dioramas show classic Corvette models and famous performance Corvette models in period settings. You'll also find the historic one-millionth Corvette, donated to the museum by Chevrolet. You may also want to visit the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.bowlinggreenassemblyplant.com"&gt;Bowling Green Assemby Plant&lt;/a&gt;, where the Corvette and Cadillac XLR are made.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;This cache is a hidden ammo can that was placed with permission from the Events Manager at the Corvette Museum. It is conveniently located right off I-65 and is in an ideal location for travel bugs. The posted hours of the Museum and this cache are 8am-5pm 7 days a week excluding major holidays. Be sure to bring your lunch – there are picnic tables nearby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1216319095"><groundspeak:date>2024-02-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great news CAA watchers and players!

Thanks to the quick work of the reviewer GreenMinds and cachers Ground Fox stepping up to represent, we now have a brand new CAA Kentucky! Ground Fox has appropriately chosen horses, blue grass and bourbon in the Lexington area and the new cache can be found here: 

[GCAKHHN](https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAKHHN?luid=f37c924f-e2d9-425b-ae53-5994f9aa24cb)

Many thanks to 6Lindseys for being a great CAA owner for many years. We appreciate you and all you did for Kentucky. 

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1215617238"><groundspeak:date>2024-02-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Good afternoon CAA players and watchers! Unfortunately we have not been able to make contact with the CO of this cache. They were a great owner for several years and we are grateful for their commitment to the Cache Across America series of caches. Without individual state owners the CAA series would not exist.

The Corvette museum no longer wants this cache at the museum location which is disappointing, but we understand their decision. But are happy to have had so many years at a location popular with cachers. The good news is that we are happy to report that a new CAA Kentucky is in the works and are working towards getting it published asap! It will be in the Lexington area with more information to come soon.

Thank you for your patience!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1213449117"><groundspeak:date>2024-01-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="748746">lorriebird</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hi Cache Across America players and watchers. Just wanted to let you know we are aware of the recent archival of this CAA KY cache. We are working on it and hope to have an update soon!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1213408831"><groundspeak:date>2024-01-24T08:48:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="20521609">GreenMinds</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Greetings,

This cache has been temporarily disabled for some time now without any action taken on your part to address the issues with the cache. The cache is being archived at this time, so please return to this location and remove what is left of your cache.

Sincerely,

GreenMinds
Geocaching.com Volunteer Reviewer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1211089036"><groundspeak:date>2023-12-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7993914">MolsonBlue2001</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Made the slight detour for this one to make sure I got the code. I don't know if I ever will finish, but I now have one more complete.

This cache is in amazing shape. It really just needs to be updated to note not being available at all hours. I looked around for the fanny pack noted back in November but did not spot anything when I was here.

SL. TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.272367" lon="-124.1097"><time>2014-05-03T00:00:00</time><name>GC541PB</name><desc>Cache Across America - Oregon by Team GreenWoodTurner</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC541PB</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Oregon</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4327303" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Oregon</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Team GreenWoodTurner</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="877199">greenwoodturner</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Oregon</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Oregon&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b9/Flag_of_Oregon.svg" width="187 height=" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Salem&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Portland&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 9th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 28th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 33rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;The &lt;i&gt;Oregon Coast Trail&lt;/i&gt; is a long distance hiking route along the Pacific coast of Oregon. It follows the coast of Oregon from the mouth of the Columbia River to the California border. It's an easy-to-moderate hike, of approximately 425 miles. If you were to hike the whole trail, you would hike on the beach, on paved roads, on dirt roads and on trail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Oregon Coast is known for its spectacular beauty, and the placement of this cache will provide you with the opportunity to hike a portion of the &lt;i&gt;Oregon Coast Trail&lt;/i&gt; while at the same time enjoying the view of the Oregon coastline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is ample parking across the highway, at the indicated parking coordinates. You will need to then carefully cross the highway, to begin your 0.75 mile roundtrip hike to the cache. After crossing the highway, walk past the gate and continue along the old road. You will cross a bridge, and when you reach the fork in the trail, you will need to bear to the left. The tree cover is pretty intense along the trail, so as you begin to approach GZ, look uphill for two trees, as shown in the picture below. Behind the trees is a downed tree, in the shape of a "Y"; the cache is hidden under the "Y", about 20 feet uphill from the trail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="http://imgcdn.geocaching.com/cache/30360289-36e7-41ad-9311-435ae163ac4c.jpg?rnd=0.8683661" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although you may be temped to park and then bushwhack straight up to the cache, &lt;u&gt;please do not do this!&lt;/u&gt; It is dangerous and it will damage the plants on the hillside.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is the view from GZ:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="http://imgcdn.geocaching.com/cache/783ea22f-f49e-4adf-bc0a-aa9b4317eb16.jpg?rnd=0.4342419" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be sure to get the numbers off the lid and take a picture if you are going for all 50 states and the grand cache at the end. For all others, just log this as a regular cache. TBs and trade items welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363250655"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T10:29:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9366409">rickdorsey8080</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">One of my two target caches during my Oregon caching adventure this weekend. Drive in from Corvallis on Sunday morning to get to the coast and drive south down the 101. Parked in the surfers lot and made the shirt hike to the gz. This is my 31 st CAA and I'm happy to listen to the crashing waves as I signed the log. FPadded, Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363043853"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5889280">Checkers042</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">2 for 2 on this weekend's coastal CAA trip. Snagged Washington this morning, and now this one at the end of the day. #35 total for me, though I'm not sure which states are up next now. Loved the hike in, and spent some time at the beach afterwards. All in good shape here, tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359467533"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1646022">simmsquest</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On an Oregon Coast birthday trip with my daughter. I try to get CAA caches when i nearby. I hope to be blessed with the opportunites to continue finding these. This is my 23rd. CAA Loved being able to say I walked part of the Oregon trail . Waves crashing , towering trees and a peaceful hike . 
Just beautiful . thanks for maintaining. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354668353"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-11T18:13:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="91451">40</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Since we were driving down the coast, I knew this had to be a stop!  Really enjoyed the hike in and the cache! Gathered the needed info and took a selfie in case I finish the entire series and
Want to get the final. Thanks for the fun today! -40-</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355604859"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="184885">Critters of adventure</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We had seen this cache series previously, but we were never sure that we would get any of them. We are pretty sure we will never gather them all.But it was nice to get one of them. This is a really nice trail. TNLN SL TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.61205" lon="-88.19935"><time>2014-05-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC55ZDZ</name><desc>Cache Across America - Mississippi by spaceteacher</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC55ZDZ</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Mississippi</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="4384703" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Mississippi</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>spaceteacher</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="471409">spaceteacher</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Mississippi</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;Cache Across America - Mississippi (2nd edition)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mississippi's newest contribution to the Cache Across America series&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Mississippi&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/42/Flag_of_Mississippi.svg/500px-Flag_of_Mississippi.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Jackson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Jackson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 32nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 31st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 20th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; The famous Natchez Trace Parkway is a three-state scenic and historic pleasure drive of 444 miles from Natchez, Mississippi through northwest Alabama and ending near Nashville, Tennessee. The Natchez Trace was the premier highway of the early 1800s. It is part of the National Park System and as such, physical caches are not allowed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache is in Tishomingo State Park. Located in the foothills of the Appalachian Mountains, Tishomingo State Park is steeped in history and scenic beauty. Archaeological excavations confirm the presence of Paleo Indians in the area now encompassed by the park as early as 7000 B.C.; the park takes its name from the leader of the Chickasaw nation, Chief Tishomingo. The Natchez Trace runs directly through the park. Today's visitors to Tishomingo State Park discover the same timeless natural beauty that enchanted the Indians centuries ago. Tishomingo offers a unique landscape of massive rock formations and fern-filled crevices found nowhere else in Mississippi. Massive boulders blanketed in moss dot the hillsides, and colorful wildflowers border trails once walked by Native Americans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The staff at Tishomingo State Park was wonderful and very helpful. If you need assistance with this cache please let them know. Be sure to go in and tell them you are geocaching-they are glad to have you. The Mississippi Department of Wildlife, Fisheries and Parks website is &lt;a href="http://www.mdwfp.com/"&gt;www.mdwfp.com&lt;/a&gt; Entrance fee is $3 per car up to six people. Parking coordinates are provided. There are many other caches in the park-check the bookmarked list I posted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache is off the red flagged trail near the office. It is about .25 mile round trip from closest parking near the office. The rocks are steep in places and the footbridge does not have a railing. You might consider walking with a hiking stick and watch your children around the drop-offs. If you could see this cache, you could probably almost reach it and not leave the trail. It is a clear Tupperware-type container with a white top, labeled as a geocache. The code is on the underside of the lid and in the log book in two places.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Hint – The trail is marked with red flagging tape and/or blazes.  There are three of these trees together very close to the cache.Then trail makes a switchback, first right then left.  The cache is under the flat rock between the change in direction.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363340826"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T18:01:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4839017">JenOvations</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What do you get when you put two determined cachers on the open road with a mountain of snacks, a GPS, and a shared addiction to smileys? A legendary cross-country caching marathon! itwasmymouse and I packed the car in Ohio and have set off on a massive multi-state loop that we won't soon forget.

Our route will be taking us on an incredible journey through Indiana, Illinois, Missouri, Kansas, Nebraska, Oklahoma, Arkansas, Mississippi, Alabama, Georgia, Tennessee, and Kentucky. We will be checking off an unbelievable list of achievements along the way. We'll be adding a slew of new counties, wrangling up some historic caches placed in the early days, adding to our Odyssey count, and snagging high favorite point targets, virtuals, and unique challenge qualifiers.

From muddy trails and guardrail P&amp;Gs to breathtaking scenic views and clever gadgets, every stop will add a new story to our journey. We will laugh, get turned around a few times, fuel up on caffeine, and make memories to last a lifetime, all culminating in the amazing chaos of GeoWoodstock! TFTC and for being a part of our unforgettable mega-road trip! Log signed or stamped. Amazing walk to GZ! Fav pt</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363689772"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8218630">itwasmymouse</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache Across America!!!!

Woohooo!!! 

* - We're not in Ohio anymore! - -
Geowoodstock 2026 Adventure! 

Geocaching from Sylvania, Ohio. Caching and spending time with JenOvations, we used our joint stamp on most logs. We have the MOST fun together. 

This caching trip was one for the statistics book! Totally blessed to share these memories with this beautiful and wonderful woman. 

Trip details: 
- 5 days - 3,365 miles 
- 12 states (2 new geo states, OK, AR) 
- LOTS of new counties 
- 7 state capitals
- 450+ physical caches
- 125+ Larges (116 in a day)
- Lab arts (MO, GWXXII, KS. OK, AL)
- Lots of oldies: 2, 3 &amp; 4 digit GC's
- Oldest letterbox in USA/world
- 3 State's Oldest's: NE, OK, TN
- 6 Cache Across America Caches:
IL, NE, KS, OK, AR, MS
- 5 Geotour Cache Odyssey Caches:
MO, KS, NE, OK, AR
- 6 new event states
- 1 awesome drone show
- 1 MEGA &amp; 1 MAZE 

Cheapest Gas - $3.78 Decatur, AL
Expensive gas - $4.99 Wilmington, IL 

Thanks for adding to our Geowoodstock 2026 adventure and helping me with various goals, TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358098096"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T13:02:56</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4439717">TeamElysians</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358098022"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T13:02:29</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4439717">TeamElysians</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358094433"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-30T12:39:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4439717">TeamElysians</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Finally found it the service is sketchy so pulling up the hint was tricky. Definitely get that before going down the trail. Container is not in good condition at all. Wear your hiking shoes!!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.580883" lon="-75.06425"><time>2014-08-20T00:00:00</time><name>GC59ZYA</name><desc>Cache Across America - Delaware by flyingmoose</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC59ZYA</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Delaware</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Letterbox Hybrid</type><groundspeak:cache id="4504343" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Delaware</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>flyingmoose</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="329132">flyingmoose</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Letterbox Hybrid</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="36" inc="0">Snowmobiles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Delaware</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;This is a letterbox, please do not remove the stamp/s or inkpad provided. Depending on how long the cache lives I will add a new stamp every so often to make it interesting.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Delaware&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/user/52e07ece-de0f-4cfb-a9ec-79f2c613c790.jpg" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Dover&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Wilmington&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 49th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 45th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 1st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Water, water everywhere describes Delaware Seashore State Park. Bounded on the east by the mighty Atlantic Ocean, and on the west by Rehoboth Bay and Indian River Bay, the 2825-acre park is a beach-goer's delight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Throughout history, the forces of wind and water have kept this barrier island largely inaccessible, due to the frequent natural changes of the inlet channel between the bays and the sea. Transportation along this narrow stretch of land was difficult until the Federal government completed construction of two large steel and stone jetties in 1939, stabilizing the Indian River Inlet. The State Park Commission (now the Division of Parks and Recreation) began operating Delaware Seashore State Park in 1965. Today, the park is a major attraction for millions of visitors who enjoy the large variety of water-related activities available along Delaware's coast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a little known area but has gotten popular over the years. The parking for this cache (waypoint below) is a small spot but there is other parking to access the park. It is just off Route 1 near Bethany Beach. At the parking area, there is a kiosk with trail info which will show you the exact route to the point you are going to - pretty strait forward to be honest. The Letterbox is hidden at the base of a tree, not a super challenge. The point is like the original Delaware cache - you have to drive across Delaware to get to it. Lots of great sights and the walk to the cache is nice as well. Feel free to walk just a little further on the path to the beach and enjoy the view. Delaware Seashore State Park is open daily 8 a.m. to sunset. Normal park office hours are 8 a.m. to 4 p.m. Monday through Friday. From April through October, the park office is open seven days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="http://imgcdn.geocaching.com/cache/large/4caee11a-6d9a-48e8-b2a4-d6392a089a72.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner (make note of secret code on inner lid &amp;amp; notebook). There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;img src="http://imgcdn.geocaching.com/cache/large/18676b32-87b9-416b-b141-6797ff4d69e2.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Base of tree</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363028316"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25469328">Missbderycke</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Phone in Airplane Mode, Work Phone &amp; Laptop Shut Off, 5 days. 4 New States. 5 CAAs, 4 Cache Odysseys, 3000+ km driving, 25+km on foot, a lifetime of laughs &amp; memories = priceless.

Here is a short story long... in booking a hotel in November of 2025 I was asked to stay on the line and listen to an offer. While listening I was getting ready to head out on a hike with a friend so Im not going to lie I was paying zero attention. Afterward the lady was like does that sound good and I answered yes which prompted her to ask for my credit card number. Still not paying attention to what was going on and thinking I was paying for the November hotel I ended up with a 3 night 4 day stay to 11 different locations in the US for a really good deal. When I saw the email stating what I had just signed up for I called lindsayasdnil and said well I did this thing so pick from these 11 locations and we will go on a geotrip! She ended up deciding on Williamsburg, VA as it was one we could drive to and the closest-ish one. Now just to decide when we would go. We seem to like to road trip in May so we decided on doing that again and combine it with a milestone birthday for her. Since my goal is to visit all of the states and also complete this series while doing so we chatted about tacking on an extra day and visiting Delaware as neither of us had it as a state we were planning on visiting for a specific reason (but boy am I sure glad we did, more on this later). About a week before leaving I convinced her that we werent far from the New Jersey CAA either and we would be driving super close to the North Carolina border so we might as well pop down there for a hot minute and grab a cache as well.

We left Niagara Falls, ON yesterday at 7:45am and arrived at our hotel at 11:03pm and were pooped so we slept in this morning. Such a beautiful state. We both decided quite quickly after waking up this morning and driving around that people are sleeping on Delaware. No one talks about how beautiful it is here! We believe it's a hidden gem and we will be back again as soon as we can! This is CAA#10. I think so far this is in the top 3 of the ones I have found thus far. Took us a bit to figure out where to park and then it ended up being a longer than anticipated hike almost 5km round trip in the 30 degree weather. It's no surprise that we ended up with a sunburn from this one. I enjoyed how wide these trails were and it was nice to see so many people out and about. Adding a fav point. Tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360649269"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-12T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10935665">Buckeye</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">**CACHE ACROSS AMERICA #27**

This was the first big target of the day! I spent the night in Millsboro, and made the drive across the state to this hide (which sounds impressive until you realize I'm in the second smallest state in the Union). The parking area I had eyed up had a multitude of No Parking signs, so I had to find a legal parking area since there wasn't a parking waypoint on this cache. I eventually found one, and set off on a (longer than anticipated) hike. I can't hate too much though, as I really like the coastal pine trails! It reminds me of the walk back to CAA South Carolina.

After hoofing it back to GZ, I was surprised to not see an obvious geotrail to this one! I weaseled through the brush and soon spotted the hide. Score! Signed myself in, checked out the stamp, jotted down the code, snapped a few photos, and replaced as found before hiking back to the Toaster to continue my adventure through Delaware. Many thanks for the nice CAA hide!

I’m off on a trip to the DelMarVa peninsula for an overnight trip to tick off a few Geocaching goals! I’ll be picking up some state oldests, highpoints, Cache Across America hides, and blacking out the counties of the First and Old Line states. Thanks for adding to my adventure!

**Cache Across America - Delaware**
Find #17605

Thanks for the Letterbox Hybrid cache, flyingmoose!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359257144"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="36191060">thatasianpanda</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wow two caches accompanied by clothing items back to back? What are the odds?

Of course I forgot to take a photo with the cache again so I guess we will be back 🤦‍♀️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358843911"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2894293">pikespice</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Logging a TB</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358843232"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-03T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2894293">pikespice</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice walk to the cache. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="30.5131" lon="-97.569717"><time>2015-11-21T00:00:00</time><name>GC677MT</name><desc>Cache Across America - Texas by Bigguy  In  Texas</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC677MT</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Texas</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="5345915" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Texas</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Bigguy  In  Texas</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="601992">Bigguy  In  Texas</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="65" inc="1">Yard (private residence)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="0">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Texas</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Texas&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Flag_of_Texas.svg/800px-Flag_of_Texas.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Austin&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Houston&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 2nd behind Alaska&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 2nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 28th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is located in Hutto Lake Park just off of Highway 130 near the Gatis School exit. The area is only about 20 miles from Austin (the capital of Texas) and in a cache rich area. Come for the CAA-Tx cache and stay for all the other central Texas caching fun! The cache is large enough for plenty of swag and medium to large travelers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
NOTE - 6/21 This is best approached from the parking coordinates listed in Hutto Lake Park. If the parking lot is closed, you can park on the street and walk in. It is in a private yard (in the BACKyard - not the front!). You should be able to retrieve it from outside the fence, but please find this one in daylight hours so that the surrounding neighbors do not kick you or me out of the subdivision! Also, no need to LS if you TS as I need to get rid of the extra swag that I have accumulated over the years. Good hunting! UPDATE - PARKING COORDINATES ADDED N 30 30.695 W 97 34.155
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>You have permission to get this cache from outside the fence</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364619600"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T09:36:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="51948737">cadeklubnikfan13</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364995900"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6265985">Fur007</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day #5 of 5 days in Austin with Jersey Girl 10 to visit with her son &amp; girlfriend. With just a few hours to go before Jersey Girl 10 &amp; I must leave to fly back to Rochester, NY, we targeted caches in Round Rock and Hutto. We were psyched to be close enough to this special cache. This is our first 'Cache Across America" find and had no issues making it to GZ to add our names to the log. TFTC!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362031733"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T14:42:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="637986">Wollaston</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Happy to be able to grab another targeted cache for the day. 🙂 Day 8 visiting from Downunder 🇦🇺, and currently outnabout on a little hunting adventure whilst on route to GeoWoodstock XXII. Primarily hunting for oldies, and the “Cache Across America” and “Cache Odyssey” series’s. It’s always a great day for caching. 😎
TFTC Bigguy  In  Texas</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360320336"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T14:43:07</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52640026">UrbanBlacksmith</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC! Located with justgeocachingalong ❤️ as we make our way to Colorado! Everything was great here and it’s such a beautiful park. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360330919"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10356987">JustGeocachingAlong</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hellooooo from Annapolis, MD!! We started this journey 20 days ago and have been having an absolute blast! We started county cached at the VA/NC state line to Cape Canaveral, FL, then from FL all the way to Galveston. But wow… Texas has a looooooot of counties, so we decided to wave the white flag on that mission for now. 😂 Instead, we shifted gears and decided to grab the TX CAA and the oldest cache in TX, letting those lead this part of the adventure. And so… here we are!

We left Galveston this morning, stopped here, and are now heading toward the oldest cache before making our way up to Colorado to watch our daughter graduate from Colorado State University, then it’s off to GeoWoodstock!

This is such a beautiful park… peaceful, relaxing, and just a wonderful place to spend some time. I’m sure you love having this right in your backyard. UrbanBlacksmith also really enjoyed chatting with the frenchies next door. 😊

We signed the log and snapped a photo. I also dropped off a travel bug that “loves all things big,” so bringing it down here to Texas, where everything is bigger, felt completely appropriate! 😂

TFTCAAC!!!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.2416" lon="-85.81765"><time>2016-05-09T00:00:00</time><name>GC6HCCW</name><desc>Cache Across America - Indiana by Kosciusko County Visitors Center</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC6HCCW</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Indiana</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="5648384" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Indiana</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Kosciusko County Visitors Center</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="453288">go-purdue</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Indiana</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Indiana&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ac/Flag_of_Indiana.svg/744px-Flag_of_Indiana.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Indianapolis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Indianapolis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 38th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 15th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 19th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;This cache is located at the Kosciusko County Visitors Center and, according to geocachers who have already visited, is in one of the coolest geocache containers ever! While you are caching, take a few minutes to stop in the Visitor Center and check out information on the area and on the entire state of Indiana. The Visitor Center is a great resource for visitors to Indiana. Whether it is your first visit or you have been to Indiana countless times, there are always new things to learn about in our great state.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kosciusko County is such a beautiful area. It is a mostly rural county with only one community large enough to be classified a city. Fields of corn and soybeans greet the visitor from just about every angle. But don't be fooled ... there's way more than corn in Indiana (and in Kosciusko County!).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kosciusko County is home to over 100 lakes including Indiana's largest nature lake, Lake Wawasee, and Indiana's deepest lake, Tippecanoe Lake.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kosciusko County is also home to the world headquarters of five large orthopedic manufacturers, earning it the title Orthopedic Capital of the World. Orthopedic implements made right here in Kosciusko County are sent around the world; Olympic Gymnast Mary Lou Retton and the late Pope John Paul II both received implements manufactured right here in Kosciusko County. Little Crow Foods, makers of CoCo Wheats cereal and Fryin Magic, started operations in 1903 in Kosciusko County and have been making their products here even since. Louis Dreyfus, in Claypool, is the world's largest bio-diesel fuel plant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So take some time to slow down in Kosciusko County. Our small town values and rural charm will bring you back again and again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache was formerly called the Travel Bug Visitors Center. It's still a great place to drop Travel Bugs!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364821137"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16271950">grandmabonnie44</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Slowly gathering CAA caches. Don't know if I will ever finish but will get any I come across in my travels. TFTC I</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364820907"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T10:00:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="468159">cjhanson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My second stop at this Indiana Cache Across America.
Traveling on a road trip with grandmaBonnie and she needed this one. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362632040"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2938303">bejs</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aegir101 and bejs from the D.C. area have teamed up for a five day caching tear through Michigan, Indiana, Kentucky, and Ohio, getting the oldests, CAAs, cache types, and finishing our second Jasmer loops.

After a great day yesterday on Power Island Michigan and south to Indiana, w toe are heading through Indiana towards Kentucky.  

A fun find - we were fooled at first, but Aegir101 cracked it.  Thanks for the fun hide, beJs

---
Find # 4502
As found: Traditional Cache 2.0/1.5 Other</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362636243"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T09:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19483995">Aegir101</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aegir101 and beJs are on a 5 day trip from Maryland💪🦀 to MI, IN, KY and OH to complete their second Jasmer loop. Today was day 3 the long leg down Indiana to Evansville from Elkhart. We stopped along the way to look for old caches, webcams, challenges, and counties, as well as all cache types to stay well rounded. It was a overcast blustery day but we had a great time. Thanks to all these COs for placing and maintaining these geocaches.
    This was one of our main targets for the trip as we are trying to get 4 CAAs and 4 oldest. Saw the “orthopedic capital” sign on the way into town and I was scratching my head but then this great cache page solved that mystery. We parked at the visitor center but no one was around this am. Found the cache after a few minutes searching. Code recorded. My 20th Cache Across America find, 30 to go! AIO, TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362142560"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T10:47:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42375063">GeoKelterFam</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it! On our way to GWXXII. Dropped a TB took a TB. Fun container. 🐦‍⬛ TFTC 1,3

CAA #2</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.149783" lon="-95.895133"><time>2016-09-24T00:00:00</time><name>GC6TB1E</name><desc>Cache Across America - Nebraska by LadyCache</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC6TB1E</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Nebraska</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Multi-cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="5885397" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Nebraska</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>LadyCache</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="568858">LadyCache</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Multi-cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Nebraska&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5a/Nebraska_state_flag.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Lincoln&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Omaha&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 16th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 38th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 37th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is not at the posted coords, but can be found a short distance away. This is a two-stage multi designed to give you a small taste of local history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the posted coords, you will find a monument of the burial site for a famous orator and man of peace. Using the information at this location, answer the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A = Fourth number of the year of birth&lt;br /&gt;
B = How many letters in who was from Offutt Air Force Base&lt;br /&gt;
C = Second number in year of birth&lt;br /&gt;
D = Fourth number of year of the second large funeral&lt;br /&gt;
E = How many letters in the Indian tribe name&lt;br /&gt;
F = Fourth number in the year of death&lt;br /&gt;
G = The month he and 14 others were reburied here&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The final can be found at N41 AB.CCD W095 ED.FBG&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a href="http://Nebraskache.com" target="newwindow"&gt;&lt;img src="http://nebraskache.com/files/images/logo1.jpg" border="0" style="width:210px;height:105px;" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Placed By A Nebraskache Member&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/107321656812/"&gt;&lt;img src="http://nebraskache.com/files/images/fb1.jpg" style="border:0px solid ;width:210px;height:64px;" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364755556"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T20:20:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="637986">Wollaston</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yahoo, managed to track this one down just before sunset which completed another awesome caching day. Day 21 visiting from Downunder 🇦🇺, outnabout on a little hunting adventure after another awesome GeoWoodstock. It’s always a great day for caching. 😎
TFTC LadyCache

If you’ve been to a GeoWoodstock you’re already checking out next years event. If not, check out GCBNWDV GeoWoodstock 2027 in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. May 29, 2027 and log a will attend to do your bit in achieving GIGA status. It’s a bucket list event that never disappoints.

Log my GW Ambassador trackable:  AM1889.   🙂</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364970359"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5200968">Lizrdh</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Based on Stage 1, we didn't expect the bushwhack for the final! Here on a 5-state air/road trip with BriGuy and we hesitated after parking for the final. Let's swap our footwear for hiking boots for one, and two, where do we enter? No great place so we just went for it. Lots of growth, thorns and a narrow path to follow. But of course, we did it! One more code number noted and the journey continues! Thanks for bringing us here! [:)]</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363631107"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="475801">FSA^2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We're coming back from Geowoodstock by way of Nebraska before flying home tomorrow.  We felt it was appropriate to visit a cemetery and this monument on Memorial Day.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363640440"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T19:28:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1754443">DirtBikeGranny</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">That was a bushwhack for sure.  I was expecting a better geotrail. 

Caching the day away. Enjoying my time. 

 Thanks for the cache and the smilie. This is my 53379 find. Thank you to LadyCache for maintaining and placing the cache. If there was an issue with the cache it would be stated in the first line of this log. Otherwise the cache called Cache Across America - Nebraska is in good shape. May 24, 2026Sunday

DirtBikeGranny
Caching since 2008
Sheridan Michigan
With Betty White and Black Betty
O|||||||O</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363346492"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="32140102">Holmer4Manistee</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">ROAD TRIP to GeoWoodstock with DirtBikeGranny. Goal is to spend over a week and connect continuous counties from where we left off from the Illinois GeoWoodstock to Missouri, Arkansas, Oklahoma, Kansas, Nebraska and Iowa.

Day 1: We went through massive rain and thunderstorms in Illinois, which impacted our trip with flash floods and road closures. But, we made it to our destination just after midnight in St Charles, MO.

Day 2: We continued on through Missouri and into Arkansas. Unfortunately, we had a few DNFs and some backtracking, but overall, the ones we did find were amazing. Great virtuals, earthcaches, and others made the day's drizzle not too gloomy.

Day 3: Running a little behind on our to-do list, we crammed Route 66 and Oklahoma in a half a day to make it to GeoWoodstock in time for the evening event and sign up for tomorrow's salt mine. The days focus was three large GeoArts. Unfortunately, Oklahoma's oldest had to be left for another time.

Day 4: Salt Mine Day. We had some time before our time slot to do some morning caching; so, we hit the challenge trail and finished it with 15 minutes to spare! The salt mine was awesome. Afterwards, we teamed up, with Racer28 and TSC, and focused on getting most of the Rocket GeoArt before the evening event. We signed those with 'DH'.

Day 5: Zoo and Cosmosphere! We began our day at the zoo. Afterwards, we finished the rocket, grabbed almost all the Barney Barnes caches, and racked up leaderboard points with another large batch of adventure labs. After a late lunch/early dinner of excellent Thai cuisine, we went to the Cosmosphere where we toured the space museum and watched three movies on their large wrap around screens (US National Parks, Space Junk, and Artemis). And, the highlight of the day, the 300 drone light show at Gowans Stadium! Having tons of fun!!!

Day 6: 19,000 MILESTONE - GeoWoodstock! After shopping at the vendors, we headed out toward Wichita. We visited Jurassic Art Park, the Keeper of the Plains and other amazing areas that had earth and virtual caches that were on our list. It was an enjoyable day of caching once again. Finally, we headed to the evening event before cashing in for the day.

Day 7: Saying goodbye to Kansas. We concluded the mega with a morning CITO, grabbing local caches before the afternoon event, and then caching our way north to Nebraska.

Thanks for placing and maintaining the caches. All caches found in good condition at the time of signing unless otherwise noted. All caches stamped or signed with CCC for our group the cherry capital cachers or signed with H4M for my initials or signed with my full caching name, 

Holmer4Manistee 

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.893567" lon="-72.073817"><time>2016-11-27T00:00:00</time><name>GC6XGVJ</name><desc>Cache Across America - New Hampshire by Max Jerome</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC6XGVJ</url><urlname>Cache Across America - New Hampshire</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="5980354" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - New Hampshire</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Max Jerome</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="145859">Max Jerome</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="0">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New Hampshire</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;New Hampshire&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Flag_of_New_Hampshire.svg/660px-Flag_of_New_Hampshire.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Concord&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Manchester&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 46th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 41st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 9th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1 align="center" class="style1"&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; New Hampshire once had a large industry surrounding the quarrying of granite, this gave it the nickname of "The Granite State." Granite stone walls, curbs, buildings, and even bridges can be found throughout the state. At one time, it appeared that almost every town had at least one quarry. Although most of the granite quarried was used locally, New Hampshire granite has journeyed to many places in the world to become part of monumental buildings, such as the Library of Congress, the Tomb of the Unknown Solider, the Brooklyn Bridge, The Pentagon, and many Civil War monuments.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
New Hampshire is home to many beautiful granite mountains. It is often said that New Hampshire's section of the Appalachian Trail is the "crown jewel" of the 2,000+ mile foot path, with rugged terrain and incredible views from the top. New Hampshire also hosts many other mountains, including Mount Monadnock, one of the most climbed mountains in the world.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This cache is a ammo canister located along the Pumpelly Trail, which goes to the summit of Mount Monadnock. From the trailhead, the walk to the cache is approximately 12 minutes. Total ascent is about 300 feet. The trail is rocky and has lots of tree roots on it, most of them being avoidable. The trail can be muddy during shoulder seasons. Children should be ok with this short hike, but pets are not allowed on the trail. If you have more time to kill, I suggest continuing onwards for a couple hours to reach the summit!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The trailhead is at N 42° 54.070 W 072° 04.495, which is about a half a mile down East Lake Road from its junction with Route 101. Park along the side of the road near the trailhead. Then, just go where your GPS tells you, following the obvious trail.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The cache is about 40-50 feet off trail, and should be pretty easy to find. The coordinates are within 22 feet of accuracy.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Enjoy!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1362376830"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T17:55:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42314978">DMizu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">6895. Found while visiting New Hampshire for a few days to work on the NH234 challenge. I somehow completely forgot to do the CAA the last time I was here so needed to rectify that this afternoon. Signed log and replaced as found. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360757727"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T15:22:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14566146">CheekyBrit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This series is absolutely nuts. I still cant quite forsee my completion of it, but what harm is there in dabbling a trifle with it along my way. Excellent trail, gorgeous views, stellar ammo can container, and overall an absolute banger of a geocache. Favorite point all the way.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359221171"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-04T14:54:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="53741305">sabrina7681</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354881924"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-12T13:37:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5431457">ziskind</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quick find on the way back down the Pumpelly trail. Tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1336446352"><groundspeak:date>2025-11-30T11:03:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30988181">Colorado_Marty</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">11 down, 39 to go. All in good shape on a cold snowy day.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.885067" lon="-71.52075"><time>2017-08-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC78QC5</name><desc>Cache Across America - Rhode Island by GeoGerry36</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC78QC5</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Rhode Island</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="6314335" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Rhode Island</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>GeoGerry36</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2236511">GeoGerry36</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="0">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Rhode Island</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This cache is a small camo'd Lock &amp;amp; Lock container. To get to the cache, take the Mercer Trail (BLUE) from the trailhead. When you get to the WWII Memorial Trail (YELLOW), follow it to the cache. Park at the Carlton's Way Trailhead at the end of the subdivision. If no space, park at the Mercer Outlook Parking area further up Mountaindale Road. Parking is NOT ALLOWED on the Carlton Trail ROADWAY. Please observe this request so we won't have to move the cache. THANK YOU.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Rhode Island&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Flag_of_Rhode_Island.svg/500px-Flag_of_Rhode_Island.svg.png" width="187 height=" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
