&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Providence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 50th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 43rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 13th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;This cache is placed in the Wolf Hill Forest Preserve in Smithfield, RI. It is a short hike on a rocky but open set of trails. Be sure to get the numbers from the front of the logbook and take a picture if you are going for all 50 states and the grand cache at the end. For all others, just log this as a regular cache. TBs and trade items welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Cache is under a rock near a pair of "V" trees.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360255690"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:13:56</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18168412">benfro2003</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC found with Turvobidaster. Logged as frofam.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360254657"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:10:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19998847">LindaWaWa</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC found with My Awesome Husband Joey and my Amazing son Benjamin and friend Marie and signed log while on a trip to see Jacob graduate UCONN </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360255909"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="18162746">jofro62</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with my family while on a trip from Newport News, VA. Slowly racking up the CAA caches. This was a nice one. All in good shape. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1356496149"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-21T22:50:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14566146">CheekyBrit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">That was a really good little hike. Loved it. And that view. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1341658126"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42314978">DMizu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">5978. Made a stop to grab another CAA cache while visiting Rhode Island this weekend to finish the RI 39 challenge. Photo attached. Signed log and replaced as found. TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.805133" lon="-89.103817"><time>2019-04-11T00:00:00</time><name>GC82Z45</name><desc>Cache Across America - Illinois by Wes_and_Tara &amp; Arndtwe</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC82Z45</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Illinois</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="7065589" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Illinois</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Wes_and_Tara &amp; Arndtwe</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2072065">Wes_and_Tara</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Illinois</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Illinois&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Flag_of_Illinois.svg/500px-Flag_of_Illinois.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Springfield&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Chicago&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 25th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 5th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 21st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache is located in Lincoln Trail Homestead State Park. The park is open daily from Dawn to Dusk. From November to April, the gate is closed to vehicles, but visitors are welcome to enter the park on foot. There is no fee to visit the park. Permission to place this cache was granted from Vern Ford, the park supervisor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lincoln Trail Homestead State Park and Memorial is a 162 acre state park located on the Sangamon River in Macon County near Harristown, Illinois. This important historic site, only 12 miles Southwest of Decatur, offers hiking, canoeing, picnicking, recreational activities, and a glimpse into the past. The park offers a unique view of central Illinois.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The state memorial, created in 1938, commemorates the approximate location of Abraham Lincoln’s first home in Illinois. The original Lincoln cabin has long been lost but the memorials and the quiet forest and stream easily transport the visitor back to the time when the Lincolns first settled this virgin wilderness. When you visit the park, drive east to the end of the park road where you will the find the memorials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.CIGAcache.org/"&gt;&lt;font size="+1"&gt;&lt;img alt="Link to CIGA" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/6e406db1-451f-4413-a8a7-969ca7d57e75.jpg" style="height:246px;width:478px;" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Central Illinois Geocaching Association&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363786329"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T15:35:35</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2292036">capumetu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for the cache, took me a while but success. In great shape.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363815482"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="372678">tallglenn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this nice cache in good shape, cleaned it up a bit.  We had the whole park to ourselves.  A bit of Poison Ivy to wade through.  Added another new county to my map. TFTMC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363608851"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T15:36:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42375063">GeoKelterFam</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it! Here we find ourselves in Illinois. Great to see this location. Love ammo cans! Woo! Thanks for bringing us here. Heading back from our GeoWoodstock XXII adventure. Grabbing some caches along the way. TFTC 1,3

Cache Across America #7</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363636158"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8218630">itwasmymouse</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache Across America!!!

Woohoo!

- - We're not in Ohio anymore! - -
Geowoodstock 2026 Adventure! 

Geocaching from Sylvania, Ohio. Caching and spending time with JenOvations, we used our joint stamp on most logs. We have the MOST fun together. 

This caching trip was one for the statistics book! Totally blessed to share these memories with this beautiful and wonderful woman. 

Trip details: 
- 5 days - 3,365 miles 
- 12 states (2 new geo states, OK, AR) 
- LOTS of new counties 
- 7 state capitals
- 450+ physical caches
- 125+ Larges (116 in a day)
- Lab arts (MO, GWXXII, KS. OK, AL)
- Lots of oldies: 2, 3 &amp; 4 digit GC's
- Oldest letterbox in USA/world
- 3 State's Oldest's: NE, OK, TN
- 6 Cache Across America Caches:
IL, NE, KS, OK, AR, MS
- 5 Geotour Cache Odyssey Caches:
MO, KS, NE, OK, AR
- 6 new event states
- 1 awesome drone show
- 1 MEGA &amp; 1 MAZE 

Cheapest Gas - $3.78 Decatur, AL
Expensive gas - $4.99 Wilmington, IL 

Thanks for adding to our Geowoodstock 2026 adventure and helping me with various goals, TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362390819"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1137940">NextStep_</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with Nurse Nanna on a road trip to Geowoodstock.  We were going to "be in the neighborhood", so we had to stop for a Cache across America cache.  We explored the park a little bit before hunting for the cache  - finding it about 25-30 South of where my gps wanted me to be.  Thanks for bringing us here and thanks for the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.671017" lon="-73.757883"><time>2019-10-08T00:00:00</time><name>GC8EHW7</name><desc>Cache Across America - New York by tenebrus</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC8EHW7</url><urlname>Cache Across America - New York</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="7411303" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - New York</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>tenebrus</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="245944">tenebrus</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="0">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New York</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;New York&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/user/fce4e217-9310-4447-a733-2242f74860d4.jpg" width="180" height="90" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Albany&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: New York&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 27th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 3rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 11th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; You can hardly really visit Albany – New York's capital – without using I-90 at some point. In fact, there were plans in the 1960s that were supposed to connect the Adirondack Northway (at an Exit 3 that they are just now building a half century later) to I-90 via I-687 (which is no longer part of the plan).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the exits planned for I-687, however, was going to be for Corporate Woods, a hub for large businesses hosted locally - the "big but small" vibe that Albany's all about. That did get built, but as I-90's exit 5A, with the original supersized ramp intended for I-687.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because I wanted to have a well-stocked ammo can, good for TBs, with easy access for the travelling geocacher, at almost any hour, this seemed to be The Spot to place it. Please be subtle in entering the treeline, preferably from the southeast, so as to avoid creating an obvious geo-trail (especially when there is snow on the ground).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Under slab</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1328593116"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-08T11:32:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="245944">tenebrus</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The replacement CCA has been published. Please use https://coord.info/GCBA4AX for that series moving forward.

Thank you to my beta testers who didn't have to return to NY just to get their CCA-NY box checked off. 

If you were one of these beta testers, please feel free to EITHER keep your log here OR convert your log here to Write Note and migrate your smiley over to the new cache as a Found It, linking back to the Write Note here. The only folks who should get two smileys are people who physically found BOTH the old cache and the new cache.

Thank you for understanding.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1328516626"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-07T20:09:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19371341">wanablee</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Caching with lakegal44 thanks from Page AZ </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1328370509"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-06T19:35:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Unknown</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="714325">Sapience Trek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This listing has been disabled for a period of time in excess of "a few weeks" as contemplated by the cache guidelines.   I know you are working to get a new one published in this one's place.  I'm assuming this one will be archived?

If there are special circumstances that will prevent a timely re-enabling of this cache, please post this as a note on the cache page so that this listing doesn't get archived for non-communication (please don't email.)   If it will take longer than 1 month, please continue to post updates approximately once a month which will help with processes.   

Failure to update this with an appropriate note may result in an archival in approximately 30 days.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1328134076"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-05T13:03:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11265453">thiayack</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My seventh CAA. Thanks for sharing the new coordinates for parking trailhead and cache. All is well. Appears I just missed a couple other cachers finding your CAA.
Left behind a trackable from Germany my personal path tag and picked up a path tag 
Tftc SL </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1328129401"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-05T12:38:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="9350479">benlorma07</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day one of trip to New England.  Quick find. We reached out to the CO in preparation for our trip north. The CO gave us new coords and we are happy to beta test. Left a pathtag. Tftc. 

Update on 2025/10/8: converted to a write note and moved the find to GCBA4AX. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="61.574617" lon="-149.54355"><time>2020-06-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC8VWY0</name><desc>Cache Across America - Alaska  by AKStafford</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC8VWY0</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Alaska </urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="7778460" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Alaska </groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>AKStafford</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="410459">AKStafford</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Alaska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2 align="center"&gt;Alaska&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Flag_of_Alaska.svg/709px-Flag_of_Alaska.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
