&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt;This cache is located in historic Concord and is within an easy walk to Minute Man National Historical Park in one direction and to Author's Ridge in Sleepy Hollow Cemetery in the other direction.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Minute Man Park is home to The Old North Bridge, where "The Shot Heard Round the World" was fired by American colonists on British soldiers on the morning of April 19, 1775 to begin the Revolutionary War.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nps.gov/mima/index.htm"&gt;Minute Man National Historical Park (U.S. National Park Service)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Author's Ridge in Sleepy Hollow Cemetery is the location of the graves of the famous writers Henry David Thoreau, Louisa May Alcott, Ralph Waldo Emerson, Nathaniel Hawthorne, and their families.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://concordma.gov/1956/Sleepy-Hollow-Cemetery"&gt;Sleepy Hollow Cemetery | Concord, MA&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
