</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Within 10' of trail.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1360710473"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-13T10:18:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14566146">CheekyBrit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Another Cache across America?!?! That would turn around any bad day. Smiles on the map, smiles on my face, and I'm ready for the next adventure. To all who built this audacious mission, I thank you. A favorite point for your troubles.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359744834"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T10:08:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="490910">Simon's Squad</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quick find while in the area tftc </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357192571"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3225416">RickieFareShowe18</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day 2 of 3 of my me-cation in Waltham for the CITO and a large amount of caching. Loved the trails from the cemetery to this parcel. The find was a bit underwhelming because it was out in the open. Added a new baggie for the log and rehid it better as to not be seen from its spot. TFTC! :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1352316349"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-01T14:08:59</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29842381">jomadol</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it and left a bracelet! Thank you!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1351182828"><groundspeak:date>2026-03-25T15:28:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4054616">kucharsm</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On a road trip in the northeast and trying to find specific geocache, including the CAA series. My wife came along and as usual, found it before I did. Logbook signed as ‘kucharsm + wife’. Thanks for the cache, and thanks for the Massachusetts souvenir! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1312887100"><groundspeak:date>2025-07-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I was planning on just doing park N grabs on this hot Friday, but happened to notice I was just seven miles from this CAA.  Of course I had to detour and do the short hike and find my first CCA!

Thanks for the hide!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.56995" lon="-87.878367"><time>2021-04-30T00:00:00</time><name>GC9ACQH</name><desc>Cache Across America - Wisconsin by awhip80</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC9ACQH</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Wisconsin</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="8210741" available="false" archived="true"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Wisconsin</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>awhip80</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5991975">Acre_and_Dale</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="21" inc="1">Cliff/falling rocks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Wisconsin</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Wisconsin&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/44c01856-a5dd-4142-8162-cf954fec8214.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Madison&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Milwaukee&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 23rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 30th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This small roadside park has much to offer travelers. Stop for a quick break from the road and you can get a bit of a history and geology lesson as well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Very near this area, in Red Banks, Jean Nicolet became the first European explorer to set foot in what is now the state of Wisconsin. The year was 1634 and this is where he started a journey along the waterways of the state to find a passage to the orient. Green Bay became Wisconsin’s first established city more than 130 years (1765) after Nicolet’s visit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rock formation, known as an escarpment, forms this area’s earthly shape. The Niagara Escarpment runs through this area and is best known for the water that flows over the cliff at Niagara Falls in New York.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wisconsin is home to about 100 waterfalls. Here, Wequiock Falls, plunges over a cliff of the Niagara Escarpment. The best viewing times at the falls are during the spring melting and after a rainstorm, but the formation is very picturesque any time you visit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The area here in this small park holds a ton of significance to the state of Wisconsin dating back thousands of years. That should become apparent as you explore the grounds here for a short time. Come, take a break, and enjoy this little jewel of Wisconsin!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td align="center" width="210"&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;font size="-1"&gt;&lt;font size="-1"&gt;&lt;b&gt;This cache placed by a member of:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;a href="http://www.wi-geocaching.com"&gt;&lt;img src="https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&amp;amp;id=19l1AM0lUK-PEFz5o0S6kwYLYSSmheRUQ" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.wi-geocaching.com"&gt;&lt;font size="-1"&gt;&lt;font size="-2"&gt;(click to visit our website)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1280073084"><groundspeak:date>2025-02-05T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1235590">JimandLinda</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Removed container per WGA Cache Rescue Mission CR3093. Still a great location to visit!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1279047262"><groundspeak:date>2025-01-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2797318">chevyole</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Just checking - has this one been picked up?  Would you like me to create a Cache Rescue for it?</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1275988745"><groundspeak:date>2025-01-02T09:40:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Archived</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5991975">Acre_and_Dale</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This cache is being archived because the new Cache Across America - Wisconsin cache (GCB1211) is now active.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1275181279"><groundspeak:date>2024-12-29T08:45:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5991975">Acre_and_Dale</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello cachers!

One final note that this cache will be archived on January 1st! I left it up long enough for those traveling for the holidays to grab it on their way through, and now it is time to say goodbye in the new year. I hope we will see you at the new cache location soon; happy caching!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1274700130"><groundspeak:date>2024-12-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="202428">The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Honestly, I was hoping this cache would remain active in Green Bay for a while longer.  I know of at least one vlogger who is chasing after the series and hasn't found the Wisconsin cache.  My hope was that folks could hit this with the new Cache Odyssey cache in town, that will publish on Sunday.  At least the new CAA cache is along the route between here and the Twin Cities, where the Minnesota Cache Odyssey cache will be located.

 -The Happy Hodag!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.887617" lon="-97.058483"><time>2021-08-02T00:00:00</time><name>GC9EMYE</name><desc>Cache Across America – South Dakota by Martinell</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC9EMYE</url><urlname>Cache Across America – South Dakota</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="8337776" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America – South Dakota</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Martinell</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="434774">martinell</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>South Dakota</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;South Dakota&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/user/84dde5b7-a807-4e83-af23-2f9f856efe8b.jpg" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Pierre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Sioux Falls&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 17th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 40th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Watertown, South Dakota's 4th largest city located along I-29 and US 212 in Northeastern South Dakota. A quiet, safe, progressive city. A perfect place to make memories for a lifetime. Enjoy great hunting, fishing, swimming and camping at our beautiful lakes. Home of the popular Terry Redlin Art Center and other talented artists, cultural and historical attractions, unique shops and wonderful hospitality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.watertownsd.com"&gt;http://www.watertownsd.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache rests by the Redlin Art Museum. Redlin's most compelling project is the construction of the museum to house his original art in Watertown, South Dakota, where he now resides. The Redlin Art Center, which includes a regional tourism office, Domed Theater, and state-of-the-art Amphitheater, opened in the summer of 1997 and has seen more than 1 million visitors from all over the world. Terry Redlin donated the $10 million museum to the State of South Dakota in appreciation for an art scholarship he received after graduating from high school in Watertown.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Few artists can rival the standards of excellence achieved by Master Artist Terry Redlin over the past 25 years. He is truly one of the country's most widely collected painters of wildlife and Americana. For eight consecutive years, 1991 through 1998, Redlin has been named America's Most Popular Artist in annual gallery surveys conducted by U.S.ART magazine. His induction into U.S.ART's Hall of Fame in 1992 followed the magazine's poll of 900 galleries nationwide which, that year, placed five of Redlin's limited editions in the top 11 in popularity. Over the life of the poll, 30 prints have been included in that list. His use of earthy colors, blazing sunrises and sunsets and nostalgic themes are often cited as the reasons for his immense popularity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache has been placed by the approval from Executive Director Julie Ranum of the Redlin Art Center.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://redlinart.com/"&gt;Visit the Museum Web Site.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://redlinart.com/artist.php"&gt;http://redlinart.com/artist.php&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1365001458"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-02T11:57:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="637986">Wollaston</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yay, another CAA completed. Day 21 visiting from Downunder 🇦🇺, outnabout on a little hunting adventure after another awesome GeoWoodstock. It’s always a great day for caching. 😎
TFTC martinell

If you’ve been to a GeoWoodstock you’re already checking out next years event. If not, check out GCBNWDV GeoWoodstock 2027 in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. May 29, 2027 and log a will attend to do your bit in achieving GIGA status. It’s a bucket list event that never disappoints.

Log my GW Ambassador trackable:  AM1889.   🙂</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364681935"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:57:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1149235">Nurse 1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for a nicely done cache.

Traveling the country to escape the stifling Savannah heat.

Came to Hutchinson for GWS XXII and now roadtripping to Gilby, picking up Odyssey caches and anything else interesting.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364046402"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T11:17:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="42126083">Josierose17</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it! 5/28/26</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363964973"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T22:16:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47506926">JoLeOh</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The final leg of our trip home from Geowoodstock brought us through Watertown. We've had this cache on the radar for a while, but today was the day. We inked the log and went on our way. On to the next!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362958566"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T14:21:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55129303">MimiK50</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found in good condition. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="37.5285" lon="-77.450567"><time>2021-11-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC9HTFF</name><desc>Cache Across America - Virginia by NPGlenn</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC9HTFF</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Virginia</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="8431521" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Virginia</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>NPGlenn</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1025585">NPGlenn</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Virginia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Virginia&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://imgproxy.geocaching.com/fe2b21d38bc578456881d4dd7388bfb3e145fc27?url=http%3A%2F%2Fupload.wikimedia.org%2Fwikipedia%2Fcommons%2Fthumb%2F4%2F47%2FFlag_of_Virginia.svg%2F670px-Flag_of_Virginia.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Richmond&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Virginia Beach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 35th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 10th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Welcome to the Virginia edition of the Cache Across America challenge. Whether this is your first find or your 50th find in this series, I am sure this will be or has been one of the most rewarding challenges you have done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This cache is located on Belle Isle in the James River as it passes through Richmond, Virginia. There is parking available on the north and south sides of the river (see waypoints) with pedestrian bridges giving access to the island.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“At 54 acres, Belle Isle is the largest island in the James River and one of the most historic sites in the city. Virginia Indians fished in the river here long before the English arrived. Captain John Smith was among the first Europeans to visit in 1607, and William Byrd I acquired the island in 1676. Sold by the Byrd family about 1776 the island soon became one of Richmond’s first industrial centers with the opening of a nail factory in 1814 and later a full-scale ironworks that operated until 1972. Granite was quarried here in the 19th and 20th centuries. During the Civil War one of the most notorious prisoner-of-war camps in the South was located on Belle Isle. The remains of a Confederate gun emplacement are visible on the island. From 1904 to 1967 a local power company operated a power plant on the south bank. In 1995 Belle Isle was listed on the National Register of Historic Places.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Belle Isle is very popular with hikers, bikers, swimmers, sightseers, and geocachers (several caches on the island). The cache is located just off of one of the many trails with minimal bushwacking required. Please help maintain this popular island by CITOing when you can and leaving it better than when you arrived. And don’t forget to pick up the code that you will need to find the final cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of you group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>About 50' off the trail. Light bushwacking. There is a lot of bounce in the area so I included a spoiler picture.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364377737"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T11:08:23</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52357928">tbray2000</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Container and log were in great shape. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364376646"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T11:05:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30649089">BWMHAZEL</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc!!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362172955"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-16T19:18:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25469529">lindsayasdnil</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Did I mention it was hot!! Happy to find GZ here as it was a beautiful time but haven’t climatized to weather that doesn’t require a sweater yet! 
Logged in, pic taken and now to find some AC lol 
TFTC </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363338190"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="25469328">Missbderycke</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Phone in Airplane Mode, Work Phone &amp; Laptop Shut Off, 5 days. 4 New States. 5 CAAs, 4 Cache Odysseys, 3000+ km driving, 25+km on foot, a lifetime of laughs &amp; memories = priceless.

Here is a short story long... in booking a hotel in November of 2025 I was asked to stay on the line and listen to an offer. While listening I was getting ready to head out on a hike with a friend so Im not going to lie I was paying zero attention. Afterward the lady was like does that sound good and I answered yes which prompted her to ask for my credit card number. Still not paying attention to what was going on and thinking I was paying for the November hotel I ended up with a 3 night 4 day stay to 11 different locations in the US for a really good deal. When I saw the email stating what I had just signed up for I called lindsayasdnil and said well I did this thing so pick from these 11 locations and we will go on a geotrip! She ended up deciding on Williamsburg, VA as it was one we could drive to and the closest-ish one. Now just to decide when we would go. We seem to like to road trip in May so we decided on doing that again and combine it with a milestone birthday for her. Since my goal is to visit all of the states and also complete this series while doing so we chatted about tacking on an extra day and visiting Delaware as neither of us had it as a state we were planning on visiting for a specific reason (but boy am I sure glad we did, more on this later). About a week before leaving I convinced her that we werent far from the New Jersey CAA either and we would be driving super close to the North Carolina border so we might as well pop down there for a hot minute and grab a cache as well.

This was day #3 of our adventure. We mainly spent the day walking around colonial Williamsburg and checking out things there, we took a brief break at the hotel to change because we weren't used to this heat and then set off to find CAA#11 for me. Super cool spot. We watched some young boys jump out off the building and thought there is no way the water was deep enough although they proved us wrong. We took our time in here checking out somethings but we were quickly losing daylight so we didn't have enough time to grab any of the other caches today. Adding a fav point. Tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361222535"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T16:27:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1283849">nikkki16</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!!!  Beautiful day on the isle!!! :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.622" lon="-79.79845"><time>2023-04-27T00:00:00</time><name>GCA7F55</name><desc>Cache Across America - West Virginia by Troopbiz</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCA7F55</url><urlname>Cache Across America - West Virginia</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9047202" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - West Virginia</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Troopbiz</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2464712">Troopbiz</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="52" inc="0">Night cache</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>West Virginia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;West Virginia&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/57aef7b3-3de0-42c9-9394-81895a58f398_l.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;Br /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Charleston&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Charleston&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 41st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 37th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 35th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Welcome to Coopers Rock State Park, 1 of 35 state parks in West Virginia and home to the most breathtaking view the Mountain State has to offer. This cache will have you embarking on a gentle 2.5-mile round-trip hike to the Raven’s Rock overlook. Please follow all park rules and signage, including no night caching. During the winter months (January - March) the main gate may be closed. This cache will still be available, but it may be a slightly longer hike. As always, please exercise extreme caution near the overlook and keep an eye out for snakes and other creatures near GZ. I hope you enjoy this hidden gem in the Mountain State!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three-digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Right side of trail as you are returning from the overlook in small rock formation just off the path</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364757753"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T22:09:37</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12176921">fatherofgrace2013</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wanted to get out of Clarksburg and hit a trail that I haven't been on yet. Yes there are still hundreds of them somehow. Today was finally the day to hike down to Ravens Rock and see what the fuss was all about. It was a nice warm sunny day and not many people out in this section. All of the trails in this area have been really nice and this one was a great exercise. Very peaceful at the rock. Oh and for the cache it was a very well hidden nice large one with plenty of room for swag. Thanks for giving me a bonus reason to finally hike down this trail. Favorite point on the way 👍 Tnlnsl Tftc </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364696003"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T14:42:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39771265">cavscaos</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found in good condition. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362639658"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="616426">smidejongh</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">#658
Verry nice trail
Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361245668"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T19:23:54</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29653350">professor10</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Camping at Coopers Rock and got the wife to make the hike to Ravens Rock.  Great place for a cache! FP</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1354866323"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-12T12:50:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54866033">caldwells927</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This is so cool!!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="37.449567" lon="-122.340567"><time>2023-07-25T00:00:00</time><name>GCABQWB</name><desc>Cache Across America - California by rragan </desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCABQWB</url><urlname>Cache Across America - California</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9174742" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - California</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>rragan </groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="78712">rragan</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="0">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="0">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="0">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>California</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;California&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img height="140" src="https://imgproxy.geocaching.com/a1b73ec90c2cb6c0196109dea93c9eb16eb97203?url=http%3A%2F%2Fi12.photobucket.com%2Falbums%2Fa240%2FSc0oByDo0%2FCache%2520Across%2520America%2520Images%2Fca-flag.gif" width="180" /&gt;
			&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Sacramento&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Los Angeles&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 3rd&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 31st&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Welcome to the California edition of the Cache Across America challenge. Whether this is your first find or your 50th find in this series, I am sure this will be or has been one of the most rewarding challenges you have done.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;California is the third largest U.S. state by area and the most populous. It has a coastline with the Pacific Ocean that is over 800 miles long. California has a wide variety of climate zones, from the hot, dry desert in the south to the cold, snowy mountains in the north. The climate zones are determined by the state's location along the Pacific coast, its proximity to the Sierra Nevada mountains, and its elevation. The variety of climate zones in California offers a wide range of outdoor activities, such as surfing, hiking, skiing, and camping. The climate zones also offer homes to iconic trees, such as the coastal redwoods and the giant sequoias.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;
			In terms of economy, California is the largest of any U.S. state. Major contributors to the state's economy are agriculture, wine, shipping, entertainment (Hollywood and the film industry), technology (Silicon Valley and the Internet), and aerospace.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;
			Early California was inhabited by at least 300,000 indigenous people. In 1542, Juan Cabrillo started the Spanish period. Not until around 1770, did Spanish colonization and the creation of 21 Spanish missions see the spread of the Spanish presence. In 1821, the Mexican War of Independence saw California become part of the Mexican Empire. In 1846, a group of American settlers around Sonoma rebelled against Mexican rule during the Bear Flag Revolt. By 1848, Alta California became the American state of California. The discovery of gold led to a massive influx of prospectors and miners. In the next 6 years, 300,000 settlers had arrived. California became the 31st state in 1850.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The cache is located along the CA-35 highway, locally known as Skyline Boulevard since it runs along the ridge of the Santa Cruz mountains with views of the Pacific Ocean and the Bay area. You can reach CA-35 from CA-92. From there, CA-35 climbs to the skyline, its namesake. Follow the winding two-lane road south until you reach the Purisima Creek North Ridge parking area (use parking coordinates).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;P&gt;Purisima Creek Redwoods Open Space Preserve is located on the western slopes of the Santa Cruz Mountains overlooking Half Moon Bay. The centerpiece of this 5,412-acre preserve is Purisima Creek Canyon, with its towering redwoods, rushing creek, and understory of ferns, berries, and wildflowers. Magnificent views of the coast and Half Moon Bay are visible from the northern part of the preserve.&lt;/P&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The trail and trailhead are closed at night (pay attention to the closing hours signed there). Also pay attention to any trail closure signage. Take the Chris Macintosh trail and &lt;strong&gt;use the waypoint to find where you leave the trail to go to the cache. Do not bushwhack up from the main trail.&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy the ferns and mosses that are all over. Respect the foliage and try to minimize geotrail formation. On some days, when the fog is in, you will find things fairly moist here so dress accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p"&gt;Once you have found the cache, perhaps taken a picture and collected the code, you may want to explore further south along Skyline Boulevard. Not far from here is an old growth redwood known as the Methuselah tree, 1800 years old. You can locate it via a nearby geocache. A bit further south where CA-84 joins Skyline, you can find food and gas. The eatery there is named after a famous Arlo Guthrie song and sports its own Group W bench. Continuing south, you might want to hike up Windy Hill for views of San Francisco, the Pacific Ocean all the way down to Mount Hamilton in the South Bay. Proceeding further south, you can see examples of sustainable California agriculture at a winery. A variety of great hiking areas dot the length of Skyline Boulevard all the way down to CA-9 at the southern end. Peninsula Open Space Trust has a good summary of highlights of the Skyline Boulevard route: &lt;a href="https://openspacetrust.org/blog/skyline-boulevard/"&gt;https://openspacetrust.org/blog/skyline-boulevard/&lt;/a&gt; .&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of you group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Container is an ammo can cabled  to a tree so it doesn't wander. Some natural cover shrouds the cable.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364835779"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="84135">Team Libra</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Revisited this cache today while hiking with nozy nabor and DavidT21 &amp; Fisherwoman.  Swapped trackables, adding one that I picked up at Mingo.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364836421"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="87748">DavidT21 &amp; Fisherwoman</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hike a loop in the park with Nozy Nabor and Team Libra. We started at Skyline Bl and were mentally prepared for going downhill and uphill at the end, which did not disapoint. We even got a FTF so it turned out to be a great day. 
Been meaning to get this cache for awhile and today was finally the day. Nice one</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364763470"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1235204">gimme5</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Together with Biker-13, I’m on a mission to complete the Jasmer Challenge. Our road trip starts in San Francisco and takes us all the way to Seattle, with a small detour to the Canadian border to collect another country souvenir 😉. From there, we’ll head south via Salt Lake City and Moab before eventually returning to San Francisco.

This is day 2 of 19 of our Jasmer Challenge tour through the northwestern United States. Today, we are caching in the bay area.

Our journey will cover nearly 7,000 km across six states and currently includes caches with a combined total of 32,980 favourite points.

Log @ 11:49, #14262.

Thank you, rragan, for hiding and maintaining this cache.

Greetings from Switzerland, gimme5
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364763407"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T11:49:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2920269">Biker-13</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">gimme5 and I are hitting the road in a motorhome for a big geocaching vacation in the U.S. from May 30, 2026, to June 17, 2026. 
The planned route is San Francisco – Seattle – Salt Lake City – San Francisco. This time, our mission is to complete the “Jasmer Challenge,” visit the Groundspeak headquarters, and find the Ape Cache. Of course, we’ll be visiting other geocaches as well.

Day 2 of 19
Beautiful hike. Found cache on way back.


Thank you rragan, for planning this geocaching adventure!

Find #14590  @ 11:49h  Greatings Biker-13 from Switzerland
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364635469"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T08:23:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4364549">nozy nabor</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tb visit</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.907" lon="-104.9794"><time>2023-08-22T00:00:00</time><name>GCAD7AB</name><desc>Cache Across America - Colorado by EJKPBR</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAD7AB</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Colorado</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9218421" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Colorado</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>EJKPBR</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="12885796">EJKPBR</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Colorado</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="4" style="width:76%;"&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td rowspan="4"&gt;
			&lt;h2&gt;Colorado&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;img height="135" src="https://imgproxy.geocaching.com/0365439a2e10be530df8d9211daf74cc5f928a3a?url=http%3A%2F%2Fupload.wikimedia.org%2Fwikipedia%2Fcommons%2Fthumb%2F4%2F46%2FFlag_of_Colorado.svg%2F800px-Flag_of_Colorado.svg.png" width="187" /&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Capital: Denver&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Largest City: Denver&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Size Rank: 8th&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Population Rank: 22nd&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Admission to Union: 38th&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style="vertical-align:middle;"&gt;
			&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img height="221" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation&amp;#39;s capital upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is placed at the &amp;quot;base&amp;quot; of Pikes Peak - Americas Mountain. Just up the road a few hundred feet, is the entrance to the Pikes Peak Highway.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Pikes Peak is the highest summit of the southern Front Range of the Rocky Mountains in North America. The ultra-prominent 14,115-foot fourteener is located in Pike National Forest, 12 miles west of downtown Colorado Springs, Colorado.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;This tollroad provides you the opportunity to enjoy 19 miles of mountain terrain, with frequent breathtaking views, four different Colorado life zones and unique animal sightings. From the summit’s various viewing areas, snap photos of Pikes Peak’s incredible scenery. Pikes Peak is one of Colorado’s majestic 14’ers and is one of the few places so grand in scale that are also accessible to be experienced first-hand by people of all ages and abilities.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;There is a fee to drive up to the summit and you do need to plan ahead in the summer months, as they require you to purchase a timed entry permit.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Find all current info such as hours and rates, weather and reservation info at this &lt;a href="https://coloradosprings.gov/drivepikespeak" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"&gt;LINK&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located on the &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOGBOOK &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache!&lt;br /&gt;
			Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color:red;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:xx-large;"&gt;Congratulations!!!! FTF!!! hartsdale!!! FTF!!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Be careful of barbed wire</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364634293"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T09:21:01</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3581435">appalachiancachin</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc more later</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364485048"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T07:51:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7823528">adria2006</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Trobat.
De camí cap al Pikes Peak, fem una parada en aquest indret per cercar aquest catxe que surt fàcilment del seu amagatall.
Moltes gràcies per amagar.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364257917"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T17:37:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12179863">wfreemanjr</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC quick P&amp;G Team Freeman Belton Tx</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364257850"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T17:35:32</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="913394">barbie6899</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!! Nice and easy find! Team Freeman, Texas.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364257771"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T17:33:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7838713">aservantsheart</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sweet Cache! TFTC This was a fun find! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="32.24265" lon="-92.51985"><time>2023-09-05T00:00:00</time><name>GCADYN6</name><desc>Cache Across America - Louisiana by darrellba</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCADYN6</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Louisiana</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9239899" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Louisiana</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>darrellba</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="7232549">darrellba</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Louisiana</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Louisiana&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://imgproxy.geocaching.com/a849a78abf4446850dd34681f605479109d0a451?url=http%3A%2F%2Fupload.wikimedia.org%2Fwikipedia%2Fcommons%2Fthumb%2Fe%2Fe0%2FFlag_of_Louisiana.svg%2F800px-Flag_of_Louisiana.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Baton Rouge&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: New Orleans&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 31st&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 22nd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 18th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is located in Jimmie Davis State Park in North Central Louisiana. The park is named after the 47th governor of Louisiana. James Houston Davis (September 11, 1899 – November 5, 2000) was an American singer, songwriter, and politician. After achieving fame for releasing both sacred and popular songs, Davis served as governor of Louisiana from 1944 to 1948 and again from 1960 to 1964.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Davis was a nationally popular country and gospel music singer from the 1930s into the 1960s, occasionally recording and performing as late as the early 1990s. He appeared as himself in a number of Hollywood movies. He was inducted into six halls of fame, including the Country Music Hall of Fame, the Southern Gospel Music Association Hall of Fame, and the Louisiana Music Hall of Fame.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In 1999, "You Are My Sunshine" was honored with a Grammy Hall of Fame Award, and the Recording Industry Association of America named it one of the Songs of the Century. "You Are My Sunshine" was ranked in 2003 as No. 73 on CMT's 100 Greatest Songs in Country Music. Virginia Shehee, a Shreveport businesswoman, philanthropist, and state senator, introduced legislation to designate "You Are My Sunshine" as the official state song.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Davis often performed during his campaign stops while running for governor of Louisiana. After being elected in 1944, he became known as the "singing governor". While governor, he had a No. 1 hit single in 1945 with "There's a New Moon Over My Shoulder". Davis recorded for the Victor Talking Machine Company, and Decca Records for decades and released more than 40 albums.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; A number of his songs were used as part of motion picture soundtracks. Davis appeared in half a dozen films, including one starring Ozzie and Harriet, who had a TV series under their names. Members of Davis's last band included Allen "Puddler" Harris of Lake Charles. He had served as pianist for singer Ricky Nelson early in his career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Davis was also a close acquaintance of the country singer-songwriter Hank Williams, with whom he co-wrote the top-10 hit "(I Heard That) Lonesome Whistle" in 1951, supposedly on a fishing day they spent together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Davis died on November 5, 2000. He had suffered a fall in his home some ten months earlier and may have had a stroke in his last days. He is interred alongside his first wife at the Jimmie Davis Tabernacle Cemetery in his native Beech Springs community near Quitman.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The park is currently open daily from 6:00 am until 10:00 pm.  There is currently a small entrance fee ($3/person) required for persons between the ages of 4 and 61.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#CCCCCC" height="61"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Between oak tree and shrub</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364102707"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T17:28:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="637986">Wollaston</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A day later than I planned, but I made it. Very happy to tick off another CAA cache. 🙂 Day 18 visiting from Downunder 🇦🇺, outnabout on a little hunting adventure after another awesome GeoWoodstock. It’s always a great day for caching. 😎
TFTC darrellba

If you’ve been to a GeoWoodstock you’re already checking out next years event. If not, check out GCBNWDV GeoWoodstock 2027 in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. May 29, 2027 and log a will attend to do your bit in achieving GIGA status. It’s a bucket list event that never disappoints.

Log my GW Ambassador trackable:  AM1889.   🙂</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363907947"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48318008">dobiest</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Made quick work of this one. As Troopbiz said, I'm not sure the park staff enjoyed the 6 minutes we were in and out. TFTC SL </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363884865"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2464712">Troopbiz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">**Cache Across America - Louisiana**
**Find #22817**
**Cache Across America #36**

**About This Cache**
Our last CAA hide of this trip, and a beautiful spot to explore. I thought the park would be busier considering it was Memorial Day, but we had the place largely to ourselves. Perhaps it was the entrance fee keeping people away. I tried to convince the gate guard that we would only be in the park for a few minutes, but he still insisted we pay the $6. It was basically one dollar for every minute we were in the park. LOL.

Spotted the cache easily from the car as we pulled up, but as we got out, the park staff drove around to let us know we couldn't be in the area. We pointed to the very obvious ammo can sitting 10 feet away from the parking, and they seemed to be content with that answer. Signed in, got the code number, and got the heck out of there. TFTC SL

**About My Trip**
Exploring Hot Springs today with DOBIEST before heading south to find Louisiana’s oldest, high point, and Cache Across America. Enjoying the bayou! All logs are signed “TB” or “Troopbiz”. Thanks, darrellba, for placing and maintaining this cache! TFTC SL</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363324772"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T16:28:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55477021">crl_7827</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for leaving it! Pants are recommended, some tall grass between the road and it. Don’t get any ticks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362387969"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T20:12:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6041752">Winston4Ever</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I’m caching with Lil Devil to GeoWoodstock in Kansas. We flew into Pensacola yesterday. Today, we started in Mobile Alabama. The sunset was amazing!Thanks for the fun! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.138917" lon="-84.510733"><time>2024-02-13T00:00:00</time><name>GCAKHHN</name><desc>Cache Across America - Kentucky by Ground Fox</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCAKHHN</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Kentucky</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9407004" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Kentucky</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Ground Fox</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2148086">Ground Fox</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="31" inc="1">Camping nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Kentucky</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="4" style="width:77%;"&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td rowspan="4"&gt;
			&lt;h2&gt;Kentucky&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;img height="135" src="https://imgproxy.geocaching.com/3fce4be4f00650ff370522bb0bac988be3b61bdd?url=http%3A%2F%2Fupload.wikimedia.org%2Fwikipedia%2Fcommons%2Fthumb%2F8%2F8d%2FFlag_of_Kentucky.svg%2F428px-Flag_of_Kentucky.svg.png" width="187" /&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Capital: Frankfort&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Largest City: Louisville&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Size Rank: 37th&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Population Rank: 25th&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Admission to Union: 15th&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41" rel="nofollow"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style="vertical-align:middle;"&gt;
			&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img height="221" src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7" rel="nofollow"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation&amp;#39;s capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; Welcome to Kentucky’s Cache Across America geocache located in the heart of the Bluegrass region of Kentucky.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Early American frontiersman and explorer Daniel Boone once remarked that “Heaven must be a Kentucky kind of place.”&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/67f9d1c9-316c-4cc9-a24a-36778cdc7691.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The Bluegrass region is home to the largest concentration of rock fences in Central Kentucky and features some of the most beautiful scenic byways lined with both stone stacked and wooden plank horse fences in the U.S. Early settlers of Scottish-Irish origin built the first dry-laid limestone rock fences in Kentucky. These immigrants brought their dry stone masonry skills and knowledge with them when they settled here.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/ebf60399-889f-41d6-baba-0fdd7a228556.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;This region of Kentucky is also referred to as the Horse Capital of the World. The distinct geological area here is known as karst, featuring gently rolling plains of deep loam soils atop phosphate-rich limestone with springs that flow and sink underground. As acidic water interacts with limestone, calcium is dissolved into the soil. Thoroughbred horses that graze on the land and drink the mineral fortified water get a healthy start with strong bones that are ideal for racing.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The Kentucky Bluegrass region is also famous for its bluegrass named Poa pratensis, a species of grass named for the blue color of its seedpods that bloom in the spring. It is excellent for horse pastures because it is low-growing, highly nutritious, very palatable and tolerant of frequent grazing. It also forms a tight sod, providing horses a good footing in their pastures here.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Located along the Legacy Trail and directly across Iron Works Pike near GZ is the world famous Kentucky Horse Park. The Legacy Trail is a shared-use greenway trail that connects downtown Lexington with area neighborhoods, parks and historic sites. The trail begins at the Isaac Murphy Memorial Garden and winds north to the far northern end of the Kentucky Horse Park.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The 1,200 acre Kentucky Horse Park brings nearly one million guests to Central Kentucky annually including tourists, competitors, horse owners and spectators.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/2b022638-69a4-4f4c-9153-e56118764987.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The most famous thoroughbred racehorse of the 20th century, Man o’ War, is buried at the park in a memorial with a statue dedicated to his life. Buried with him are some of his offspring, including Triple Crown winner War Admiral, who was upset by Seabiscuit in their famous match race in 1938. The 2010 World Equestrian Games were held at the Kentucky Horse Park and drew an estimated 507,000 people.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;The Kentucky Derby, America’s most famous horse race, is held just down Interstate 64 at Churchill Downs racetrack in Louisville. It was established in 1875 and runs annually on the first Saturday in May.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/92bc5010-3b2d-4d1b-9690-6b98cdecd338.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Some of the earliest whiskey and bourbon distilled in Kentucky was produced in the Bluegrass region because it was well-suited for growing corn, the major ingredient used for its distillation. Corn and other grains like barley or rye were combined with the fresh water produced naturally by local limestone springs and placed in barrels for storage. Today, Kentucky still reigns as the nation’s leading distiller, producing more than 95% of the country’s bourbon.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;This Cache Across America geocache is an ammo can located just off the Legacy Trail not far from parking. Be sure to completely close the container and cover cache back up after finding. You can open up the cache without the lock here.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Enjoy this cache as you would any other. If you are searching this cache as a participant in the Cache Across America series, please post a photo of yourself or a member of your group with the cache in your online log. If you for some reason are unable to meet the photo requirement, please make alternate arrangements to verify your find with the individual cache owner. There is no photo requirement for non-challenge participants.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck! See hint for combo.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Geopile between cluster of trees. You can open up the cache without the lock.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363785159"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T16:24:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8589340">Floridafinder2</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I was in town for a friend’s retirement and had some time to pass before my flight. I didn’t realize how close this was to the airport and so I made a detour and in the rain made the find while also dropping a few tbs! I was smiling to see a friend was the last person to log this cache! Happy to have another CAA off the list!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363026656"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T17:55:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19483995">Aegir101</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aegir101 and beJs are on a 5 day trip from Maryland💪🦀 to MI, IN, KY and OH to complete their second Jasmer loop. Today was day 4 the drive from IN to KY. It was an overcast rainy day but we had fun. We started on the waterfront in Evansville and headed to Louisville then Dayton. We stopped along the way to look for old caches, webcams, challenges, and counties, as well as all cache types to stay well rounded. Thanks to all these COs for placing and maintaining these caches. 
  This was one of 2 main targets in Kentucky today. After an intense rain coming down from Louisville, we arrived and it was dry. We made a short and a pleasant walk on a paved trail over to GZ from parking. Once there this was a quick easy find. My 21st CAA, 29 to go! AIO, TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363040510"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2938303">bejs</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Aegir101 and bejs from the D.C. area have teamed up for a five day caching tear through Michigan, Indiana, Kentucky, and Ohio, getting the oldests, CAAs, cache types, and finishing our second Jasmer loops.

Today - after a great Thursday on Power Island Michigan and a Friday drive getting oldies through Indiana - we are wrapping up our time in Indiana and heading into Kentucky and then Ohio.

Checks off another CAA! Thanks for the fun hide, beJs

--- 

Find # 4545
As found: Traditional Cache 2.0/2.0 Regular</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361825045"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T15:45:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1567152">HikingSeal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Two faint trails going into the woods in the general direction of the geocache. Naturally, I choose the wrong one first. Very quick find once I was on the Wright Geo trail. Once signing the log, I was surprised to see somebody was here before me today. Left a flash tag and some cashing cards.

Thanks for the cache!

Found with [Cachly](https://www.cach.ly/)
[Cachetur](https://cachetur.no) Contributor &amp; Ambassador
[Podcacher](https://www.podcacher.com) Club Member</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361813129"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-17T15:12:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29511656">Pokemonmon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="37.17475" lon="-113.009183"><time>2024-06-21T00:00:00</time><name>GCARCTE</name><desc>Cache Across America - Utah by RockQ</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCARCTE</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Utah</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9551395" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Utah</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>RockQ</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4299515">RockQ</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Utah</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Utah&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://imgproxy.geocaching.com/cf3b08a42ec81e6ba1d8fb49a181a6691a9510fb?url=http%3A%2F%2Fupload.wikimedia.org%2Fwikipedia%2Fcommons%2Fthumb%2Ff%2Ff6%2FFlag_of_Utah.svg%2F660px-Flag_of_Utah.svg.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Salt Lake City&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Salt Lake City&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 13th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 34th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 45th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41" target="_blank"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7" target="_blank"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is located on the serene Springdale River Trail, offering stunning views and a unique trail experience along the Virgin River near Zion National Park.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nestled along the Virgin River, the Springdale River Trail provides breathtaking views of Zion National Park’s towering sandstone cliffs. This trail is perfect for a peaceful walk and offers a tranquil escape from the hustle and bustle of more crowded areas.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Zion National Park is my favorite place on earth, and the Virgin River is its beating heart. I’ve spent countless days biking, swimming, tubing, reading, and walking along its path. The magic of Zion is best felt by the river, where the serene waters and the towering sandstone cliffs create a sanctuary of peace and beauty. Many visit Zion, but few truly experience the majestic serenity of the river that has crafted its magnificent landscape.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Access the trail from George A. Barker River Park, which offers ample parking and restrooms. The park provides a perfect starting point, allowing easy access to the river and the trail. The Springdale River Trail is suitable for all ages, making it a wonderful outing for families and individuals alike.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cache is an ammo can hidden behind a pile of rocks near some shrubs just off the trail. Please ensure it is well-concealed to prevent accidental discovery and avoid unnecessary trampling of the fragile desert landscape by referring to the spoiler photo for precise hiding details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please re-hide the cache as you found it, using natural materials to keep it concealed. Avoid creating new trails and always practice CITO.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After finding the cache, take some time to enjoy the river. Walk along the edge of the river trail, under the shade of the cottonwoods, and let the serenity of this magical place wash over you.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Happy caching!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Across America Series Bonus Cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is part of the Cache Across America series. Learn more about this series and the requirements for finding and logging the &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7" target="_blank"&gt;bonus cache&lt;/a&gt; on its dedicated page. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/td&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Pile of rocks behind shrub</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363006948"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T16:42:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13646896">pnwfamily6</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362766734"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T09:47:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8943446">GC Rogier</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a wonderful place! Thanks for sharing! And thank you for the geocache! 🙏🏻🙏🏻</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362383157"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T17:40:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="749832">RRRL</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for the Utah installment.
Grabbed on the way to the campground. 
TFTC.
-RRRL.
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362383082"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T17:38:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="29171930">Squiggsss</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Some cache grabs on the E-scooters with RRRL! TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361013873"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T17:44:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3313059">TheRamblinRs</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Beautiful day for geocaching!  Our first Cache across America!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.9501" lon="-90.801717"><time>2024-12-06T00:00:00</time><name>GCB1211</name><desc>Cache Across America - Wisconsin by Acre_and_Dale</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB1211</url><urlname>Cache Across America - Wisconsin</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="9779356" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - Wisconsin</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Acre_and_Dale</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5991975">Acre_and_Dale</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="46" inc="1">Trucks/RVs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="43" inc="1">Livestock nearby</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Wisconsin</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Wisconsin&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/44c01856-a5dd-4142-8162-cf954fec8214.png" width="187" height="135" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Madison&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: Milwaukee&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 23rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 30th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Highway 29 is a bustling midwestern route, whisking travelers through little towns, sprawling fields of corn, and rolling Wisconsin hills. Communities and businesses alike thrive sitting just off the highway, and the location for Wisconsin’s Cache Across America hide is no exception. This special little cheese house is owned and operated by a Dutch-born cheese maker, and calls the quiet country town of Thorp its home. One of many excellent cheese houses in our fine state, this cache location is a true testament to Wisconsin’s nickname and heritage as “America’s Dairyland.”&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When it comes to Wisconsin, images of cows, cheese, beer, brats, and the Packers come readily to mind. What is lesser known is that Wisconsin also thrives in the tourism business. According to Travel Wisconsin, 1 in 21 Wisconsin jobs are sustained by tourism in some way. Gorgeous natural areas, lively arts and music scenes, and engaging downtown experiences make Wisconsin a state folks return to.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;As a proud Wisconsin native, I wanted to highlight a few of the diversely wonderful and distinctly recognizable aspects of our state. This site leans into our dairyland heritage and exceptional experiences by way of agro-tourism.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This cache has been placed on the property of a dairy farm, cheese house, store, and cafe all in one. CAA - Wisconsin  is a great stopping spot for visitors to take a break after a long car ride and have a chance to stretch their legs. There are lots of dairy-themed activities available to visitors in the town of Thorp, but stopping to say hello to Violet will likely be the highlight. Violet, the flower box cow, is the keeper of this geocache and the newest addition to the property! She is named after Wisconsin’s state flower, and her ear tag denotes what number in the state lineup Wisconsin is. If you are having trouble opening the cache box, take a good long look at that ear tag. Please be kind and gentle with Violet, so she can live a long and happy life here on the farm.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are not required to purchase or participate with the activities on the property in order to get this cache, nor do you need to speak to any employees if you do not want to. This cache is out in plain sight, and should simply require following the coordinates to find the prize.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please be respectful of the cache container and the property it is placed on, as we have kindly received permission to place this cache from the managers of this establishment. Feel free to snap a photo with the cache box (I would recommend doing it in front of Dutchess the giant cow) and then return everything back to its place.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The nearby business is open from 7am to 7pm seven days a week. Please refrain from going after this cache after dark in the summer (or after closing hours in the winter months) out of respect to the property owners. Even though they love visitors, it is still an operational farm and we need to be respectful of their business and resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;
&lt;table&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logging Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; There is no photo requirement for logging this cache, although it is highly recommended as this cache is part of the Cache Across America series of caches. To learn more about the logging requirements for the Cache Across America series Bonus Final Cache, please read more here:  &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;CAA Series Final&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual verification of all 50 state finds will be required before logging the series final.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If participating in the series, please take note of the three digit code located inside this cache. Save this code in a secure place. When you have visited all 50 caches, and have collected all 50 codes, you are welcome to seek and find the final cache! Good luck!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Padlock Code: What number state is Wisconsin for joining the Union?  "0xx"</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364732935"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T16:14:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1595500">bulldogshouse</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great cache! Hopefully someday we will complete the series. SL TFTC 🐾 </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364265061"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T21:07:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1159226">XZQ&amp;Dad</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Passing through today on a drive from Minnesota to Door County WI and had to stop. Don’t think I’ll ever complete the whole CAA series but thought I’d take a photo just in case. Adding a fav for the fun container. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362727053"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T16:21:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52482104">erinb777</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362356524"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T14:25:45</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="34471389">aghehdbdvsvsvzvvsv</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice one! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362161657"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T11:26:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="32773046">beckpac</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC!! This was too cute!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.687233" lon="-73.769733"><time>2025-07-19T00:00:00</time><name>GCBA4AX</name><desc>Cache Across America - New York by tenebrus</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCBA4AX</url><urlname>Cache Across America - New York</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="10049703" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Cache Across America - New York</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>tenebrus</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="245944">tenebrus</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="0">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New York</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;span&gt;&lt;table width="76%" border="0" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="2"&gt;
&lt;tr valign="top"&gt;
&lt;td width="190" rowspan="4" align="center" bgcolor="#999966"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;New York&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/user/fce4e217-9310-4447-a733-2242f74860d4.jpg" width="180" height="90" /&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Capital: Albany&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Largest City: New York&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Size Rank: 27th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Population Rank: 3rd&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Admission to Union: 11th&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="left"&gt;Find the other caches in the series &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=9bbb6655-e2ef-459b-80f6-66a9decd9d41"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td width="693" height="48" align="center" valign="middle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/166de36d-345c-48ac-a95b-898064ff2c2c.jpg" width="450" height="221" /&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td bgcolor="#99CC99"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cache Across America Series:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a series of caches that will take you on a caching tour of the entire United States. One cache is hidden in each of the 50 states. These caches each contain a numeric clue that will lead you to &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.geocaching.com/bookmarks/view.aspx?guid=68e2d17a-8ae9-45c9-9516-0e45694cc2d7"&gt;one final cache&lt;/a&gt; located in our nation's capitol upon completion of the series.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this cache:&lt;/strong&gt; You can hardly really visit Albany – New York's capital – without using I-90 at some point. In fact, there were plans in the 1960s that were supposed to connect the Adirondack Northway (at an Exit 3 that they are just now building a half century later) to I-90 via I-687 (which is no longer part of the plan).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the exits planned for I-687, however, was going to be for Corporate Woods, a hub for large businesses hosted locally - the "big but small" vibe that Albany's all about. That did get built, but as I-90's exit 5A, with the original supersized ramp intended for I-687.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because I wanted to have a well-stocked ammo can, good for TBs, with easy access for the travelling geocacher, at almost any hour, this seemed to be The Spot to place it. Please be subtle in entering the treeline, preferably from the southeast, so as to avoid creating an obvious geo-trail (especially when there is snow on the ground).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; While this cache can be done in darkness, please limit it to reasonable hours of operation: 6AM-8PM (or sunset, if later).
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td height="61" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cache Across America Series Bonus Cache:&lt;/strong&gt; This cache is part of the Cache Across America series. Learn more about this series and the requirements for finding and logging the bonus cache on its dedicated page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Fallen tree</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363954280"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="14048516">Poppa Dean</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I made a second visit because I wanted to drop a TB that I've been carrying around for too long.  This White Bear wants to go someplace warmer than here.  I'm thinking that this would be a good place to leave it because the TB that I launched at this cache is now in the Neatherlands.  I wish good travels to the White Bear!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363624546"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T18:13:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1041842">lschweic</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">The ground was wet, but the cache was dry. I didn’t expect a proper path so close to the cache. The path seems to come out of nowhere. 

CAA #14 for me. 

TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360352002"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T18:46:39</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="767840">BevanQ</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I found this pretty exposed so I tucked it in when I left. All in good shape. Quiet spot today. 

I discover two trackables and we grabbed two trackables. Found with CCF to finish our finds here. Thanks for the hide!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360470369"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-10T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="334784">CCFsmile</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I have no idea how I forgot to log this, but I did. A day late but not a dollar short?! We were out grabbing a few nearby caches and had this on the radar too. Short bushwack... found with BevanQ on a nice Spring afternoon. TFTC tenebrus :-) </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1357378455"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="411445">Fink007</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found this afternoon with sjfink, RyanXY, and HayBeth.  We've found the two previous CAA caches for New York, so decided to grab this one today while passing by.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="34.8441" lon="-92.478867"><time>2006-09-29T08:13:12</time><name>EHYJKN</name><cmt>This is the Eastern Trailhead of the Pinnacle Mountian Base Trail</cmt><desc>Base Trail East Trailhead</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=d617b228-b2b3-4f86-a470-2c9c70ddebec</url><urlname>Base Trail East Trailhead</urlname><sym>Trailhead</sym><type>Waypoint|Trailhead</type></wpt><wpt lat="34.83878333333333" lon="-92.49121666666667"><time>2006-09-29T08:16:26</time><name>WHYJKN</name><cmt>This is the Western Trailhead of the Pinnacle Mountian Base Trail</cmt><desc>Base Trail West Trailhead</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=cd945626-4d96-4532-8f50-96ac8b9e1780</url><urlname>Base Trail West Trailhead</urlname><sym>Trailhead</sym><type>Waypoint|Trailhead</type></wpt><wpt lat="37.413033" lon="-122.069133"><time>2018-08-16T10:04:15</time><name>01XWRQ</name><cmt>Park at the end of LaAvenida St. You can pick up the original Jasmer on the way.</cmt><desc>Parking</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=a1208e43-734d-42cc-b26c-9bfc7ba81852</url><urlname>Parking</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="39.98115" lon="-105.57896666666667"><time>2007-03-04T19:09:16</time><name>PAX482</name><cmt /><desc>parking area</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=2d920726-b6d1-43fa-aaa7-98dbbd703bf4</url><urlname>parking area</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="41.821866666666665" lon="-72.48023333333333"><time>2006-09-12T15:57:40</time><name>01Y9H4</name><cmt /><desc>Parking Area</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=7d0bd7fd-3c6f-4c2a-a910-7fe95a8e37a9</url><urlname>Parking Area</urlname><sym>Parking Area</sym><type>Waypoint|Parking Area</type></wpt><wpt lat="28.91415" lon="-81.544583"><time>2024-05-02T10:13:08</time><name>AAYXHW</name><cmt>Mount up Posse! Let's hit the trail.</cmt><desc>Start</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=a79f28b3-8e07-413c-9477-6ce21f3fd553</url><urlname>Start</urlname><sym>Physical Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Physical Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="0" lon="0"><time>2006-10-22T07:25:27</time><name>BBYXHW</name><cmt>Yippee Ki Yi Yee, get along little doggies! </cmt><desc>Stage 2</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=7ccea6f8-e40d-4239-8663-32e70d8bdda2</url><urlname>Stage 2</urlname><sym>Physical Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Physical Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="0" lon="0"><time>2006-10-22T07:24:21</time><name>CCYXHW</name><cmt>You can lead a horse to water...</cmt><desc>Stage 3</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/seek/wpt.aspx?WID=f83ca01c-08de-4537-b3b3-ebbce7cca66d</url><urlname>Stage 3</urlname><sym>Physical Stage</sym><type>Waypoint|Physical Stage</type></wpt><wpt lat="0" lon="0"><time>2024-05-02T10:13:0